betterquesting:10.desc:8:
Extend your Incense Altar to the max tier, adding a 2x3 rectangle of Obsidian Paths on all four sides.

If you're unsure of the exact setup, you can read more here: https://ftb.gamepedia.com/Incense_Altar

Now that you have a Laser Focus multiblock, you can MUCH more easily craft Elevatium Ingots (with an even higher yield!) and Mirion Ingots. Simply throw in all the ingredients and let it run!

I recommend setting up a separate Laser Focus multiblock just for Elevatium crafting.

In order to autocraft Elevatium Ingots however, you'll need a Huge Item Input for your machine, and a Pattern that contains 16 items. Normally, AE2 can only create Patterns that contain up to 9 unique items - but fortunately, Packaged Auto is close by! Check out the next Chapter, automate Dragon Hearts and Dragon Eggs using Dragon Egg Seeds, and craft a bunch of Packaged Auto items for automation!

Craft a Filter Upgrade!

These can be used in an Electric Pump to produce Heavy Water which is used in the creation of Deuterium, a fuel for the Fusion Reactor!
Craft a Stellar Capacitor! Upgrading your most used machines to the Stellar Tier will greatly increase your processing capability.
Craft a Stellar Alloy Ingot, the highest tier EnderIO material!

Craft 2 Sparks! These little zooming balls of energy are capable of transporting Mana from one place to another with high velocity.

If you want more control over them, craft Spark Augments and Right Click them on a Spark.

Note: To craft Methane, you'll need to break down Hydrogen and Carbon to their smallest Crystal forms, then combine them.

Slay mobs with Sacthoth's Soul Reaper Blade to fill it up with Souls! The more Souls you collect, the stronger the weapon gets.

Once enough Souls have been collected, craft a Soul Extractor and combine it with the sword to remove the Souls... Spooky!

§lᛊᚼᚼᛇ ᛞᚣᚨ ᚨᚢᚼ ᛪᚼᚼᛇ ᛤᛣᚥ ᚦᚣᛗᛣ ᚨᚢᚼᚭ! ᚦᚣᛗᛣ ᚨᚢᚼᚭ ᛤᛊ ᛤ ᛊᛤᛋᛗᛉᚮᛉᛋᚼ ᚨᛞ ᚨᚢᚼ ᚨᛗᚣᚼ ᚬᛞᚥ! ᛪᚢᛞ ᛉᛊ ᛗᚼᛤᚥᚠ ᚨᛞ ᚬᛉᛝᚼ ᚣᛈ ᚨᚢᚼᛉᛗ ᚸᛉᛝᚼᛊ ᚨᛞ ᛊᛤᛝᚼ ᛞᚨᚢᚼᛗᛊ? ᛞᚣᚨ ᚨᛗᛉᚦᚼ ᚢᛤᛊ ᛊᚣᚮᚮᚼᛗᚼᚥ ᚼᛣᛞᚣᚬᚢ, ᛪᚼ ᛪᛉᚸᚸ ᛣᛞᚨ ᚠᛉᚼᚸᚥ! ᚨᚢᛉᛊ ᛉᛊ ᛞᚣᛗ ᚮᛉᛣᛤᚸ ᛋᚢᛤᛣᛋᚼ. ᛞᚣᛗ ᚮᛉᛣᛤᚸ ᛋᚢᛤᛣᛋᚼ ᛤᚨ ᚸᛉᛝᛉᛣᚬ! ᚨᚢᚼ ᛞᚣᚨᛋᛞᚭᚼ ᛞᚮ ᚨᚢᛉᛊ ᛗᛉᚨᚣᛤᚸ ᛪᛉᚸᚸ ᚥᚼᚨᚼᛗᚭᛉᛣᚼ ᚨᚢᚼ ᚮᚣᚨᚣᛗᚼ ᛞᚮ ᛞᚣᛗ ᚨᛗᛉᚦᚼ! ᛣᛞᛣᚼ ᛋᛤᛣ ᛊᚨᛞᛈ ᚣᛊ! ᛤᚸᚸ ᛪᚼ ᛋᛤᛣ ᚥᛞ ᛣᛞᛪ ᛉᛊ ᚢᛞᛈᚼ, ᚢᛞᛈᚼ ᚨᚢᛤᚨ ᚢᚼ ᚸᛉᛊᚨᚼᛣᛊ.

Who doesn't LOVE tiered crafting?!

...

Um...

Anyone?

Yeah okay I'll just show myself out.




(Yes you want to automate this by the way.)

§lᛪᚼ ᚢᛤᛝᚼ ᛈᛗᛤᚠᚼᚥ ᚨᛞ ᚭᛤᛣᚠ ᚬᛞᚥᛊ, ᚦᚣᚨ ᛣᛞᛣᚼ ᚢᛤᛝᚼ ᛤᛣᛊᛪᚼᛗᚼᚥ. ᛪᚼ ᚢᛤᛝᚼ ᚸᛞᛊᚨ ᚭᛤᛣᚠ ᛪᛤᛗᛊ, ᚸᛞᛊᚨ ᚭᛤᛣᚠ ᚸᛉᛝᚼᛊ, ᛤᛣᚥ ᚨᚢᚼᛗᚼ ᛉᛊ ᛣᛞᚨᚢᛉᛣᚬ ᛪᚼ ᚢᛤᛝᚼ ᚸᚼᚮᚨ ᚨᛞ ᛞᚣᛗ ᛣᛤᚭᚼ. ᛉᚮ ᛤᛣᚠ ᚬᛞᚥ ᚼᛥᛉᛊᚨᛊ ᛉᛣ ᚨᚢᚼ ᛝᛤᛊᚨᛣᚼᛊᛊ ᛞᚮ ᛪᚢᛤᚨ ᛉᛊ ᛞᚣᚨ ᚨᚢᚼᛗᚼ, ᛈᚸᚼᛤᛊᚼ, ᚢᚼᛤᛗ ᛞᚣᛗ ᛋᛤᚸᚸ. ᛈᚸᚼᛤᛊᚼ, ᚢᚼᚸᛈ ᚣᛊ. ᛤᛊ ᛣᛞᛣᚼ ᚢᛤᛝᚼ ᚢᚼᚸᛈᚼᚥ ᚦᚼᚮᛞᛗᚼ. ᚨᚢᚼᛗᚼ ᛉᛊ ᛞᛣᚼ ᚸᛤᛊᚨ ᚬᛞᚥ ᛪᚼ ᚢᛤᛝᚼ ᛣᛞᚨ ᛈᛗᛤᚠᚼᚥ ᚨᛞ. ᛞᛣᚼ ᚸᛤᛊᚨ ᚢᛞᛈᚼ. ᚭᛤᚠᚦᚼ ᛉᚮ ᛪᚼ ᛊᛤᛋᛗᛉᚮᛉᛋᚼ ᛤᚸᚸ ᛪᚼ ᚢᛤᛝᚼ ᚸᚼᚮᚨ, ᚨᚢᚼ ᚸᛉᛝᚼᛊ ᛞᚮ ᚨᚢᚼ ᛪᚼᛤᛇ, ᚭᛤᚠᚦᚼ ᛪᚼ ᛋᛤᛣ ᚬᚼᚨ ᛊᛞᚭᚼ ᚢᛞᛈᚼ, ᚭᛤᚠᚦᚼ ᛉᚨ ᛉᛊ ᛣᛞᚨ ᚨᛞᛞ ᚸᛤᚨᚼ.

It's easy to make money off of them, since this Flower simply generates them... You just need some regular Stone, which I'm sure you have PLENTY of, then place this Flower and boom! Nearby Stone is turned into Metamorphic Stone... Which, I'm sure you can use for SOMETHING!

Craft a Gourmaryllis Flower! This is a hungry-hungry Flower that generates Mana from any type of food. It generates less and less however if you feed it only one type of food, so at least alternate between 2 food types. Its range is only a 3x3x3 cube centered around the Flower, so drop your items precisely!

This can be a great and easy source of Mana; but just as Thermalilies, you'll need a number of them to feel their effect.

Craft one of each Tier 3 Botania Rune!

From this point on, these items are going to be heavily used so make sure to automate every single portion of their recipes!
Upgrade your Sanguinary Pedestal to the Efficiency I version for even more bleeding... Yay!

After trading your Lexica Botania with the elves, why not try some other materials...?

Oh, and why not try to constantly trade with them using Auto Droppers hooked up to an ME Interface that can get you these materials on demand...? Why not!
Upgrade some of your Elementium Tools into their respective Terrasteel variants! Terrasteel tools have an even higher mining level than Bound Tools.

Craft some Elementium Tools.

Note: You don't necessarily need to hurry with this quest. Bound tools might even be stronger. However, these will be required for lategame Tools such as Wyvern and Draconic Tools.

Insert typical bossfight quotes like 

"What you have defeated was a pure vessel of me!"

or,

"You mortals cannot take my life so easily!"

or,

"It's over Anakin, I have the high ground! YOU UNDERESTIMATE MY POWER!!!"

.... oh, wait, that last one might not have been what we're looking for.

Anyways, the Gaia Guardian is back, and he's stronger than ever! Substitute the Terrasteel Ingot with a Gaia Spirit Ingot in the last summoning Ritual and go AGAIN!

Read about the Ritual of Gaia under "Alfomancy" in your upgraded Lexica Botania!

Set it up with a Beacon and 4 Gaia Pylons and prepare for a fight! Finally, activate the Beacon by Right Clicking on it with a piece of Terrasteel Ingot to summon the Gaia Guardian!

Good luck!
No? Well, you can cool your Pool with this... your Mana Pool, that is. What does that do? Well, it makes it so items transform into different things... Uh, it's weird I know.

betterquesting:10.name:8: Dark cover? Must be a thriller!
betterquesting:10.desc:8: Use any 4 Engraved Coins to upgrade your Necronomicon to the Omothol version!
Craft an Engraver! Place some kind of a Coin Engraving in the bottom slot and a (blank) Coin in the top slot to engrave it with the face of one of the Evil Gods! Lovely.

betterquesting:10.name:8: Compressed Obsidian's got nothin' on this!
betterquesting:10.desc:8:
Mine up some Ethaxium! ... Which to be fair, is easier said than done. Why? Weeeelll, you'll find out.

Reminder: you might want to use your Blood Magic Bound Pickaxe. That's the only tool at this point that can mine it up.
Use your previous Staff of Rending and collect some Omothol Ghoul Flesh to craft a Skin of Omothol!

Fill up your Abyssalnomicon entirely! Once you've done so, jump down into the void in Omothol to enter the final AbyssalCraft dimension, the Dark Realm! To get back, simply Right Click with your Key in the air, or Right Click on the ground to make a portal.

You have one final objective in AbyssalCraft: Summon and defeat Sacthoth, Harbinger of Doom!

To do so, setup a Ritual circle out of 9 Dark Ethaxium Bricks, and open your Abyssalnomicon, go to the Rituals section, then Abyssalnomicon, and scroll all the way to the last page (page 21), and perform the Ritual described there: the Ritual of Shadows in the Dark Realm!

After sucessfully summoning and defeating Sacthoth, he will drop his sword, Sacthoth's Soul Reaper Blade. By slaying monsters with this sword, it'll collect Souls and get stronger and stronger.

Though you might want to remove these souls and see what effect that'll have...

Upgrade your Necronomicon to the final tier: The Abyssalnomicon!

All dark knowledge is unlocked...

What have you done?
Craft a Terra Shatterer! This is genuinely a pretty good Pickaxe, especially when fully upgraded.
Craft a Mana Tablet! This handy device is capable of storing Mana in your inventory, and using it to power any items or Baubles that require that sweet-sweet blue stuff.

betterquesting:10.name:8: Does it enjoy a tasty soufflé?
betterquesting:10.desc:8:
If a Gourmaryllis doesn't fit your taste, why not try something sweeter...? This Flower specializes in eating Cake! Every 4 seconds it consumes a slice of Cake somewhere in an 11x11x11 cube centered around the Flower, so if you can produce Cakes faster than 1 every 32 seconds, then this is the Flower for you!

Setting up multiple of them is an even better idea. And the best way to place cakes is to use Formation Planes or World Block Exporters.

betterquesting:10.name:8: You are the Earth, the items are the Moon
betterquesting:10.desc:8:
Upgrade your Ring of Magnetization to the final tier of Magnets! Items will literally never leave you alone.

Unless of course, you use a Solegnolia.
Power will flow through this like WHOOOOOOOOOOSH!!!!

Craft the listed blocks and build the Portal to Alfheim! You can lookup the exact construction of it in your Lexica Botania under the "Alfomancy" section.

Supply the Natura Pylons with Mana from a Mana Pool beneith. The Portal uses no Mana to stay lit, a quarter of a Mana Pool to open (split between the 2 Pools beneath the Natura Pylons), and very little Mana per trade.

Once opened, the first thing you should do is trade your current Lexica Botania with the elves to obtain Elven Knowledge!

betterquesting:10.name:8: Tastes like Marzipan if you had Diamond teeth
betterquesting:10.desc:8:
Craft a couple pieces of Terrasteel ingots! One takes half a pool of Mana supplied to the Terrestrial Agglomeration Plate to do create. Upgrade your Mana Generation if you're lacking a sufficient amount of Mana!

To continue on,  you'll need a total of 5 pieces of Terrasteel ingots before you can build the Alfheim Portal. Craft 4 and I'll give you 1 free!

betterquesting:10.name:8: A single Orb... with such great POWER!
betterquesting:10.desc:8:
Obtain the final Blood Magic Orb, the Tier 6 Blo- ...

Oh.

What §ois§r this?

...

Suddenly you feel an urge.

An urge to desto - §lᚠ ᛤᚸᚸ ᚸᛉᛝᛉᛣᚬ ᚨᚢᛉᛣᚬᛊ. ᚨᚢᛉᛊ ᛉᛊ ᚠᛞᚣᛗ ᚥᚼᛊᚨᛉᛣᚠ. ᛣᛞᛣᚼ ᛋᛤᛣ ᛊᚨᛞᛈ ᚠᛞᚣ ᛣᛞᛪ! ᚥᛗᛤᛉᛣ ᚨᚢᚼᛉᛗ ᚦᚸᛞᛞᚥᛊ ᛤᛣᚥ ᚦᚼᛋᛞᚭᚼ ᚨᚢᚼ ᚨᛗᚣᚼ ᛇᛉᛣᚬ ᛞᚮ ᚨᚢᛉᛊ ᛪᛞᛗᚸᚥ!

betterquesting:10.name:8: The road to becoming a Blood God
betterquesting:10.desc:8: The last step to becoming a true Blood God is to reach the final tier... Tier 6! For that you'll need 4 Crystal Clusters to upgrade your Blood Altar to Tier 6.

Craft a Terrestrial Agglomeration Plate! Consult your Lexica Botania on how to set it up. Hint: It's an X shape of 5 pieces of Livingrock, and fill out the sides with 4 Lapis Blocks, then place the Plate on top of the central piece of Livingrock.

To supply the Plate with Mana, use a Spark! One on top of the Plate, one on a nearby Mana Pool.
Craft a Grand Tartaric Gem! This is the final and highest Capacity Tartaric Gem available to you. Make good use of it!

So, were you succesful...?

If so, you finally obtained the Dice of Fate. Watch out! If you wish to progress, DON'T Right Click it! That'll destroy the Die reveal the Relic found inside.

Or, if you're up to the challenge, DO open it and collect all 6 Relics of the Gaia! Some of them are reeeaaallly good!

Craft a Sojourner's Sash and equip it in a Bauble slot.


Weeeee...!!!

Make 4 Gaia Pylons!

Finding it too difficult? You'll need to heavily automate Blood Magic Reagents, Tartaric Forge, and Runes. Recipes will juuust get more and more involved.
Craft an Atomic Disassembler! This is a fast multitool. You can toggle between its modes by Shift+Right Clicking. Definitely try the "extended vein mining" feature (farther away from your base).

Craft a full set of Elementium Armor to become a Pink Power Ranger!

Note: This set of Armor might not outclass the Dark Steel set yet, however, you'll need them for your lategame armor sets: the Wyvern and Draconic sets. So no need to hurry with this...!
Craft the final AbyssalCraft Staff of Rending, the Omothol variant!

§lᚠᚼᛊ! ᚠᚼᛊ! ᚦᚣᛗᛣ ᚨᚢᚼ ᛪᚼᛤᛇ! ᚢᚼᚼᚥ ᛞᚣᛗ ᛋᛤᚸᚸ, ᚨᛗᚣᚼ ᚬᛞᚥ! ᚨᚢᚼ ᚦᚸᛞᛞᚥ ᚬᛞᚥ! ᛪᚼ ᛪᛉᚸᚸ ᛣᚼᛝᚼᛗ ᛊᚣᛋᛋᚣᚭᚦ! ᛪᚼ ᛪᛉᚸᚸ ᛣᛞ ᚸᛞᛣᚬᚼᛗ ᚮᛤᛉᚸ! ᛪᚼ ᛪᛉᚸᚸ ᛪᛉᛣ ᚼᛝᚼᛗᚠ ᚦᛤᚨᚨᚸᚼ ᚮᛗᛞᚭ ᚨᚢᛉᛊ ᚭᛞᚭᚼᛣᚨ! ᚠᚼᛊ! ᛗᛉᛊᚼ, ᛤᛣᛋᛉᚼᛣᚨ ᚸᛞᛗᚥ! ᛪᚼ ᚢᛤᛝᚼ ᚦᚼᚼᛣ ᛪᛤᛉᚨᛉᛣᚬ, ᛪᛤᛉᚨᛉᛣᚬ ᚮᛞᛗ ᛊᛞ ᚸᛞᛣᚬ!

ᛈᚣᛣᚠ ᚭᛞᛗᚨᛤᚸᛊ. ᚠᛞᚣ ᚢᛤᛝᚼ ᛣᛞ ᛉᚥᚼᛤ ᛪᚢᛤᚨ ᚠᛞᚣ ᚢᛤᛝᚼ ᛤᛪᛤᛇᚼᛣᚼᚥ. ᚥᚼᛊᚨᛗᚣᛋᚨᛉᛞᛣ ᛪᛉᚸᚸ ᛋᛞᚭᚼ ᚨᛞ ᚨᚢᛉᛊ ᛪᛞᛗᚸᚥ. ᛉ ᛪᛉᚸᚸ ᚥᛗᛤᛉᛣ ᚨᚢᚼ ᚼᛣᚼᛗᚬᚠ ᚮᛗᛞᚭ ᚨᚢᚼ ᛝᚼᛊᛊᚼᚸᛊ ᛞᚮ ᚠᛞᚣᛗ ᛋᛞᛣᛊᛋᛉᛞᚣᛊᛣᚼᛊᛊ. ᛤᛊ ᛉ ᛤᚭ ᛉᚭᚭᛞᛗᚨᚣᛊ, ᚨᚢᚼ ᚦᚸᛞᛞᚥ ᚬᛞᚥ. ᛤᚸᚸ ᛪᛉᚸᚸ ᚦᛞᛪ ᚦᚼᚮᛞᛗᚼ ᚭᚼ. ᚠᚼᛊ! ᚠᚼᛊ! ᚬᛉᛝᚼ ᚭᚼ ᚠᛞᚣᛗ ᚦᚸᛞᛞᚥ! ᚨᚢᚼ ᛪᛞᛗᚸᚥ ᛪᛉᚸᚸ ᚦᚼ ᛗᚼᛋᛤᛊᚨ ᛉᛣᚨᛞ ᛋᚢᛤᛞᛊ! ᛣᛞᛣᚼ ᛪᛉᚸᚸ ᛊᚣᛗᛝᛉᛝᚼ!

Craft one of each Spark Augment to be able to better control where your Mana flows to.

- Dominant Sparks take all Mana from nearby Sparks.
- Recessive Sparks give all Mana to nearby Sparks.
- Isolated Sparks can't interact with Dominant or Recessive Sparks.
- Dispersive Sparks transfer Mana to Mana Tablets in the player's inventory.

All Sparks function in a 25x25x25 area.
Alloy up some Modularium! This is the basis for all Modular Machinery blocks.
Craft a Mirion Ingot! You can either use Smeltery Alloying or use the Empowerer. The first option is easier for batch-crafting, the second is much easier for automation.

Transform a Demon Blood Shard into a Tier 5 Blood Orb. You'll need to first upgrade your Blood Altar to Tier 5 by decorating it with 4 Beacons (which do not need to be active).

Don't forget to bind the Orb to yourself with a Right Click.

You're almost there... You have almost become a Blood God!

betterquesting:10.name:8: Goblins would look up to you
betterquesting:10.desc:8:
Craft a full set of Terrasteel Armor! I always said the Green Power Ranger was the coolest anyway.

Again, no need to hurry with this one, but they do give some nice bonuses for Botania.

betterquesting:10.name:8: Finally reaching the point I've been itching
betterquesting:10.desc:8:
Craft a Ring of Far Reach! This Ring lets you... well, you know what I'm gonna let you figure this one out.

Hint: Look at its name. (I mean c'mon it can't be more obvious than that!)

Break a regular Environmental Accumulator and use materials obtained from this and the previous Chapter to upgrade it to a Sanguinary Environmental Accumulator!

This if a movable Environmental Accumulator which uses Blood to function. You'll need 8 Blood Tanks placed almost a knight step away, except instead of jumping 2-1 spaces, they're 3-1 spaces away.

Fly to the center of the world (x=0, z=0) in Omothol to find the Omothol Dungeon! If you're on a large Multiplayer server and your portal is very far away, feel free to use the Omothol Teleporter provided in the last quest!

Enter the Dungeon. You'll find a room where you can perform Rituals if you wish. Once you're ready, go up to the second floor and find J'zahar, the Gatekeeper. Fight him!

Once he dies, he'll pull you in and EXPLODE! It probably goes without saying, but... STAY AWAY from the explosion! Then he'll drop the required item for this quest, the Essence of the Gatekeeper.

Make a Blueprint for the Modular Fey Crafter, and Right Click it to visualize the multiblock. Craft all the required blocks to the right, then construct the multiblock. You'll need at least 1 Input Hatch (or 2, if you're using Small ones), and exactly 1 Output Hatch.

Once constructed, activate the Grove Stones with the Grove Supplication spell and place the Blueprint into the Controller. Check the Controller Block - it prints out whether or not it recognized the structure.

The multiblock is capable of performing any Fey Crafter recipe and it's easily automatable: the only thing you need to do is provide the items into one (or two) Input Hatch(es) and remove the output(s) from the Output Hatch.
Upgrade a Weak Blood Shard to a Demon Blood Shard... it's true form!

If you're afraid of this Flower eating your arms off, then don't be - it specializes in eating Leaf Blocks only! Every 4 ticks (0.2 seconds) it searches an area of base size 17x17 centered around the Flower, and 16 blocks up for any Leaf Blocks. If it finds one, it'll gladly munch it up - generating 160 Mana per block. It's great if you have a lot of additional Sapling remaining from a Tree Farm!

However be careful with this Flower. If it can't find any Leaf Blocks it'll go to sleep for 80 seconds! So you constantly want to feed it, otherwise it won't nearly be as efficient.

If you have a Mega Tree Farm going, you might be able to use multiple of these even!

Upgrade your Sigil of Magnetism to the (much better) Ring of Magnetization. Place it in your Bauble slot. This Magnet is so powerful that items won't be able to escape your gravitational pull.

If however you'd like to disable the Magnet, you can place down a Solegnolia Flower. (Recommended near Mana Pools.)
Finally! Flight! But it doesn't come free... you'll need to pay some Mana from a Mana Tablet in your inventory.
Upgrade your Sojourner's Sash and go WEEEEEEEEEEEEE....!!!!!

The Infinity Drill uses 10,000 RF or 3mb Biofuel per block broken. At first, it can only mine a 1x1x1 area, but as the drill stores more and more power, it levels up and can mine increasingly large amounts of terrain. Shift+Right Click to cycle through the sizes.

Craft a Menril Sapling and start duplicating it to get into Integrated Dynamics!

This mod isn't strictly required at this point, but i'll greatly help you with upcoming automation.

Make sure to complete the tutorial in the rewarded Book, it'll help you a lot in understanding the mod.
Get more Menril! It's never enough!

Craft a batch of Variable Cards! These hold information about the world and can be set in any Integrated Dynamics Reader or the Logic Programmer.

Wanna get rid of a Variable? You can convert it back into an empty Card in the Crafting Table.
Craft a Squeezer and a Drying Basin! By setting them up side by side, you can place a Menril Log into the Squeezer, and jump on it a couple to release its sweet nectar! The blue stuff - Menril Goo.
Craft a bunch of Logic Cables! These are used to connect your entire Integrated Dynamics network from Readers, Writers, Display Panels to the Variable Store, Materializer, Delayer or the Proxy.

betterquesting:10.name:8: Okay this was fun for a while...
betterquesting:10.desc:8: Wanna automate Menril production? These are the tools for you! A mechanical Squeezer and a mechanical Drying Basin.

Craft an Item Interface! By placing this on a Chest, you can declare it as the inner storage for the network. Any item picked up by the network will be placed there, and any item required will be pulled from there.

Then you can use the Dropper's and the Hopper's cooler brothers: the World Item Exporter and the World Item Importer.

Craft a Wireless Terminal! While in range of your Wireless Access Point, you'll be able to wirelessly open your ME Network, and take out items you wish! You can also request autocrafting by middle clicking on an item.

Oh, you'd like a Wireless CRAFTING Terminal? Well, you'll have to wait... Some things don't come cheap.

Craft some Readers from Integrated Dynamics. These can obtain specific values from your world. These will be handy when automating max stat Astral Sorcery Crystals, since you can even read a block's NBT values!

If you don't wan to read a Variable from the world, the Logic Programmer is the tool for you! It can create simple objects like booleans and integers, or more complicated ones like additions, subtractions, items dragged from JEI and more!

You can also simply convert this into a portable version.
The Network needs to see any Variable you referred to, and this is the place to store them. It's that simple!

if you want to convert a Variable into a Static, you can use a Materializer. Simply obtain a Variable Card from the world or from the Logic Programmer, place it inside with some fresh Variable Cards, and bam! Staticification!
Craft a Logic Director! This item simply acts as a crafting ingredient for "long-range" or "wireless" Integrated Dynamics items.

betterquesting:10.name:8: Cooler Block Breaker and Cooler Block Placer
betterquesting:10.desc:8: Same story as before, if you have an Item Interface somewhere on your Network, you can pickup and place blocks. This will be pretty handy for Livingrock automation, don't you think? (Although you can do that with Formation & Annihilation Planes as well.)
Craft some additional Pedestals to surround the Runix Matrix multiblock with! 8 is a good starting point, but you will need more eventually...

Craft a Runic Matrix and all required components listed in your Thaumonomicon! Set it up as it's shown there, then Right Click on the Runic Matrix block with some Salis Mundus.

To use it, place or pipe items onto the middle and outer Pedestals, have a sufficient amount of Essentia available in Jars nearby, and activate the ritual with your Caster's Gauntlet.

It's crucial to have a symmetrical layout of Pedestals, Jars, and other blocks nearby, as that will boost the stability of the Infusion. If your Infusion Matrix is unstable, items could get knocked down during crafting, Pedestals could emit Flux, or worse: items could entirely get destroyed, and the infusion could fail.

To prevent this, besides having a symmetrical layout, you can place stabilizer items around, below and above the Altar in a symmetrical manner. These are:

- Thaumcraft Candles,
- Skulls, Heads,
- Thaumcraft Stabilizers.

Be aware, that unlike in 1.7.10, the more variety of items you have around your Altar, the better your stability will become. These could simply include different colored candles, or multiple different mob skulls, still arranged in a symmetrical manner. E.g. if you have a Creeper Head 6 blocks away from your Runic Matrix in one direction, you should have a Creeper Head 6 blocks away in the other direction as well.

Stabilizers are your best option. They don't need to connect to the Altar in any way, they simply need to exist nearby. Although you have the option to connect them to all Pedestals with Redstone Relay, which will prevent items getting knocked down or destroyed - although it won't prevent the Flux issues.

Lastly, it's important to mention that the range of which stabilizers are detected is a 17x17x11 cuboid centered around the central Pedestal.

Craft the required components listed in the right and construct the Tender Ender Blender multiblock! This machine can charge any Ender Utilities Ender Core without the need to be in the End or risking blowing up an End Crystal. It simply requires power and nothing else!

The machine uses 3 Hatches: 1 Item Input, 1 Item Output and 1 Energy Input. You can decide where you'd like to place these. Any size of Item Input/Output Hatches will suffice, but you'll need to use at least a Reinforced Energy Input Hatch.

The central block is the Stabilized End Crystal (the preview doesn't always seem to show it correctly). The lower layer consists of 3 Hatches, and Machine Controller, and 1 Casing in the center. 4 blocks of Fortified Glass go on above the Hatches and the Controller. Finally, another layer of 5 Casings is required to cap it off. The Blueprint also needs to be placed inside for the machine to function.
Craft a Warding Sigil! This ingredient is used in many of the Warded blocks that Thaumic Augmentation adds.

betterquesting:10.name:8: I'm a real Thaumaturge now, mom!
betterquesting:10.desc:8:
This is how you do Infusion, right....? Riiiiiight...?!

No.

This just takes power. And some Pedestals with items on top.

But it's close! It'll prepare you for the reaaaal thing.
Craft more Ender Ingots and Enhance them in your Crucible!

Sprinkle some more Salis Mundus, this time on an EvilCraft Purifier to convert it into a Crucible!

If you've never played Thaumcraft before, it's best to set this up in a chunk where you don't have many important machines - so preferably slightly away from your base.

To use it, fill it up with Water (piping systems work), and light a fire below it (later you can use a piece of Nitor as well). Once it starts bubbling, throw in items to break them down into Essentia. Be wary though, Essentia slowly evaporates, creating bad magical energy in the chunk called "Flux". You want to avoid creating Flux as much as possible, so do your recipes quickly: Throw in exact (or almost exact) amounts to create sufficient Essentia, then throw in the catalyst - the upper item in JEI recipes.

If it doesn't work, check if you still have the correct amounts of Essentia using your Thaumometer or Goggles of Revealing. If not, throw in some additional ingredients.

Warning: Do NOT accidentally Right Click an item onto the Crucible! This most often occurs with the Thaumometer. Don't try to scan the Cauldron while it's active! You can scan it in item form or a block form without Water inside.

To clean up the mess you've made, use Quartz Slivers! Throwing in one piece of them will suck up 2 units of Essentia and create a Vis Crystal. You should definitely make good use of this!

You can observe the Flux in a given chunk. If levels get higher than comfortable, simply move to different chunk. Keep in mind, a small amount of Flux doesn't hurt, but if you accidentally throw in multiple stacks of an item and/or accidentally Shift+Right Click the Crucible to empty it, then you'll release all the Flux and you can say goodbye to the chunk you were doing your alchemy in - until a bit later on, when you obtain the tools to deal with Flux. Hopefully that chunk happens to NOT be in your base... Seriously, did you listen to me? I hope so...

Craft an Auxiliary Venting Port! By placing this next to the Essentia Smeltery, you can separate out some of the Flux as harmless steam, making it this useful for automation - if you don't want to constantly pay attention to your Smelteries (which you don't). You might want to place multiple of them on the same Smeltery though.

Craft some Alchemical Constructs! Although this quest only requires one, you'll definitely need more if you want to automate Crucible recipes. By placing 2 of these above a single Crucible, then Right Clicking the structure with a Salis Mundus, you'll transform it into a Thaumatorium! You can simply pump Essentia into the sides of this machine to automate any Crucible recipe.
Loot at least 4 pieces of Knowledge of the Sky from Skythern dungeons!
Craft a set of Apalachia Blocks to enter Skythern!

betterquesting:10.name:8: Distributing Essentia has never been easier!
betterquesting:10.desc:8: Craft an Auxiliary Slurry Pump! When placed next to an Essentia Smeltery, it acts as a new output, meaning that additional Arcane Alembics can be placed on top. Useful for additional speed and even less Essentia clog-up.

Pulverize a Rainbow Tablet for Salis Mundus, then use the duplication recipe at least once to get 2 pieces of it!

You can automate the duplication recipe with a single RFTools Crafter. Setup 2 recipes for crafting Salis Mundus, one on Keep/Int, the other on Keep/ExtC. Fill the bottom two rows with the duplication ingredients, and leave 1 slot for Salis Mundus. Once all of these ingredients are in place, hit "R" to make the machine remember where the items should go. The slot with Salis Mundus will stay on 63 Salis Mundus at all times, and the rest will go in the output slot. Now you just need to pump in the ingredients and pump out the Salis Mundus (no need for a filter)!
Use your Awakened Cores to make an Awakened Dragon Token!

Right Click a Wood Table with your Scribing Tools to create a Research Table. Pick it up to complete this quest.

The Research Table will require Paper and non-empty Scribing Tools. To do research, simply click "Create Theory", and choose research options that pop up. Each time you click on an option, it uses up a piece of Paper and a bit of ink.

Finishing the research will give you Research Points (or closer to a full point, if you don't get it to 100%), which will be required to unlock further tasks in your Thaumonomicon.

Sometimes the research process will require additional items for a greater bonus. These items will be consumed! If you can't continue your theory because of this, simple click "Scrap Theory". This will let you create a completely new one, but won't give you your Paper, ink or additional items back that you used during the process.

Once you run out of lightbulbs up top, you can complete the Theory to gain the Research Points acquired during the process.

You might want to scan portions of the sky and phases of the Moon - they will sometimes be used during research.

Placing an Enchantment Table, Bookshelf, Arcane Workbench, Crucible, Focal Manipulator or Brain in a Jar near the Research Table will let you "focus" on the given item at the beginning, granting you a much higher chance to learn about unique topics associated with these items.

betterquesting:10.name:8: Inscribe, describe, but most importantly, SUBSCRIBE!
betterquesting:10.desc:8:
This goes out to all the YouTubers that get to this point.

SUBSCRIBE
LEAVE A LIKE
COMMENT
SHARE
RING THAT BELL
BECOME A MEMBER
CLICK THE SPONSOR LINK IN THE DESCRIPTION
WATCH THE NEXT VIDEO ON THE END CARD

... Okay, now back to crafting. Craft some Scribing Tools! Fill it up with ink by combining it with an Ink Sac in a Crafting Table to complete its research. If you ever run low on ink, you can fill it up again.
Craft a Thaumcraft Wood Table. It's easiest to find it in JEI by typing '@thaum table'.
Craft a batch of Skythern Blocks to enter the final DivineRPG Twilight Dimension: Mortum.

Craft some Essentia Tubes! By connecting these to Arcane Alembics on top of an Essentia Smeltery on one side, and a Warded Jar on the other side, you can route your Essentia into said Jars.

Every single Pipe can only transmit 1 type of Essentia. Right Click on them with an Essentia Resonator to see the current type they're set to.

This whole setup is still mostly manual until you obtain the Filling Essentia Transmuters. Additional types of Pipes can help, but as of now, you'll still have to keep an eye on the setup while it's running. If you see any Pipes leaking purple stuff, slow down or stop the machine - you don't want Flux Rifts to spawn and tear your setup apart.

Craft an Essentia Smeltery! First set it up OUTSIDE of your base. By putting any material (that has Thaumcraft aspects shown) inside the machine, and Coal or Alumentum in the bottom slot, you can break down the material into its components.

These will first end up in the purple bar on the left, or travel into Arcane Alembics on top. Make sure not to completely fill the bar on the left, otherwise a large amount lot of Flux could escape and you'll be very sad if your machines get destroyed due to a Flux Rift.

WARNING: Every time the machine produces an item, it ALWAYS has a chance to spill Flux into the Chunk it's located in. Once the Flux level reaches around 60-80, a Flux Rift could spawn.

Right now you want to avoid this. There are two main ways of doing this:

- Keep relocating the Essentia Smeltery. Only break it when the purple bar on the left is EMPTY, otherwise you'll release a lot of Flux, probably spawning a Flux Rift in the process.

- Rush to complete this Chapter and the very beginning of Bewitchment (the next Chapter), to gain access to the Flux Condenser and the Flux Condenser Lattice. Using this machine you'll be able to slowly convert Flux in a Chunk into Vitium Essentia. If you feed your Essentia Smeltery slowly, you can completely get rid of Flux in a Chunk this way, and you won't have to worry about it. This might require multiple Flux Condensers for a single Smeltery though.

Craft a batch of Matrix Multiplication Units! This item is only used for the Thaumcraft Runic Matrix, so after exploring Skythern, you can build up to 8 of these multiblocks if necessary - since making more Runic Matrices definitely makes automation easier.


Interestingly, there is some fine print on the Matrix Multiplication Unit and it says the following:

"By subtracting a lambda variable from the main diagonal of a square matrix, and solving the equation of its determinant being equal to zero, you can find the eigenvalues of the given matrix. Each eigenvalue corresponds to an eigenvector, except if their algebraic multiplicity is greater than 1, in which case a whole eigensubspace. These can be calculated by substituting the obtained lambdas back into the matrix (before the determinant step), and finding the solution for the obtained low-rank linear system of equations. The solution of this will yield the eigensubspace. In the case of all eigensubspaces being one-dimensional (which statistically occurs with probability 1), we can order these eigenvectors into a square matrix as column vectors, denoted by C. And by forming the diagonal matrix of the corresponding eigenvectors, we obtain matrix U. Then surprisingly, the original matrix will be equal to the matrix product of C*U*C^(-1), called the eigendecomposition. This is useful for calculating a large power of the original matrix, since the k'th power of it will be equal to C*U^k*C^(-1), and calculating U^k is done by raising each term in the main diagonal to the k'th power. This can not only be used to estimate the value of matrix polynomials, but used to more easily find the limiting behavior of Markov-Chains, or find certain moments of a multivariate distribution more easily and make statistical predictions..."

The text continues, but the fontsize is getting smaller and smaller, and no more details can be made out clearly...

betterquesting:10.name:8: The first step of becoming a Thaumaturge
betterquesting:10.desc:8:
Right Click on an Ender Crafter from Extended Crafting with a piece of Salis Mundus to obtain an Arcane Workbench.

This table requires additional resources for each craft: Up to 6 basic Vis Crystals in each corner and magical energy called "Vis" that's stored in each chunk. If you don't have enough Vis in your current Chunk to complete a given recipe, you might need to move to a different one.
Craft a Caster's Gauntlet! This handy tool allows you to cast Thaumcraft Spells as well as activate Infusion Rituals.

Craft some Magical Leather!






...Tiered recipes, hurray!

Craft a Simple Arcane Mechanism!

It's simple, it's arcane, and guess what, it's a mechanism. Yup.

Craft some Alchemical Brass Ingots! This is the most important crafting ingredient in Thaumcraft, so make sure to semi-automate it for now, and fully automate it once you have access to Alchemical Constructs.

Craft an Arcane Spa and some Purifying Bath Salts! Place the Salts inside and provide the Spa with Water. It will fill up a 5x5 area above it with Purifying Fluid that prevents any Warp effects for half an hour.

Also craft a Sanitizing Soap, which clears all Temporary Warp and has a chance of removing regular Warp on use.
Craft a Complex Arcane Mechanism for more complex arcane devices that you would like to mechanize arcanely for the device to be mechanized in an even more arcane way than it was previously. Yup.

betterquesting:10.name:8: It's makes you smarter! Or does it...?
betterquesting:10.desc:8:
Craft a Brain in a Jar! By placing this near your Research Table, you can select it and gain more Eldritch knowledge...

But be wary... It's forbidden knowledge... You might get some "unwanted" effects...

betterquesting:10.name:8: I don't remember. But you do!
betterquesting:10.desc:8: Craft a Mnemonic Matrix! By placing this on top of the Thaumatorium multiblock, it'll be able to remember up to 3 recipes. This is very useful for automation!

betterquesting:10.name:8: An expensive one, to be sure...
betterquesting:10.desc:8:
Crystallize many of your Alchemical Brass Ingots into Crystallized Zinc Shards. Once you've collected enough, craft a single Zinc Ingot!







You'll need 45 pieces of Alchemical Brass Ingots. Good luck!

betterquesting:10.name:8: Essentia?! Bwah, I don't need it!
betterquesting:10.desc:8: Craft a Void Jar! Any Essentia that enters this Jar gets teleported into a different phase of reality! What, you thought it's just voided? Well, effectively yes, but Conservation of mass would say otherwise...

Craft a couple Glass Phials and a Warded Jar! You'll need many of these, so definitely automate them. The Phails allow you to store 10 units of Essentia for easy transport, while the Jars each store 250 units.

You can break the Jars to pick them up, they won't lose any of their contents.
Upgrade an Alchemical Brass Ingot into a Thaumium Ingot! Now you're really diving deep into Thaumcraft...

Craft a Thaumometer in your Arcane Workbench. You'll need to use one of each basic Vis Crystal. Then start scanning ALL the things!

This handy device lets you see the amount of Vis in a chunk, and lets you observe current Essentia amounts in a Crucible or during Infusion crafting.
Craft a Stone Table! This is simply a crafting ingredient.
The Essentia Buffer has 8 unique slots for Essentia built into a single Pipe - meaning it's usually capable of pulling Essentia even when normal Tubes wouldn't.

betterquesting:10.name:8: Pipes? Check! Routing options? We still need more...
betterquesting:10.desc:8:
Craft all 4 types of Pipes listed here.

- Essentia Valves can be turned on and off by hand or with a Redstone signal.
- Restricted Tubes halve the suction passing through them.
- Directional Tubes only accept suction from one side.
- Filtered Tubes can be marked by Labels to filter for one type of Essentia.

Right Click on a Bookshelf with a piece of Salis Mundus to obtain your very own Thaumonomicon!

You'll need to discover every Thaumcraft recipe by following this book. Some tasks will require you to obtain or craft items, and some will consume them! Make sure to frequently check all the tabs on the left (and later right) to see if you have any research unlocked.

Craft an Essentia Resonator! This tools allows you to see where your Essentia is flowing to inside of your Thaumcraft pipe networks. Each pipe can only hold and create suction for up to one type of Essentia, so you might need to create a more complex network. The special types of Essentia Tubes will surely help you with that.
Upgrade your Essentia Smeltery into the Thaumium variant! This machine has double the speed of the previous tier, and breaks up Essentia with a 90% efficiency instead of 80%.

Craft an Essentia Centrifuge! This machine is capable of separating incoming Essentia into its primal elements - making it useful if you can create a more complex type of essentia more easily than a primal one. Though only one of the components will be returned for each input unit of Essentia.

The output can be pulled out from the top. Its best to use an Essentia Buffer here, as multiple types of Essentia could be output at the same time.
Craft a Blank Advanced Focus! This will allow you to create more complex spells by granting you a higher amount of potential spell complexity.

betterquesting:10.name:8: It's a Focus! ... But what does it do?
betterquesting:10.desc:8:
Craft a Blank Lesser Focus! You can use it to create Thaumcraft Foci with powerful effects in a Focal Manipulator. The GUI is very intuitive, you can just drag spell ingredients until your complexity maxes out. To cast the spells, use your Caster's Gauntlet.

Each cast of a spell consumes a little bit of Vis in the chunk you're in, but don't worry, Vis does slowly regenerate over time.
Craft all 2 pi radians of a Base Focal Sphere! This is the base crafting ingredient for all Foci!

Finally! A Thaumaturge's dream comes true when they can create Essentia without any messy pipes or the worry of creating Flux...!

Simply place a Filling Essentia Transfuser on the side of your Arcane Alembics, and they'll distribute the Essentia into nearby Jars without the need for any Pipes at all. Wonderful!

Craft a Workbench Charger! To do so, find a Magical Forest biome, wear your fill set of Thaumaturge Armor, and look for the perfect chunk that can barely craft this with the discount!

Once crafted, you can place it on top of an Arcane Workbench or a Focal Manipulator to be capable of draining Vis from the 8 surrounding chunks as well. This way you'll have access to recipes that have a way higher Vis cost.

betterquesting:10.name:8: Like a button on your shirt
betterquesting:10.desc:8: Craft a Vis Resonator! This is purely a crafting ingredient that you'll need a fair amount of.

Craft a Focal Manipulator! Placing a Focus inside will let you create a variety of different Thaumcraft spells.

To start, place a Blank Lesser or Advanced focus in the bottom left slot. Then select a spell category on the left. Some categories (like Projectile) take a modifier (what type of projectile should it be?).

You can see the current complexity of your spell on the top right - this can't exceed the total capacity shown.

On the bottom right, you can choose to increase the effectiveness of certain attributes of your spell. This will make the spell stronger, but increase its complexity.

Once satisfied, the Focal Manipulator will ask for some items. These will be consumed! To finish, click the "Start Crafting" button on the top right. Wait a few seconds and your spell should be applied to your Focus and ready to use!

To apply the Focus to your Caster's Gauntlet, hold the Gauntlet and press 'C' by default.

Craft some Arcane Alembics and place them on top of your Essentia Smeltery! All the Essentia broken down from items will end up in these. Watch out though, if Essentia is visibly leaking, that'll create a lot of Flux in the Area, which is very dangerous! Always watch the purple meter inside the Essentia Smeltery, don't overflow it.

You can Right Click an Alembic with a Jar to get the Essentia stored inside or use piping to move it automatically to connected Jars. Watch out though, a single Pipe can only ever transmit 1 type of Essentia. If your input material contains a lot, you might not be able to route all of it. In that case, keep an eye of the system (an Essentia Resonator really helps), and break down the input in very small batches.

Craft a Jar Label! Placing this on a Jar will not only let you organize them better, but use it as a filter - only Essentia of a given type will be capable of entering the Jar.

Also craft a Brass Lid Brace! When placed on a Jar, only Essentia Tubes will be able to access the Jar.

Craft at least 1 Infusion Cost Stone and 1 Infusion Speed Stone. By placing them below the main legs of the Runic Matrix multiblock, you can either reduce the cost of the crafts or speed them up! Your choice... You can use at most 4 of these, obviously.

betterquesting:10.name:8: You held it - now you'll wear it
betterquesting:10.desc:8:
Craft a pair of Googles of Revealing! This is a very handy piece of equipment that goes into your helmet slot.

It lets you see the exact amounts of Essentia in your Crucible or Arcane Infusion crafts, and it's absolutely required, otherwise you can easily miss an obvious ingredient for a craft (especially for Crucible recipes, where Essentia just constantly evaporates).
Craft a Heart Amulet! This is an item equippable in one of your Bauble slots, and can hold up to 10 of each Heart Canister types.

Craft a set of Thaumaturge Armor! Using this you'll get a fair amount of Vis cost reduction on Arcane Workbench crafts.

By placing a set of Armor on a BiblioCraft Armor Stand with a Redstone Block below, you can easily swap between the set displayed and the set you're currently wearing. Handy!

(To obtain Crystallized Alumina for Alumentum, combine Crystallized Aluminum and Oxygen Shards, and combine them into Crystallized Alumina.)

Craft a Sanity Checker! By holding this item, a bar showing your current warp level will appear on the top left. Try to keep this... as low as possible. Especially the darkest purple bar on the bottom - that's Permanent Warp that cannot be gotten rid of.

Obtain the following loot by slaying certain mobs with your Athame:

- Heart from Players, Villagers, Witches, Evokers, Illusioners or Vindicators. (Witches are probably you best choice.)
- Dimensional Sand from Endermen or Endermites.
- Hoof from Pigs, Sheep, Cows, Horses, Zombie Pigman, Mooshrooms, Llamas, Donkeys or Mules.
- Spectral Dust from any Undead mob like Skeletons or Zombies.
Craft an Athame! Killing various mobs with this might make them drop some special loot! (See: next quest.)
Brew up some Fiery Unguent and automate it as best as you can!

Craft some Tallow!






















It's Swellow's pre-evolution... or is it?

betterquesting:10.name:8: It's like a sieve... but for liquids!
betterquesting:10.desc:8:
Make a Distillery! Make sure to place it near a Witches' Altar.

To automate this machine, you'll need to insert the ingredients from the top, Blaze Powder from the sides, and pull out the results from the bottom.

However, you might come across some difficulties:

- Items might end up in the wrong slots, for example 2 stacks of the same item get sent into the Distillery, instead of 2 stacks of unique ingredients.

- Some recipes take fewer than 6 inputs, and the 6th slot also gets filled up - stopping the crafting process.

- Some recipes take multiple stacks of the same item, and when they enter the machine, they don't spread out correctly.

But there is a fix for all of these!

Introducing (or more like revisiting a Chapter you've completed a long time ago): THE IMPULSE HOPPER! Simply setup a filter in the middle row, and the Impulse Hopper will only let a set of items through if all of the ones in the Filter have arrived.

This still poses an issue for crafts that take multiple of the same ingredients. The solution is rather simple though: Set the filters to be 64 of each item, and only let them through once multiple stack have arrived. They are surely going to go in the correct spot!

If you're still having trouble because your input slots are filling up, use an Integrated Dynamics Block Reader on the Distillery or a buffer chest that checks if the target block is empty, and if so, emits a redstone signal to the Impulse Hopper (in Redstone Mode: Active with signal) which will let some items through.

betterquesting:10.name:8: Oilin' up those Tiers and Tierin' up those Oils
betterquesting:10.desc:8: Craft some Heaven Extract and Otherworldly Tears. One tastes like mashed potatoes except instead of potatoes it's more like clouds, and the other one tastes like scorched Ender Dragon wings. None of them are my favorite though.

Woo, made this here with all the ice on in the booth,
All the gating in the pack can't stop me that's the truth,
Yeah, jump on into Bewitchment it's like I'm a sleuth,
This is way too big, when we end this give me the loot!
Throw some Splash Iceworld Potions on a field of Stone, Granite or Diorite to convert it to Perpetual Ice! The Potion has a large spread range, it even goes underground a bit.

It's time to perform your first Circle Rite.

Make some Tough Purified Paste! You'll need to Right Click the ingredients on the Golden Rune in the center, then Right Click with an empty hand. If your Circle layout is correct and you have sufficient Altar Power, you'll be able to perform it.
And here is the Golden Chalk I promised in the previous quest!

Brew up some of the nothingness, vacuum, manifestation of the realization of our mortal lives being insignificant in the wastness of the universe, the Brew of the Void!

...

Uuhhhh, ...nyeheheh, it's great to be a Witch...?

...
Brew up a Bottle of Blood from Adder's Forks or Tongues of the Dog! Nyeeehehehehehehehheeeee....!

* Doesn't actually give you Speed.
* Not for human consumption.
* Consult a doctor if you've accidentally inhaled or touched it... or worse.
Craft either a Silver or Iron Candelabra! Placing this on top of your Altar will boost its Altar Power.

Craft any 6 pieces of Witches' Altars! Place them in a 2x3 formation and place any piece of Carpet on top to form the multiblock.

This structure provides power for all your Bewitchment machines to function. Witches' Cauldrons, Distilleries, Spinning Wheels, Braziers and Circle Rites wouldn't function without sufficient Altar power in a 16 block radius.

To boost the power stored by your Altar, you need to spice up the immediate area with a bunch of wildlife! Trees, crops, growables, grass, flowers, fungi, anything you can think of. And variety helps! Two different types of crops will boost the power of your Altar more than two of the same type.

To boost the power further, you can also place any of the following items on of the top 6 slots (in increasing order of effectiveness):

- Cups: Flower Pot / Glass Bottle, Goblet, Flying Ointment, or Filled Goblet

- Vanilla Swords or Athame (with the Diamond Sword and the Athame being the best).

- Wands or lighting: Torch / Redstone Torch, Candles, Blaze Rod, Candelabra, End Rod, Leonard's Wand, Caduceus.

- Pentacles: Head / Skeleton Skull, Redstone / Nether Quartz / Lapis Lazuli / Opal, Wither Skeleton Skull, Amethyst / Diamond / Emerald / Garnet / Prismarine Shard, Grimoire Magia, Idols, Pentacle, Demon Heart, any Statue, Dragon Head.

More information on the Bewitchment Wiki:
https://bewitchment.fandom.com/wiki/Witches%27_Altar

Use the Rite shown in JEI to obtain a Villager Egg.

Summoning any Demon requires a sacrifice of a Player or a Villager, and this is the best way to have them 'ready'. Yikes!

betterquesting:10.name:8: Ouch! Hot hot hot hot hot!!!
betterquesting:10.desc:8:
Craft a Fiery Chalk!

Oven mitts recommended.

Read the Codex Infernalis / Higher Demons / Master Leonard section to summon the Lord, the Master, the One who's behind all of this.

Reluctantly, but challenge him to a fight. In order to progress, there is only one way that fight should end...

Craft a Stew of the Grotesque!

...Buuut I'd recommend NOT eating it.

You'll need it for the next quest in un-eaten form, and it might not be too beneficial for your health anyway.

Craft a Bewitchment Spinning Hwheel.

What did you say...?

Uhh, to craft a Bewitchment Spinning Hwheel?

Spinning Hwheel?

Spinning Hwheel, yeah.

You mean Spinning Wheel.

Yeah, Spinning Hwheel.

Spinning Wheel.

Spinning Hwheel.

Spinning Wheel.

Spinning Hwheel.

You're saying it weird, why are you putting so much emphasis on the 'H'?

What are you talking about, just saying it: 'Spinning Hwheel'. Craft a Spinning Hwheel. That's how you progress.

Say 'wheel'.

Wheel.

Now say 'Spinning Wheel'.

Spinning Hwheel.

Spinning Wheel.

Spinning Hwheel.

SPINNING WHEEL. D:<

Spinning Hwheel.

FINE. WHATEVER. YOU WIN. By the way, you need altar power for it... Now go.

Altar Wpower.
Distill some Stone Ichor!
Craft a Sigil of Purity. It burns like pure fire in your hands, reflecting your inner soul... I'm sure it's nothing to worry about!

betterquesting:10.name:8: It's not a table you preach from..
betterquesting:10.desc:8: Craft a Sigil Table! With this, you can (unsurprisingly) create ... Sigils! (Who would have thought.)

Perform the Spiritual Rift Rite at night! You can find it under the Circles Rites section of your Book of Shadows.

Sometimes (not always) Ghosts will end up spawning. Defeat them to obtain some Shards of the Grotesque!

Okay, this quest is tough.

I'll accept it.

But try to fully automate Poppets, and eventually Death Protection Poppets.

Good luck!
Distill some Demon Heart combined with some of your previous Oils, and add a pinch of Pride... for an interesting result.
Create the listed Essential Oils using your Witches' Oven! These ones aren't as frequently used as the ones in the "These are Essential!" quest, you only need to batch craft a few.

Craft a piece of Ritual Chalk!

You can draw Bewitchment Circles with this tool. All Circles have to have a Golden Rune drawn in the center.

There are 3 layers of Circles you can draw:

            ███████
         █                 █
      █      █████      █
   █      █             █      █
█      █      ███      █     ⠀█
█   █      █        █      █   █
█   █   █             █    █   █
█   █   █      §6█⠀§r    █    █   █
█   █   █             █    █   █
█   █      █        █      █   █
█      █      ███      █     ⠀█
   █      █             █      █
      █      █████      █
         █                 █
            ███████

The white squares represent White Chalk - but some Rites later will require Red or Purple Chalk to be used for one or more of the circles.

if you want to conserve Chalk, you can recolor your existing Circles with the Rite shown in your Book of Shadows / Rituals / Circle Drawing.
Weave up some woven, and wave when you're done.
Freeze some Thaumium for Cold Iron. Don't worry, Frostfire never goes out, and you can even pick it back up!

Craft a Death Protection Poppet. When bound to yourself with your own Taglock and held in your inventory or on a Poppet Shelf, it'll prevent a lethal blow by reincarnating you instantly using its own woven body.

If that's not witchy enough for you, then I don't know what is.

You may want to fully automate these... For your own well-being, and also... for what's to come.

Craft a Witches' Cauldron! Nyaaaahahahahahahahaaaaaa!

This machine functions very similarly to the Thaumcraft Crucible. You need to light a fire beneath it, fill it up with some Water, then throw in the required ingredients shown in JEI. However there are some key differences:

- You need Altar power for each recipe. A Cauldron more than 16 blocks away from an Altar won't function.

- You can't directly pipe Water into it. Instead, to automate it, you'll have to use a Mechanical User with a Water bucket inside. You can detect whether or not the Cauldron is empty with an Integrated Dynamics Block Reader, and have the Mechanical User in 'Redstone On' mode to fill the Cauldron exactly when it's empty.

- You can also brew Bewitchment Potions in the Witches' Cauldron. Simply start with a piece of Mandrake Root, add an additional ingredient (listed in JEI), and either Redstone or Glowstone, and optionally Gunpowder for the splash effect. Once done, Right Clicking with Empty Bottles will create the desired Potion.
Craft some Phasing Chalk, and hold it strongly, otherwise it may slip out and phase away into another reality.
Create the listed types of Essentia Oils with your Witches' Oven! All of these will be heavily used later, so make sure to constantly produce them!

Craft a Witches' Oven! Supply it with Empty Jars to get a chance to obtain the various Essential Oils from Bewitchment!


To automate the machine, insert Coal, Empty Jars and the required input ingredient from the top and the sides, and extract the results from the bottom.

Perform one of the most difficult Cauldron recipes to create some Dragon Resin. Fortunately you'll only need to do this once. Good luck!




















Is this how your get a Ground Dragon? Like, a Garchomp?! No. No it isn't. (That's it for the Pokemon references.)
If the input Spirit is strong, the output String will be strong too, they say...
It magically floats. Wingardium Leviosa or somethin'?

Find some Mysterious Leaking Souls in Mortum's Dungeons! You'll need 2 to complete this quest, but eventually you'll need 5 to delve deeper into Bewitchment!

Oh yeah... Welcome to Bewitchment, by the way.

Craft 4 Awakened Cores!


...Getting fancy here, are we?

Well hopefully the title doesn't match your current feelings - you're closer than ever to lategame!

Craft a Hellebore Seed and plant it to get more!

...is what you would say, if we were in 1.7.10! Buuuut, since then, Mandrakes have been cultivated and they no longer attack the player when harvested... Which is for the better.

Craft a Mandrake Seed and plant it to collect more!
Craft a Poppet! This definitely isn't a toy that wicked Witches abuse in any way... Nonononono... Of course not.

Open your Codex Infernalis and read the Higher Demons / Lord Baphomet section on how to summon this creature of nightmares, God of the Underworld.

Beat him.

A new book, containing more demonic knowledge is now available to you... the Codex Infernalis!

Lookup the Lesser Demons / Demon and Demones category on how to summon them. They'll require 3 entirely red circles and a sacrifice of a Player or a Villager.

Once summoned, fight them to obtain their Heart!

Craft a Pentacle.


... I don't like where this is going.

Craft some Diabolical Vein..

And realize, you've already gone down on a devilish path... But there is no more turning back...
Craft your first Dragon's Blood Sapling, then grow it to get more!

betterquesting:10.name:8: It's like taking a shower in heaven
betterquesting:10.desc:8: Ahh, so pure!
Craft a Flame Devourer Pendant. When the user's inflicted with the Hell Fire status effect, Right Clicking this item will yield a piece of Ignition.

Craft some Oil of Vitriol.

There is nothing more to say.





















...


















What?


















...















I said there is nothing more!

















...















There is definitely not a meme or a reference down here, stop looking!















...
















...

















FINE...


















Son: "Dad, why is my sister called 'Peace'?"
Dad: "Well, son, your mom thought there was not enough peace in the world...!"
Son: "Ah, that's interesting. Thanks, Dad!"
Dad: "No problem, Oil."










...












I told you not to look, it way bad anyway. :I
Even though Gypsum is missing from 1.12 Bewitchment, it makes a return in the form of a custom item! Hurray!

We rise

We rise
We fall

We rise

We rise
