WE RISE

SWIRL

(Swirl... of Depths.)

Craft some Ritualistic Salt!






















I heard sprinkling this on some undead on Thriller Bark will release their captured shadows... Or wait, that's not in this game...!
Wanna be fancy and drink from a Goblet? Now is your chance! Not only will your wine taste better, but it this will also give you an exquisite amount of Altar Power! Nice.

Use your Witches' Cauldron to create an Iceworld II Splash Potion. You'll need to throw in the following ingredients in order:

- Mandrake Root
- Ice OR Snow block
- Glowstone Dust
- Gunpowder

Then Right Click on the Cauldron three times with an Empty Bottle to get 3 of them!

betterquesting:10.name:8: There is only one way out...
betterquesting:10.desc:8:
All this dark magic has messed with your brain... The only way out... The only way to end this... Is to go away with it... Go into the hellish Underworld by sacrificing yourself to a Curse... The Curse of Conflagration will be perfect...

How? Well, it's quite simple actually:

Fill a Taglock with your own juices by Shift+Right Clicking on a Bed you've slept in. (Don't try to think about it more than that.)

Having this, inflict yourself with the Curse of Conflagration using your Brazier. The ingredients can be found in your Codex Infernalis, under Curses / Conflagration.

Once under the Hell Fire status effect, use your Flame Devourer Pendant to obtain some Ignition!

Craft a Brazier!

To use it, lookup the Curses section in your Codex Infernalis. Place it input items on top, and light it with a Flint and Steel. The Curse will be cast of the player whose Taglock you've used.
Create some Liquid Witchcraft and a Droplet of Wisdom! Mmmm... smells good! Smells a bit... witchy and knowledgy...
Craft a Boline and use it on the logs of a Dragonsblood Tree. It will eventually bleed Dragon's Blood Resin. Collect it using an Absorption Hopper!
Use more Mysterious Leaking Souls to craft Aconitum, Belladonna and Wormwood Seeds.

Fill it up! In what other way did you plan to drink from it, huh?

Besides the superb taste, it'll also serve you as the best "Cup" type item for Altar Power. Magnificent!

Craft a 16k ME Essentia Storage Component.

When upgraded to a Cell, it stores 128,000 units Essentia. Wow!

Honestly that's more than you'll ever need, buuuuut, you can't stop before the finish line, can you?

Craft a 4k ME Essentia Storage Component! Just like regular Storage Components, when upgraded to a Storage Cell, these are capable of storing Essentia (instead of items).

This one stores 32,000 units of Essentia (8 times the size of the Cell).

Use a FULLY CHARGED Impetus Conductor with an Impetus Crystal to craft Conducted Impetus. WARNING: Do NOT autocraft this. AE2 could eat up your inputs, if the given Impetus Conductor isn't fully charged*.

To charge your Impetus Conductor, insert it into your Void Recharge Pedestal. Make sure it has an incoming beam of Impetus.



-------------------------------

* This is because the charge value is (untraditionally) stored in the Forge Cap NBT of the item, not the regular NBT.
Craft a Void Recharge Pedestal and connect a beam of Impetus to it. This machine charges any items that accept Impetus, such as an Impetus Conductor.

Craft a 1k ME Essentia Storage Component. When upgraded to a Storage Cell, this is capable of storing 8000 units of Essentia. (8 times the size of the cell). That's 32 times the amount a single Jar can store, so these Components are VERY powerful.

Simply place it in regular Drives, and use Essentia Import and Export Buses to distribute the Essentia between the outside world and your system. Just like you would with items!
Upgrade a quarter stack of Void Stones to Eldritch Stones!

Craft an Arcane Charging Upgrade. Placing this in the slot on the right inside the Arcane Crafting Terminal's GUI will act as a Workbench Charger - the Terminal will be able to draw Vis from all 8 adjacent Chunks too!

Craft an Arcane Crafting Terminal! Attaching this to your ME Network will let you pull items from your system for Arcane Crafts.

Unfortunately we haven't been able to figure out a way to keep the 6 Vis Crystals refilled, so you'll still have to do that manually. Simply place them in the slots on the right.

Craft a Diffusion Core and a Coalescence Core to get into Thaumic Energistics!

To unlock the Thaumic Energistics tab in your Thaumonomicon, simply scan any Applied Energistics item or block.
Craft an Impetus Drainer! Placing this close to a Void Rift will start draining it. You can disable/enable this functionality with a Redstone signal.
Once you've defeated the Eldritch, break apart their tower, and loot the items listed on the right!
Craft an Impetus Jewel! This is the base crafting ingredient for all machines that interact with the energy gained from Void Rifts - also known as "Impetus".

Find an Eldritch Spire structure in the Emptiness and raid it!

You'll need to find 4 key pieces hidden throughout the dungeon and ascend the main tower to progress!

Defeat the final boss and gain access to the Eldritch Revelation!

Craft a 64k ME Essentia Storage Component!

When upgraded to a Cell, it can store 512,000 units of Essentia. (That's 2048 times the amount a single Jar can store. Wow!)
Craft some SPOOOOKY Lanterns!

Craft 12 Arcanium Bases. You can only craft this while standing inside a concentric square of biomes of this shape:


§5███████
█§c█████§5█
█§c█§a███§c§█§c█§5█
█§c█§a█§b█§a█§c█§5█
█§c█§a███§c█§5█
█§c█████§5█
███████§r

With

§5█§r = Mortum biome
§c█§r = Hell (Nether) biome
§a█§r = Magical Forest biome
§b█§r = Ocean biome


To set this up, you need to use an Arcane Terraformer on top of where the Ocean biome is, with the following steps:

1. Transform a Square area with Range = 4 into a Mortum biome.
2. Transform a Square area with Range = 3 into a Hell biome.
3. Transform a Square area with Range = 2 into a Magical Forest biome.
4. Transform a Square area with Range = 1 into an Ocean biome.

If you're unsure if you've transformed the area correctly, you can craft a Ritualistic Biome Checker. by standing in the middle and Right Clicking the item, it'll tell you how many blocks you have correctly transformed into the required biome.

YOU DON'T HAVE TO BE PERFECT THOUGH! There is some leeway. The recipe will still work if you only transformed:

- 22 of the 24 Mortum biome blocks,
- 15 of the 16 Hell biome blocks,
- 7 of the 8 Magical Forest biome blocks.

You can only do this MANUALLY, and only your Player needs to stand in the central Ocean biome block, the Crafting Table can be further away (as long as you can still reach it).

Note: There is sometimes a bug where the biome layout is entirely correct, and item can still be crafted, even though the crafting output is empty. Then you'll need to click the empty output slot to get the item. This is due to the recipe detecting Player location, not the Crafting Table's location.

Craft an Arcane Terraformer and 4 regular Biome Foci in an Arcane Workbench, them use each one in the 4 biomes listed the right: Ocean, Magical Forest, Hell (Nether) & Mortum.

WARNING: If you Shift+Right Click an Arcana Focus, it will get cleared and turn it back into a regular version.

The Arcane Terraformer can take any of these Foci and turn a circular or square area around it into the wanted biome.

For this, it'll require 3 key ingredients:
- Vis, drawn from the air.
- Essentia, drawn from the 5 input hatches located on the sides and on the bottom. These are specifically for Terra, Aer, Ignis, Aqua and Permuatatio, with Permutatio being drawn from the bottom. The rest should be routed into their respective colored input plug using Essentia Tubes or ME Essentia Export Buses.
- Impetus, drawn from an Impetus Relay, Impetus Matrix or Impetus Drainer - routed by an Impetus Resonator.

These materials will only be used while the machine is active. To activate it, select the desired area in the GUI, then Right Click it with your Gauntlet.

Using your Void Seeds and materials from Bewitchment, craft some Cold Void Seeds, Cold Void Metal Ingots, and finally, Void Metal Ingots.

What a process!

betterquesting:10.name:8: If you haven't messed up yet, now is the time!
betterquesting:10.desc:8:
Pump of a lot of Flux into a chunk! This can be best done by setting up a Crucible, filling it to the brim with items that have a high Essentia amount, then breaking or Shift+Right Clicking on the Cauldron.

WARNING: Do NOT to this inside your base. Nearby is fine - although you'll need to keep an eye on the Void Rift spawned this way, not to cause Taint to spawn.

Use a Causality Collapser on the Void Rift! This closes the Rift and drops a fair number of Void Seeds. You'll need a good amount of them, so repeat this process a couple of times.
Craft a couple Causality Collapsers! Depending on your luck, you may need more than the 5 needed to complete the quest.
Craft a Chaotic Energy Core!
Mine up a stack of the base Stone of the Emptiness: Void Stones!

Discover a tear in the fabric of spacetime, and activate it with your newly acquired Gauntlet that has an Impetus Conductor attached!

Then enter the Emptiness...
Sometimes you want to store the Essentia outside of your Storage Cells (for a subnet, for a simple setup that doesn't need as much Essentia, etc.), and these components can come useful.

Craft an ME Essentia Import Bus & Export Bus.

They can import / export Essentia from Jars into your Essentia storage system. They can also accept all types of Cards that regular Import and Export Buses can.

To filter them, use Phials of Essentia.

Loot or craft some Ancient Pedestals! Using Ancient Stones instead of Arcane Stones, and an Ancient Pedestals instead of Arcane Pedestals, you can upgrade your Infusion Altar.

This new Infusion Altar comes with decreased Essentia costs and increased stability.

Once it's formed, the center pedestal does not need to remain an Ancient Pedestal.

You can also place down Ancient Pedestals instead of Arcane Pedestals around the Infusion Altar, reducing Essentia Costs and increasing speed slightly at the cost of increased Instability. You do not need Ancient Pedestals for an Ancient Infusion Altar to function, any Pedestal will work.

Craft all the required items on the right for an Auto Infusion Matrix multiblock!

Check the figure in JEI and setup the machine. Make sure to place the Blueprint inside the Machine Controller.

WATCH OUT: You should set it up in a single chunk, and make sure it's more than 16 blocks away from any Thaumcraft Filling Essentia Transfusers you're not planning to use for this machine!

THE SETUP: There are 41 individual Essentia Input Hatches on the machine, since there are 41 types of Essentia. Each one should be whitelisted to only accept 1 unique type of Essentia. To do this, place a total of 41 Essentia Export Buses (or Storage Buses with a higher priority than your Drives) on each individual Essentia Input Hatch.

BE CAREFUL: Empty Essentia Input Hatches can steal Essentia from each other, so try to fill them up quicky. Breaking and replacing an Essentia Input Hatch will delete its contents and NOT create any Flux in the process - so feel free to do so. Other than that, these Input Hatches basically act like Jars, having a max capacity of 250 units of Essentia, and being able to accept from anything and output to anything that normal Jars can.

FIRSTLY: Of course, you'll need a sufficient supply of ALL 41 types of Essentia before you can use this machine effectively. Setup a large automation facility to convert basic materials into Essentia (like Stone into Terra, Redstone into Potentia, etc.).

BUT WHAT ABOUT THE FLUX? Spread out your facility over multiple chunks and use many Flux Condensers to get rid of the Flux. More optimally, let a Flux Rift build, and stabilize it using Stability Field Generators. These are rewarded, although you may need to craft more. Once the Rift is stabilized, you can generate as much Flux in the Chunk as you want, about 32,000 is the limit. Have at it!

BE AWARE, that if the Thaumonomicon requires you to craft something in the Infusion Altar, using this machine WON'T COUNT. So do all your crafts in the regular Infusion Altar first.

Note: This whole automation setup will take a while, so don't be discouraged by getting stuck on this quest for a couple days even.

Also Note: The Essentia Import Hatches don't get colored due to a bug with Modular Magic.

Craft an Essentia Infusion Provider!

Using your Thaumic Energistics system, you can provide Essentia for regular Infusions with this. No need for Jars anymore!

However, since "vanilla" Infusion itself cannot be fully automated (there is no way to activate it), I recommend using this in the Auto Infusion Matrix, a custom Modular Machinery Multiblock.

Craft the fastest Essentia Smeltery, the Void Metal Essentia Smeltery. This machine also has a much lower chance of producing Flux than the previous variants. Though you'll still need to use Flux Condensers if you fully want to get rid of it.
Craft an Advanced Alchemical Construct! This is purely a crafting ingredient for (you guessed it) advanced alchemy.

betterquesting:10.name:8: Power of the Void - Stuck together
betterquesting:10.desc:8: It's vibrating... what is it up to?

Using your Primordial Pearl and Void Metal craft some Impetus Crystals!

WARNING: Do NOT break the Primordial Pearl. Keep repairing it instead. If you accidentally do, you'll have to obtain another one, which could be quite painful.

Craft a Thaumium Caster's Gauntlet, and apply an Impetus Conductor to it by crafting.

WARNING: If you had previous Foci attached, remove them before crafting!

Craft a Fracture Locator!

Before you do the following, make sure you have a Gauntlet with an Impetus Conductor attached (the quest below this).

Oh you do? Well then, let me explain.

There are tears in spacetime, that are pretty difficult to notice without an external tool... And they seem to be more common in the Nether than any other place.

But this invention will let you locate them! It'll brighten up if you get close to and you FACE a tear.

Time to spin around in the Nether like it's breakdance!

While destroying Flux Rifts with your Causality Collapsers, you might come across a very rare item - the Primordial Pearl. It'll most likely be damaged the first time you obtain it, so it'll have a different name, likely "Primordial Mote" or "Primordial Nodule".

This item is used in a multitude of crafts, always only using 1 durability per craft.

In this pack however, you can also repair the Primordial Pearl with a Tool Poppet! Each Poppet will add back 1 durability point. This can ONLY be done manually, however, the Primordial Pearl isn't used in a lot of crafts.

Craft 8 Eldritch Pedestals! These are used for the Impetus Matrix multiblock, and they also give an even more increased Essentia cost reduction, and an even more increased stability when used for the regular Infusion Matrix multiblock.

You can also place down Eldritch Pedestals instead of Arcane Pedestals around the Infusion Altar, reducing Instability and increasing the speed, but slightly increasing Essentia costs. You do not need Eldritch Pedestals for an Eldritch Infusion Altar to function, any Pedestal will work. Take care not to leave an Eldritch Pedestal unbalanced, as it will massively increase Instability.

Craft an Impetus Resonator and a couple Impetus Relays!

The Resonator is capable of routing the Impetus you collect. Set the input by Shift+Right Clicking on a machine or node, and set the output by Right Clicking on another one.

Relays are 1-input 1-output connectors to transfer Impetus with.
Fully repair the Primordial Pearl with multiple Tool Poppets!
Craft an Elite Crafting Table (7x7)!

Craft 12 Arcana Portal Frames!

To set them up, stand in the middle of where the Portal will go, and rotate around, placing the Portal Frame blocks without moving. The shape is exactly the same as an End Portal, 5x5 without corners.

You'll know if you set it up the right way if the little circles on the side of each Portal Frame block point inside - or, if the portal activates and you end up in the Dungeon of Arcana. That's also a good indication.

Alright, enough with the Flux!

This is an automatable way of getting rid of the Flux you've accumulated in a Chunk. Craft the items shown on the right, and place the Flux Condenser Lattice on top of the Flux Condenser, feed it any kind of Essentia from the 4 sides, and pump out Vitium Essentia on the bottom.

If you can reliable store the output Vitium Essentia, then do so - otherwise pump it into a Void Jar. If the output Jar fills up, it'll STOP the Flux Condenser, and you'll be sad to see your machines destroyed by a Flux Rift in the same Chunk.

Setup the Impetus Matrix multiblock, requiring a Runic Matrix block and 2 Eldritch Pedestals placed on the top and the bottom; sprinkled with some Salis Mundus.

This multiblock structure is capable of storing Impetus. However to use it, you'll also need to insert at least 1 (but up to 8) Impetus Cells in the side of the bottom and top Eldritch Pedestals.

Similarly to the Infusion Matrix multiblock, this one also requires stabilization. The more Impetus stored inside, the less stable it will become - knocking down Impetus Cells and losing stored Impetus. However the range at which it detects stabilizer items is only 5 blocks (counted from the bottom Pedestal).

The methods a the same though - a variety of Candles, Skulls, or even better, a symmetrical layout of Stabilizers will do.

It takes a little while for the multiblock to detect the Stabilizers, but around 8 will likely be more than enough (of course, laid out in a symmetrical manner).

Craft an ME Essentia Terminal. Attaching this to your ME Network will let you see the amount of Essentia stored on it.

You can also use Phials to quickly fill or empty some Essentia directly through the Terminal.

You've been able to automate almost everything in Thaumcraft... but there is one more missing piece.

Vis!

With this block however, you can slowly regenerate Vis in a Chunk. And they stack! In the lategame, you can place down hundreds of these in the chunk(s) you're doing Thaumcraft in to regenerate all the Vis very quickly!

Craft some Mortum Blocks!

But hold on... the recipe only gives 3 now... What will THIS be useful for?
Upgrade your current Lightning Cell to the Advanced version, capable of storing a lot more LE!

betterquesting:10.name:8: So this is what I needed Demon Hearts for...!
betterquesting:10.desc:8:
Defeat or Powered Spawn some Demon Soliders, found naturally spawning in the Nether.

And now that you have a sufficient source of Demon Hearts, infuse some Demonstones as well!

You're stronger now.

Much stronger.

It's time.

Travel to 2 coordinates to the end that are both a multiple of 10,000 to find the island of the Chaos Guardian.

Make sure to bring additional charge for your armor.

Defeat the Dragon.

Dig down in the center and collect its Chaos Shards.

Quickly fly away, before the island goes boom. (The explosion even kills in Creative mode.)

Good luck!










Hooooo jyaaah...!! Sunshu-- uh, o ah yaa-aah!
Eh-eh oh eh o e AH! Eh-eh ooooo-ooooj!
Hooooo jyaaah...!! Sunshu-- uh, o ah yaa-aah!
Eh-eh oh eh o e AH! YEWS! OH MY GOD!

Collect some Underworld Lanterns, Corrupt Stone and Undersand from the Underworld.

DO YOU UNDERSAND NOW?!
Craft a Skyfather Ingot in your Lightning Infusion Table!

Craft a Lightning Energy Cell! This device is capable of storing LE (Lightning Energy), and automatically powering any LE consuming machine placed next to it.

To charge it with LE, place some kind of a Terminal on top, and swing your Golden Club to summon Lightning! Later you'll be able to automatically gain Lightning Energy too, but for now, this is the only method.

Craft an Iron Air Terminal and keep upgrading it until you reach the Copper version!

Placing any of these on top of a Lightning Energy Cell and then summoning Lightning on top will fill the Cell with a bit of LE (Lightning Energy). The amount of LE per Lightning is determined by the type of the Air Terminal.

Craft a Lightning Infusion Table!

This machine requires LE (Lightning Energy) to function. See the nearby quests on how to generate LE.

You will no longer need to create Electricium in-world, you can use this machine from now on.

To automate this machine, you need to insert the central item from the top, the outer items from the side, and pull out the result from the bottom.

Make sure not to fill up all the outer slots if a recipe requires fewer than 4 of them. The best option is to use an Impulse Hopper set to only extract items when it receives a Redstone Pulse, and set a Timer behind it.

Each recipe in the Lightning Infusion Table takes exactly 30 seconds to craft. Later you can upgrade the machine so each recipe will take exactly 15 seconds. Though even with a 30 (or later 15) second clock it sometimes clogs up (depending on server TPS), so I recommend setting your Timer to around 30.25 - 30.5 seconds to begin with.
Make a Crafting Table and use it to create a Moonlight Furnace. It works functionally the same as a regular Furnace. Use it smelt your Ores you create with Dream Stone and Dream Dirt!
Craft a Wooden Pickaxe and collect some Dream Stones! These work exactly like Cobblestone, with the exception of being able to use it and Dream Dirt to magically conjure up some Ores...!
Alloy up some Invar in your Smeltery!

Make some Seared Bricks and setup a basic Smeltery! You can obtain Lava from Fire Crystals, and you can create some useful alloys to make powerful tools and weapon!

Make sure to create a powerful Cleaver or Longsword and some kind of ranged weapon!
Craft some Lightning Furnaces. This is a machine that takes LE Power to smelt items, but you'll mostly need it for the Lightning Crusher recipe.
Setup a small base (I recommend simply digging into a wall), and craft all Tinkers' Tables listed to the right. Create some Tools that are better than the Vanilla ones!
Use Dream Dirt, Dream Stone and Water to obtain Sand, Gravel and Clay!

Once you've collected 8 pieces of Firelights, you can obtain 2 Water Buckets to make an infinite Water source.

Using this, make Mushrooms and Mushroom Stew for food!

betterquesting:10.name:8: Light the Fire, spill the Water!
betterquesting:10.desc:8: Find some Firelights randomly scattered across Vethea! It's most common on the top layer, but before having access to good equipment, stay on the bottom layer and look for brown structures that may include this block!

Use Dream Stone and Dream Dirt in the Crafting Table to obtain all of the Ores listed to the right.

Some additional ones are also available if you want to make tools, weapons or anything else out of them. Lookup the usage of Dream Dirt or Dream Stone, and scroll to the end to see their recipes!

These are: Lapis, Realmite, Arlemite, Rupee, Quartz and Salt Ores.
Craft a Redstone Flux Power Tap. You need that sweet-sweet power, man!

Craft some Reactor Casings to get into Extreme Reactors! This mod works exactly like the 1.7.10 Big Reactors mod. However since it's only available so late into the game, Reactors generate WAY more power this time!

How much power? 500 times the default.


Yeah.

By the way, if you're new to Extreme Reactors (of Big Reactors), make sure to read the guide book rewarded for this quest! It contains information on how to construct, activate and use these reactors.

Oh, and by the way, they can't blow up. It's not a possibility that's coded in. Hurray!

Craft 27 Coke Bricks and Blast Bricks! Also craft an Engineer's Hammer and use it to form the multiblocks!

Similarly to how you did it before, create Coal Coke and create Steel!

Advance to the topmost layer of Vethea and find a rare structure: an Arena made of Luna Bricks. Collect a couple of the Bricks and head out!





By the way, this Arena would host the final boss of Vethea, but it's so ridiculously overtuned, that I can't wholeheartedly require you to fight it... It's Lady Luna and she has 4000 hearts of health and can two-shot you with acid on the ground, not to mention you can only damage her with either melee, ranged or arcanic weapons, depending on her current form which she changes about every 10-15 seconds.

I'm not even gonna tell you how to summon her, but if you're really up for a challenge (and I mean REALLY up for one), then lookup 'Lady Luna' on the DivineRPG Wiki.
Upgrade your LE Transmitters and Receivers to Tier 2 for more efficient wireless transmission!

Craft a Tier 1 LE Transmitter and LE Receiver! Place the Transmitter next to the Lightning Energy Cell where you're generating LE, and place the Receiver next to a Lightning Infusion Table to provide it with LE!

To connect them up craft a Tx/Rx tag, Shift+Right Click the Transmitter and Right Click the Receiver. To use the Tx/Rx tag again, simply craft it into a fresh one in the Crafting Table.

Unfortunately due to the nature of Lightning Energy, it cannot be transmitted through mundane cables, so the only option is to send it wirelessly!

Find a Restroom where Datticon hides! Collect some of her Furnaces. These will be used later on...

Remember where Datticon's room is, you'll need to trade with her soon.

This modpack's been sponsored by Raid: Arcane Legends! Simply load into the Dungeon of Arcana using the link in the description, defeat mobs, trade with NPCs and collect various powerful materials! You can choose to be a melee fighter or a ranged archer! No microtransactions*

The rewarded Levers are used to open doors with incredible loot behind!! (Or, just Raw Arcanium...)















* I swear**
















** Okay, fine, there are microtransactions, you got me...

betterquesting:10.name:8: Crushin' it as much as you can
betterquesting:10.desc:8:
Craft a Lightning Crusher! This machine uses LE to run, so place it next to a Lightning Cell or an LE Receiver.

To automate this, insert items from the sides or the top, and extract items from the bottom.
Craft an Underworld Charge to charge up the Underworld with...

Find a large brown structure on the top layer of Vethea. Get through a small parkour puzzle and loot some Heliosis Lumps from Chests at the end! Use them to craft an Ender Chest!

You can also create dyes to color your Ender Chest. Lookup the usage of DivineRPG Acid to see how they're made. Of course, Lapis is also available. To secure the Ender Chest, use a piece of Diamond on its handle. Of course, this means you also need an Ender Chest with a piece of Diamond attached on the other side.

Send back 4 Souls Vials to the Overworld that contain different types of mobs from each layer so you can Powered Spawn them for their Pearls.



WARNING: Do NOT attempt to spawn Heliosis. It will crash your game (or server) and corrupt the world. Yikes! You do NOT need any loot from it.

Combine Dirty Pearls, Acid an Emerald to conjure an Ender Pearl.

Then upgrade it into an Eye of the Nightmare using some Blaze Powder, a slice of Glistering Melon and some Shiny Pearls!
Energize some Osmium and craft a Mekanism Steel Casing!

Biodiesel!

That's what they make.

For some reason...

Find a room with some Parasecta or Dramix Altars inside the Dungeon of Arcana! Place your Wizards Book on one of them to spawn Parasecta / Dramix!

Defeat it an collect your loot, the Dungeon Tokens!
Find Lord Vatticus inside his special room (the small Library) in the Dungeon of Arcana. Exchange some Arcanium with him for a Wizards Book!

Locate a tree of some Logs nearby and dig a tunnel towards it, collecting some Dream Dirt in the meantime.

But WATCH OUT: there is NO BEDROCK LAYER at Y=0, so always watch your height level when mining below ground! Don't fall out of the world!

Craft some Thunderstones!

(You can get Scorned Bricks from Compressed Netherrack and Compressed Obsidian.)

betterquesting:10.name:8: It's farther down than the Nether
betterquesting:10.desc:8:
Build up a vertical Portal of a 2x2 inside (or 4x4 outside) shape out of Demonstone and light it with your Underworld Charge. (You do not need to have corner blocks.)

Then enter the Underworld!

If you haven't done so yet, it's time to fully automate the summoning and killing of regular Bewitchment Demons!

In order to do this, you'll need to use a Mechanical User to provide all the items one by one to the central Golden Glyph. Make sure to have a two Impulse Hoppers with a long timer attached to send exactly 1 of each required item.

You'll need two Impulse Hoppers, since one just barely doesn't have enough slots. But setting them to Redstone Mode: Active with Signal, and having a sufficiently long Timer and short pulse generator at the end will still allow you to send the exact items you need.

The Mechanical User will also automatically activate the Ritual after placing all the ingredients, if you have it set to constantly Right Click the central Glyph.

Villager spawn Eggs need to be automated as well in the same way.

The sacrificial Villager needs to be placed in so that it doesn't get placed into a wall and immediately suffocate.

You'll also need a Mechanical User with a sword or a Mob Crusher / Mob Masher to sacrifice the Villager and kill the Demon once it gets summoned.

YOU'LL NEED TO CLEAR SOME BLOCKS! The Demon won't be able to summon if you build a tube of solid blocks right above the Ritual Circle. Don't place anything on the bottommost layer, and build the layers above it entirely out of Glass or other non-solid blocks.

Finally, pickup the dropped items with a Vacuum Chest or Absorption Hopper (including the Athame which gets returned to you).
Upgrade your Electricium Air Terminal into a Skyfather variant!
Craft an Electricium Air Terminal for even more efficiency!
Craft a Lightning Upgrade! Applying a single one of these to a Lightning Infuser will speed it up by a factor of 2, making it so every recipe takes 15 seconds instead of 30.
Upgrade your LE Transmitter and Receivers to Tier 3, the final tier!
Craft some Mystical Iron Ingots to finish up the LightningCraft progression!

Wow, a lot of mobs inside! And it's very dark indeed.

Your first goal should be to survive: Dig yourself a small tunnel right below ground, but WATCH OUT: there is NO BEDROCK LAYER at Y=0, so always watch your height level when mining below ground! Don't fall out of the world!

Your tunnel should lead to nearby trees. There are 3 types of them in Vethea: Firewood, Hyrewood and Mintwood. Find any of them and get some Logs. They don't drop any Saplings though, so you should be conservative.

Once you collected some, make a Wooden Pickaxe Head.

Return home and craft a Nightmare Bed!

Make a completely dark area (you can use Dark Ineffable Glass to keep the area dark while still being able to walk into it), and place the Bed inside. (Make sure to have at least a 2x2 area beside your Bed to spawn into when coming back.)

Sleeping in it will send you to Vethea, the Nightmare! Obviously, since it's a dream, you can't bring any of your items with you, and you can't bring any items out...

Or can you?

With your technology, it might be possible. Make sure you have an Ender Chest outside of the Nightmare to send items to, then you'll only need to build an Ender Chest inside... How hard could it be...?

Then, with the Ender Chest, you can send items back and forth! The most important items to send back are the various Pearls you can find my defeating mobs, and to make the Pearl farming easier, also send back Soul Vials with the mobs inside - to Powered Spawn them.

Vethea has 4 layers, with different types of mobs spawning on each layer. To advance to the next layer, simply dig up! These mobs drop all the Pearls listed to the right, and the Acid Hag (spawning on the bottom two layers) drops Acid. Collect it all!

Note: You probably want to prepare before heading up to the top layers, as mobs are increasingly more difficult. I would suggest creating a network of tunnels to travel between. Use ladders to your advantage!

Once you have access to Soul Vials (which you pretty much should, if you've completed this quest), also grab a mob from each layer to transfer back into the Overworld!

Use Sand, Lava and Polished Pearls to create Soul Sand!

Use Soul Sand, Glass and any kind of Pearls to make a Soul Vial! Collect 4 types of mobs (1 from each layer) to later Powered Spawn them in your base for their loot!
Find some Fire Crystals! There should be plenty in Vethea. You can use these to conjure Lava! Useful for powering a Tinkers' Construct Smeltery.
Use a Lava Bucket and Clean Pearls to make some Blaze Rods!
Find some Dream Melons inside Chests in small Crypts on the bottom layer of Vethea, then craft it into vanilla Melon slices and Glistering Melon slices!

Return from Vethea using the Portal located right where you spawned in.

Using a Dungeon Token, some Ignition (from the end of Bewitchment), an Impetus Crystal, Lightning Grenade (gathered from an Environmental Accumulator) and Clean Pearls you've just obtained: craft some Lightning Charges! This will open LightningCraft for you!

betterquesting:10.name:8: I like my Arcanium well done
betterquesting:10.desc:8:
Find an Arcanium Extractor inside the Dungeon. It can spawn in multiple different types of rooms.

Use Raw Arcanium in the top slot and Collectors in the bottom slot to create Arcanium!

Throw a piece of Diamond, Gold Ingot and Iron Ingot on the ground in the same spot, and (while highlighting a block) strike them with Lightning to transform them into a piece of Electricium Ingot!

Rinse and repeat 3 more times to complete the quest.

Find Datticon inside the Dungeon of Arcana and buy 3 Accelerons from her!

These will be used to accelerate your dreams and send you flying into the nightmare of Vethea...
Craft a Mystic Ingot! This is the highest tier LightningCraft material.

betterquesting:10.name:8: If Thaumic Tinkerer won't add this...
betterquesting:10.desc:8:
...Then LightningCraft will!

Craft some Ichor by striking Lightning on Demon Blood, a Skyfather Ingot, and an Emerald.

You longer need to use your Club (you can if you want to), instead use the Lightning strikes generated by your Electrostatic Generators!
Use the Lightning Crusher to get Guard's Bone Meal, any Crusher to get Electricium Dust and the Underpowder you've gained from Powered Spawning Undercreeprs to craft some Empowered Underpowder!
Open Dungeon Doors with Levers (or any other type of Redstone) and collect Raw Arcacium behind using a Shovel.
Defeat mobs inside the Dungeon to collect Collectors and become a Collector collector.
Construct your Reactor and use it to produce Cyanite Ingots!

Craft one (or two) Access Ports for Yellorium input and Cyanite output. You can change it between Inlet and Outlet mode and insert Yellorium into one using an Export Bus, Item Conduit, etc., and extract Cyanite from the other one using an Import Bus, Item Conduit, etc.
Craft a Reactor Controller! This is where you can start and stop the reactor, and check how much RF it's producing.
Craft some Fuel Rods and Control Rods to cap them off!

Use your Cyanite Ingots and some Mystical Iron to craft a Blutonium Ingot and unlock Astral Sorcery!






















Yo, listen up here's a story
About a little ingot
That lives in a blue world
And all day and all night
And everything it sees is just blue
Like itself inside and outside
Blue its house
With a blue little window
And a blue corvette
And everything is blue for it
And itself and everybody around
Cause it ain't got nobody to listen to

I'm blue
