Da ba dee da ba di
Da ba dee da ba di
Da ba dee da ba di
Da ba dee da ba di
Da ba dee da ba di
Da ba dee da ba di
Da ba dee da ba di

Craft an Enchantment Reallocator! This machine uses LE to transfer all Enchantments from the item placed into the top slot to the item placed into the bottom slot. There is no excuse for Protection III anymore!
Find a special Library Room inside the Dungeon and use a Silk Touch tool to collect some Bookshelves! These will be used later on...

Craft a Golden Club! You will need more than one, although likely not that many. If used optimally, you won't need more than 2.

By swinging this in the air it uses up 1 durability to summon Lightning! If you want to use it for anything useful (other than looks), then make sure to use it WHILE HOVERING OVER a block. This is required for both Lightning transformations and LE (Lightning Energy) generation.
Use your Blast Furnace to create some Steel!
Find some Undercreeps and defeat them to collect their Underpowder! You probably want to Powered Spawn these fellahs as well.

Craft a Dislocator Receptacle and a couple pieces of Draconium Infused Obsidian!

These can all be arranged into a shape of a portal (either standing like a Nether Portal, or lying down like an End Portal). Make sure not the have the Dislocator Receptable on a corner.

To link up 2 of such Portals, use 2 Dislocators. Shift+Right Click on one of them with one Dislocator, then Right Click on the other one to place it inside. Do the same with the other Dislocator on the other Portal if you'd like to travel both ways.

These portals can not only transfer you, the player, they also work on any entity - perfect to transport the Wither from a spawning place into a killing chamber, since the Wither floats down.

That still isn't all! They can also transmit RF power through Draconic Evolution Energy Crystals.

Wireless power, teleportation and entity moving all in one multiblock. Amazing!
Find a Skeleton Guard Tower spawning rarely in the Underworld. Capture a Skeleton Guard and Powered Spawn it for its Bones!

Make an Electrostatic Generator!

This is a powerful machine that can summon Lightning using two materials:

- some LE Energy,
- any kind of block (Cobblestone is probably the easiest).

To kickstart the process, place this next to a Lightning Cell, place a higher tier Air Terminal on top of the Cell, provide a constant stream of blocks to the Electrostatic Generator, and wait until Lightning strikes!

The Lightning will generate more LE than the Electrostatic Generator used, effectively creating free LE from just Cobblestone.

You can also place multiple Electrostatic Generators next to a single Lightning Cell to charge it even faster!

What's darker than Steel?

...

A lot of things, actually. Like, I don't know, a spruce tree log, a lump of coal, a black hole, or my wintercoat.

Buuut this as well.
Upgrade your Skyfather Air Terminal into a Mystic variant! This is the highest tier of Air Terminal.

The Woodland Mansion Locator Token will find you the nearest Woodland Mansion!
You will need to kill the Evokers inside to get their Totems of Undying.
Craft 10 Orange Heart Canisters. Drop these into your Heart Amulet and gain another 20 max HP!

Craft a Network Visualization Tool! You'll need an activated Ender Core (Enhanced), for which you'll need to Right Click an End Crystal in the End.

This Tool allows you to visualize your AE2 Network channels and connections by simply Right Clicking with it anywhere on your Network. It's especially helpful for visualizing where each P2P tunnel leads. For a pack that requires heavy automation through AE2, it's a very-very handy tool.

The Spectral Relay can be placed down to activate specific structures, and as a crafting ingredient.

A common use is to collect Starlight for your Starlight Altars. For this you'll need to build a small structure: A 3x3 area with the corners being Chiseled Marble, the sides being Marble Arches, and the center being Sooty Marble. Place the Spectral Relay on top, and put a Glass Lens inside. The Crafting Altar closest to this structure (that isn't blocked by a wall) will receive significantly more Starlight.
The Glass Lens is a crafting material and can be placed in specific blocks, such as a Relay, to cause special effects.
Toss some Wood into Liquid Starlight to get Infused Wood, a crafting material.

Craft the Startlight Crafting Table!

This would normally require the light of a Collector Crystal, but not in this pack! You can just craft it in any Crafting Table.

Craft a Dislocator! Shift+Right click to bind to a place. Right Click to teleport to that base. Has twenty (20) uses.
When placed on a Dislocator Pedestal, has infinite uses.

And, if you have a moment to spare, consider how horrifying teleportation would be.
Nocturnal Powder will cause the block it is placed on to be covered by a dark cloud for a few seconds and spawn multiple mobs. Same as Illumination Powder, you can throw it.

Illumination Powder is primarily a crafting material, but also works as a light source when placed down. As it isn't a block, the only way to remove it is to smother it by covering it with a solid block.

Also you can throw it, it's very fun.

Just like the Lens, the PrismLens will redirect Starlight directed into it by a Linking Tool towards another location determined by the Linking Tool. Unlike the Lens, it can split Starlight among multiple points.

Toss some Sparkling Aquamarine into the Starlight Infuser and right click it with a Resonating Wand to craft Resonating Gems. Make sure that your Liquid Starlight isnt flowing.

It's only Resonating Gem if it's from the Resonating region in France. Otherwise it's just Sparkling Aquamarine.

Craft a Containment Chalice! On the surface, this is a tank that can hold up to 24 Buckets of fluid. But it can do sooo much more!

1. You can simply pump Liquids in and out from the bottom with any kind of Liquid Pipe.

2. When you place two of these Chalices close to each other, the Liquids inside start interacting with each other: Water + Lava will create Cobblestone, Stone, and sometimes Obsidian, Water and Starlight will create Ice, Lava and Starlight will create Sand and sometimes even Aquamarine Ore! You can collect these with an Absorption Hopper.

3. Placing a Chalice next to a Lightwell will drain the Lightwell automatically. Perfect for automation!

4. Placing a Chalice in the Starlight Infuser structure will allow you to directly pump Starlight into the Chalices for the ritual, without having to replace the small Starlight puddles. The Infuser will draw Starlight from nearby Chalices first, before it drains it from the pools.

Using your Enchanter's PhD, craft the Iridescent Altar. Just like its prior Starlight Altars, it gains more max Starlight, generates more natively, and gains more slots to craft with.
In addition to that, it also unlocks the ability to place an attuned crystal to specify a Constellation, which is required for many items.
It also unlocks the ability for crafts to require items placed on Spectral Relays after the craft is initialized. These are indicated by spectral versions of themselves displaying above the specific Spectral Relays.

The Starlight Crafting Altar is the next tier of Starlight Altar. It can craft all the items that the Luminous Crafting Table can, but requires a multiblock structure to function. You can use a Sextant on it to see what a spectral preview of the multiblock.
It has a higher amount of maximum Starlight, and gets more Starlight, meaning prior tier recipes will become easier to accomplish.

The Starlight Crafting Altar will replace your Luminous Crafting Table, so make sure everything you need to complete the upgrade is made.

To finish the quest, pickup the Altar so the quest book detects it.

The Celestial Gateway is a multiblock structure that allows easy cross-dimensional teleportation! Simply place down, assemble the structure (remember the Sextant shows a preview), do that in another place, and then look in the direction of the desired place. A star will appear, and by holding shift you can teleport over to the desired location. Once you have teleported once, a preview of the landscape on the other side will be displayed. Celestial Gateways can be renamed to further help navigation.

Also, 2 of them will be used for the final item in this Chapter.
Process some Starmetal Ore and get both Stardust and Starmetal Ingots.

The final tier of Astral observation, the Observatory allows you to finally view Faint Constellations. Similar to the Looking Glass from long ago, to draw Constellations you must hold Shift to connect the stars.

The Celestial Altar is the next tier of Starlight Altar. It can craft all the items that the Starlight Crafting Altar and Luminous Crafting Table could, but requires a larger multiblock structure to function. You can use a Sextant on it to see what a spectral preview of the multiblock. The listed items only include additional materials you need to get to upgrade your previous Altar.
It has a higher amount of maximum starlight, and gets more starlight, meaning prior tier recipes will become easier to accomplish.
The Celestial Altar will replace your Starlight Crafting Altar, so make sure everything you need to complete the upgrade is made.

To finish this quest, pickup the central Altar so the quest book can detect it.

First, craft a Ludicrite Block. Then, break it up into ingots and alloy it into Ludicrous Ore. Finally, using your Linking Tool, link a Starlight orgin to a placed down Ludicrous Ore. This will eventually turn into Starmetal Ore.

To automate this, you simply need some Block Placers and Block Breakers on a timer. Since you'll use a lot of Starmetal, I recommend automating this immediately!

The Attunement Altar is a multiblock structure that will allow you to attune a large variety of things.
To specify what to attune to, place down Spectral Relays in the locations needed to form a Constellation. This is indicated by blue sparks when holding a Constellation Paper.
Then, wait for that Constellation to be in the sky at night.
The nodes around the central Altar with lift up with the pure, channeled force of the Starlight.
Now, toss an item that can be attuned, such as Rock Crystals or Celestial Crystals, onto the Altar.
Or Attune yourself and unlock the powerful world of Perks!

The Looking Glass requires a clear view of the sky, but will allow you to spot the Bright Constellations you've been gathering. These are indicated by a grouping of large and distinctive stars. Hold shift to freeze the Looking Glass in place, and connect the stars in the manner shown on the Constellation Papers. The stars that are relevant to a Constellation are visibly larger than irrelevant ones.

The Stellar Refraction Table can give you Enchanted Books over the maximum vanilla level. Using Mending III, gained from Aevitas, Sharpness VII, gained from Discidia, Power VII, gained from Discidia, and Feather Falling, gained from Vicio, craft the Enchanter's PhD.

You've earned it.

(These can be placed anywhere in the Crafting window, and the Books may have other enchantments on them.)

The Stellar Refraction Table will allow Constellations in the sky to empower what's on the board, using an Infused Glass. It does its magic on Potions and Enchantments, and it does its job extremely well. Its effect increases based on the number of overlapping stars on the Constellations placed down on the paper inside.

First, you need it to be night.
Then, Right Click Parchment and Infused Glass onto it.
Next, move up to 3 Constellations onto the table. The Constellation matters for what effect it gives, which can be found in the Constellation tab of the Astral Tome.
This may fail, burning away the Parchment used, but if it succeeds you have gained an Engraved Glass.

Now, Shift+Right click to take the Engraved Glass out to inspect it - does it have the right effects?
If it does, put it back in, and Right Click a Potion, Book, Tool, Armor, or other enchantable items.
It will add the effects on the Engraved Glass onto the item at the cost of durability.

Happy Infusing.
Happy Engraving.
Happy Enchanting.
Happy Ending.

The Conversion Wand is a unique builders wand. Shift+Right clicking on a block will add it to a list displayed in the top left. When used on a block it will replace an area of the target block with a random mix of blocks from the list! Left Click mid-air to clear the list.
Like many Astral tools, holding it will display a blue shimmering bar overlaid ontop of your experience bar. This indicates the tool's ability to work, and slowly recharges.

After exploding some Mystical Iron Ingots into Shattered Mystical Iron Crystals, alloy it into Stone to create Rock Crystal Ore. This will give Rock Crystals when broken by a player.

Rock Crystals have a random Size, Cutting, and Purity when obtained. Its not going to be relevant until later, but higher stats are always better.

(PS. Rock Crystal Ore does NOT generate normally, this is the only way to obtain it.)

The Lightwell produces various fluid outputs when an item has been placed in it. It must have access to the sky, and works faster at night. Fluids are produced at different amounts based on the item. They also have a shatter percentage, which is their chance to break.

The main function is to gather Liquid Starlight. In order of least Liquid Starlight to most Liquid Starlight per cycle: Sparkling Aquamarine (your only option right now), Resonating Gem, Rock Crystal, Attuned Rock Crystal, Celestial Crystal, and Attuned Celestial Crystal.

In order of highest break chance to lowest break chance: Sparkling Aquamarine, Resonating Gem, Rock Crystal, Celestial Crystal, Attuned Rock Crystal, and Attuned Celestial Crystal.

betterquesting:10.name:8: The Divining Rod That Works TM
betterquesting:10.desc:8:
The Fosic Resonator is the first of a multi-tier item that allows you to detect important information. For the first tier, it only allows you to see Starlight Fields at night, indicated by glowing blue layer on the ground when held. Starlight Fields increase the amount of Starlight in a Crafting Altar, so if you're struggling getting enough Starlight at night, make sure to build your Crafting Altar at a high Starlight-concentration area.

Also, building your setup higher in elevation will also grant more Starlight.

Snag a bucket of Liquid Starlight. A Lightwell holds a maximum of two buckets.
Will give you Night Vision if you stand in it.

Finally you have access to an easier way of crafting potentially even better Collector Crystals!

When placed down, it will gather Starlight in an area around it. It can then be redirected using a Linking Tool towards something using it, such as a a Lens or a Starlight Altar.

The Shifting Star will completely reset your Perks - both their allocation, and all experience gained.
Later, you can upgrade your Shifting Star to an Irradiant Star, which only resets their allocation, and keeps all experience and progress gained. Additionally, they reattune you to the specified Bright Constellation.
To use, simply hold Right Click for a few seconds as an animation plays.

Infuse Magical Leather for the epic and long anticipated next tier of extravagant Leather, which will dazzle your eyes and nourish your very soul.
meh

The Starlight Infuser is a multiblock structure. The item to infuse is placed in the center, and then right clicked by a Resonating Wand. When the infusion is completed, there is a chance that a Liquid Starlight bucket has been consumed, and must be replaced to continue using the Starlight Infuser.

To automate this, use a Mechanical User for the input/output Right Clicks on a timer, and use an ME Fluid Formation Plane or an Integrated Tunnels World Fluid Exporter. Howover, later you'll be able to automate it in a much simpler way: Once you have access to a Containment Chalice, the Starlight Infuser can directly pull Starlight from it. Then you'll only need a Fluid Pipe of some sort to provide Starlight for this machine.

The Telescope requires a clear view of the sky, and is placed down. You can rotate through 8 different views, some of which may have Constellations on them, depending on what Constellations you know from the Constellation Papers you have gathered, and depending on the current moonphase. If you can't find any more Constellations, you might need to wait for the following night!

The Telescope can see both Bright and Dim Constellations, so 7 more than the simple Looking Glass.

Just like the Looking Glass, you will need to connect the stars in the manner shown on the Constellation Papers to learn more about them.
The Lens will redirect all Starlight directed into it by a Linking Tool towards another location determined by the Linking Tool.

The Linking Tool will allow you to link Starlight producers, trasmitters, and collectors together. To link, Right Click on the orgin, then Right Click on the target. To unlink, Shift+Right Click on the orgin. To stop selecting the orgin, switch it out of your hand. An origin targeting multiple locations will evenly split across all of them, if possible.

The Formation Wand is a unique builders wand. Shift+Right Clicking on a block will add it to a list displayed in the top left. When used on a distant block, it will build towards you, placing them in a random mix of blocks from the list! Left Click mid-air to clear the list.
Like many Astral tools, holding it will display a blue shimmering bar overlaid ontop of your experience bar. This indicates the tool's ability to work, and slowly recharges.

Craft a Resonating Wand! This Wand is used to finish all Astral Sorcery crafts. Once you have the required items laid out in a Luminous Crafting Table or Altar, Right Click with the Wand to activate the craft.

Toss a Stardust and a Rock Crystal into a pool of Liquid Starlight. After a few seconds, they will be consumed and replaced by a Celestial Crystal Cluster. This will slowly grow, until eventually it will emit white glimmering particles. When broken in this state, it will drop a Celestial Crystal of random stats and 2 Stardust.
Celestial Crystals have the same 3 stats as Rock Crystals, but instead of going up to Size 400, they go all the way up to size 900!

A reusable source of placing Illumination Powder! It can be colored by placing it with a dye in the crafting grid. Using a colored Illumination Wand on a Cave Illuminator will cause all lights that will be placed by the Cave Illuminator to be the same color as the Illumination Wand's.

Use your Astral Core to craft a Star of Revelation! This Star reveals the truth about the universe for you... Is there something outside? All this time you've been looking up at the night sky, finding Constallations, using the power of Moonlight, and being truly mesmerized... Is it a place you could some day reach?

...

You ponder.

Maybe we can visit it....

...Personally.

Using your recently identified Faint Constellations, Attune 4 Celestial Crystals, one to each of the 4 Faint Constellations, and craft them with a Resplendent Prism.
To Attune Faint Constellations to Celestial Crystals, they need to already be attuned to a Bright or Dim Constellation.

betterquesting:10.name:8: Sunlight, Sunbright, Oh Sun You Are My Star "Tonight"
betterquesting:10.desc:8:
The Celestial Collector Crystal is far more powerful at gathering Starlight than the normal Collector Crystal. However, to function, it needs a structure to channel this power. Liquid Starlight will never be consumed from this structure, unlike the Starlight Infuser.
Remember to Link it to a Lens, Prism, or Starlight Altar with the Linking Tool, otherwise it won't help you!

This will finally allow you to generate enough Starlight for your Starlight Altar for you to be able to craft during the day!

When crafted, it will gain traits that will increase specific enchantments. Its effects are only active when equipped in the Amulet slot. It can be re-rolled to try to get better effects.

This is called gambling. May the rolls be with you.

Craft some Galactic Ingots with your Star of Revelation to unlock Galacticraft!

Note: This does NOT use up the Star of Revelation, however AE2 is not too well-informed, and it eats up the Star anyway. Use an external crafter (like an RFTools Crafter) if you want to automate the creation of Galactic Ingots!

The Domic Resonator is a direct upgrade to the Fosic Resonator. It adds another mode, which can be togged between. This mode displays the area of Starlight a single absorber, such as a Collector Crystal, consumed. Competing Starlight absorbers will have reduced effectiveness. To hide the preview, simply move far enough away.

When right-clicked on the focal block of a structure, the Sextant will display a phantom of the structure to help you build it.

(When right-clicked elsewhere, it will open a star map. Now this would normally help you find Astral Sorcery structures, buuuuut these structures have been disabled in this pack. Sorry!)

When placed down, it will slowly place Illumination Powder in any place that doesn't have sky access and isn't lit up. It has quite the range, being able to light up a huge area of the caves below ground. Remember, Illumination Powder can be removed by smothering it with a block.

Since Astral Sorcery structures are disabled, there needs to be a way to craft a Collector Crystal. This method is pretty expensive, and gives you a decent Crystal, but soon upcoming methods will make this much cheaper.

Nonetheless, craft this specific Collector Crystal in your 7x7 Elite Crafting Table, and place it in a location.

If directed towards a Starlight Altar, it will increase the Starlight within it, making crafting easier - and potentially letting small crafts occur during the day!

Craft some Constellation Papers! (These can no longer be found in the world.) They grant you knowledge about the exact look of each Astral Sorcery Constellation. You'll need more than 3, this is just to get you started. Overall there are 16 Constellations: 5 Bright, 7 Dim and 4 Faint. Each Constellation Paper should give you a unique one, so you won't have to craft more than 16 of these.

Later you'll be able to craft each specific Constellation Paper, and they'll be slightly less expensive too.

While this isn't §otechnically§o§r required for any quest, you need to discovery every Constellation this to complete this page. Better get cracking!

The Flügel Tiara is cool an' all, but you constantly need to refill it. Wouldn't it be better to use something that doesn't constantly lose its charge?! Well, your Astral studies have paid off: You can craft an Angel Ring now! There are 6 types, but they only differ in looks.

Make sure to have enough GP to use it and feel free to place it in your Bauble Ring slot.

Setup Fusion Crafting! Place the Fusion Crafting Core in the middle, and place the 9 Fusion Crafting Injectors nearby. Note that some recipe take more than 8 Crafting Injectors, but 8 is a good number to start with.

You'll need to power each Crafting Injector, and place the central item in each recipe in the Crafting Core and the outer item in the Injectors.

Eventually you'll NEED to automate this machine (preferably one of the higher tier ones), and it's not the easiest thing to do. Here are some important tips:

- Shift+Right Click each Injector to set it to Single Item Mode. That way only 1 item can enter the Injector, not a stack of items. Since many recipes take identical items, this is crucial so your items don't get stuck in 1 Injector.

- When using an ME Interface, set it to Blocking Mode. This way the Interface won't push items until the current crafting operation is done. But since the crafts are usually pretty slow, this won't solve all your issues.

- Some items can go in the Fusion Crafting Core for some recipes, and the Crafting Injectors in other recipes. So a simple filtering won't be enough to determine where each item should end up every time. Now you could just build 2 Fusion Crafting setups, but it's possible to automate all recipes with just 1. The solution is to use 2 ME Interfaces, both connected to the same Fusion Crafting setup. You can split your recipes so that each given item will only go into either the Crafting Core or one of the Crafting Injectors. Then, pull the items out from the ME Interfaces with EnderIO Conduits on different channels. It's basically like having 2 separate Conduit lines running in the same blockspace. Setup your Filters for each channel.

- Sometimes the ME System pushes items too fast and the system can get clogged. To avoid this, you can use a dummy item in each recipe, like a piece of Cobblestone for example. Each Crafting Pattern will then have the required ingredients and this dummy item in it. The items are pushed into a Chest, all the required ingredients are whitelisted to pass through, but the dummy item is only allowed to leave once the craft finishes. That way the ME Interface won't push the next set of items into the same Chest because of Blocking Mode. To remove the dummy item, trigger another whitelisted Conduit for a split second when the craft finishes. You can detect this by leading the output into a separate Chest once the craft finished, leaving it there, detecting its presence with a Comparator, and using this Redstone signal to get rid of the dummy item. You can use the same Redstone signal to get rid of the output item as well.

If you have any questions, the MindCrafters have a great tutorial for this:

https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=xogeV6wnwV0

(If you can't copy the link, search for "Fusion Crafting Automation - Draconic Evolution" by The MindCrafters.)

Although RFTools Control is being used in the video and it's not available here, it's only really used to provide a Redstone signal for the dummy item to leave its Chest. You can simply use EnderIO Conduits or an Import Bus with a Redstone Card for this.

We're closing in on the lategame... And so far, with the default settings, you only had 50 Chunks you were able to load. This changes to today! You need more Chunks to load, I know you do: Introducing the Chunk Loading Ward! Simply place it down inside a Chunk, and it'll be forever loaded!

Many servers will disable this, but even if they don't, check with your server owner to make sure using them is okay.
Now these items could have been crafted before you reached Mars, you didn't need them yet. So once you return, craft 5 Ambient Thermal Controllers and upgrade them later with Martian materials.

betterquesting:10.name:8: The God of War, the Red Planet
betterquesting:10.desc:8: Fly to Mars! Your landing will be softer thanks to the Tier 2 Rocket, so you won't even need to hold Space this time.

Craft a Satellite Controller and a Communications Dish Card. Then Right Click the Dish Card onto a Communications Dish and the Satellite Controller itself, and power the Controller from the top.

If the Communications Dish can find a Satellite in orbit, you'll be able to contact it to discover all the planets in order.

Once you've sent a Satellite into orbit, keep the Controller powered, and check back on it regularly. Maybe it has discovered a planet you can go to!
Build a Basic Satellite! You'll need additional infrastructure to send it up into space and contact it...
Craft a Communications Dish. This machine is used to locate Satellites you've launched into space. It is also used as a crafting ingredient.

Craft some Tier 2 Heavy-Duty Plates!



























I swear they're better and not just more expensive...! Trust me!

Obtain some Meteoric Iron! This is normally done by seeking some Fallen Meteors on the surface of the Moon, however that can be slow and tedious. Because of this, an alternative recipe has been added that you might want to use.
Craft some Compressed materials. I would recommend setting up separate Compressors for each of the items listed.

Make a Compressor and immediately upgrade it to an Electric Compressor!

This machine can make various Compressed and Heavy-Duty materials, and is vital to semi-automate it immediately. It's a bit awkward to fully automate it, since the input items don't spread out correctly, and so the machine doesn't craft.

You'll be able to overcome this limitation with the Ultimate Compressor, a Modular Machine only available after visiting the Moon. Until then, make a bunch of Compressors and CONSTANTLY keep crafting the requirements for Heavy-Duty Plates.

§6§6Remember that Galacticraft machines only accept power from the side with the green dot!

Craft some Heavy Oxygen Tanks! To fill them, place the into the bottom right slot of the Oxygen Compressor. Make sure to equip them in your Galacticraft inventory.

When on a planet that lacks Oxygen, a graphic on the top right of your HUD will show up, letting you know how much Oxygen you have left.

Craft an Oxygen Collector and an Oxygen Compressor.

1. Place the Oxygen Collector near some leaves (these can be natural or placed down), power it through the green dot on the side, and let it collect some Oxygen.

2. Place the Oxygen Compressor on the side with the black dot to transfer the collected Oxygen to it. Power it through its green dot as well.

3. Now you can place an Oxygen Tank in the bottom right slot to fill up with Oxygen.

You can also craft an Oxygen Storage Module to store some Oxygen. That way the filling process could be faster.

Make all 4 types of Galacticraft Wafers that are available at this point.

It'll come useful if you immediately automate them with 4 unique Circuit Fabricators.

betterquesting:10.name:8: What starts as black and becomes yellow afer refining?!
betterquesting:10.desc:8: Craft a Refinery! You can power it from the top, push Oil in from the left, and pull Fuel out on the right.

Make some Compressed Bronze and create your first Heavy-Duty Plates! Since this material will be used a LOT throughout Galacticraft, I highly recommend setting up a separate Compressor for it, and later fully automating it.

Craft a Tier 3 Rocket and obtain the Research Paper for Venus from your Satellitle Controller!

This Tier of Rocket will be capable of bringing you to both Venus AND the Asteroid Belt, the final two Galacticraft dimensions available in the pack. 

Before traveling to Venus, make sure you have all items listed in the Tier 1 Rocket quest. Additionally, you'll need to bring a Bucket and a Fluid container again, as well as your §cIsothermal Armor§f and §cShears§f.

Use the Tier 2 Dungeon Key you've obtained from the Evolved Creeper Boss to open the final Chest at the end of the Dungeon. You could either find the Schematic for the Automatic Cargo Rocket or the Tier 3 Rocket. You (again) need the latter, and they are (again) convertible into each other.
Craft all the items listed to the right for a Tier 3 Rocket!

Craft a full set of Isothermal Armor! Equipping these in your Galacticraft inventory will make your character immune to extreme heats or extreme colds. Like Venus! Did you know that the surface temperature of Venus is about 475 °C or 900 °C? Yay!
Craft a Frequency Module! When equipped in your Galacticraft inventory, you'll be able to hear MUCH better in space. It's also used as a crafting ingredient.

Refine some Oil into Galacticraft Fuel.

Also craft an Empty Canister and Right Click a container to fill it up with Fuel. Keep this on you, you might need it to return from a planet if something goes wrong. You don't wanna get stranded!

Use your Liquicrafter to create some Oil!

You'll need 1 Bucket of Actually Additions Empowered Oil, 1 Bucket of Thermal Expansion Tree Oil, and 1 Basic Wafer.

Note: Galacticraft Oil appears as 2 different items in JEI. However both of them can be used for the exact same thing. This is because Galacticraft doesn't actually use the Forge Liquid API like literally every other mod. Wonderful! If your quest isn't completing, then simply place down the Oil and pick it back up to convert it.
Craft a couple Sapphire Accelerators. These are components used for the Tier 2 Rocket.
Craft some Cheesy Wafers! Setup a fifth Circuit Fabricator to automate it!
Find some Sapphire Ore underground on the Moon! Or, you know, just use your Quarry.

Find some Secret Aliens Technology in above ground Mars Dungeons, and obtain some Bacterial Sludge from underground. Although the quest only asks for one, you'll need 5 Buckets of it to upgrade your Ambient Thermal Controllers.
Craft some Tier 3 Heavy-Duty Plates! They're eeeeeven better than the Tier 2 variants. Hurray!

betterquesting:10.name:8: It's always sunny in Phila- I mean on Venus
betterquesting:10.desc:8: Obtain some Fragments of the Sun from above ground Venus Dungeons!
Here we are! Venus. What a wonderf- Is that ACID RAIN? ... And why is there so HOT!? Ugh, I hate this place...

Craft a couple Single Solar Modules and combine them into a Full Solar Panel. You'll need 24 of the latter for a working Satellite, but as you can automate almost every part of the process (together than the Compressed materials), your ME System will happily do the job for you! Make sure to setup the required automation now. Go!

betterquesting:10.name:8: Awww, it isn't made out of cheese?
betterquesting:10.desc:8:
If you've made all the preparations, enter your Tier 1 Rocket and press Space to launch. Once you reach a high enough altitude, the map of the solar system opens up. Select the Earth and then select the Moon, and press "Launch" on the top right.

Make sure to hold spacebar when entering the Moon's orbit, otherwise you'll crash your Rocket. That wouldn't be great now, would it.

You can recover your Rocket and your Launch Pads after safely landing.

Craft a Tier 1 Rocket and 9 Rocket Launch Pads. Place down the Launch Pads in a 3x3 formation. If correctly assembled, the central square should pop up a bit. Place the Rocket on top and Fuel it up with your Fuel Loader.

§c§lBUT BEFORE YOU GO!§f

You need to make sure you can return, otherwise you WILL get stranded on the Moon. Even if you die, you'll respawn on the Moon again. To do this either take your Fuel Loader with you, or bring along some teleportation technology - choose from between EnderIO, Quantum Flux, Mekanism, and Astral Sorcery!
If you ever get stuck out in space, /home, /spawn, and /gchouston should all be able to take you back, but they should make you feel like a dirty cheater! >:D

SO READ THIS CHECKLIST BEFORE YOU GO:

1. Have you discovered the Moon in your Planet Progression Telescope? If not, check the previous quests.

2. Fuel up your Rocket to the maximum. (if you are doing the intended route, §cremember to bring the Fuel Loader and a power source with you§f).

3. Make sure you have your full Oxygen apparatus on you. This includes: an Oxygen Mask, an Oxygen Gear, two full Heavy Oxygen Tanks, and a Parachute. If you don't have the Parachute, you'll die upon landing.

4. Bring an additional Filled Fuel Canister and an additional Empty Canister. You might need to move some Fuel around to return.

5. Bring a Dungeon Locator, if you don't want to spend HOURS looking for an underground Dungeon.

6. A Frequency Module is technically optional, but without it you won't be able to hear much of anything on a planet without an atmosphere.

7. Bring some Food, Armor and Weapons.

8. Bring an RFTools Builder with a Shape Card Quarry, a power source and an inventory to place items into. A Dimensional Transceiver or an Ender Chest is the best option. You'll need a bunch of Ores and Rocks from the Moon, so might as well not do it manually.

Craft a Dungeon Locator! This is normally a tool usable only in Creative mode, but since underground Galacticraft dungeons can be really difficult to find, it's available to craft in this pack. Make good use of it on the Moon, Mars and Venus.

Craft a Telescope! This time you'll use it to discover planets, not stars.

Once your Satellite Controller is done researching, it'll spit out a Moon Research Paper. Put this in the top slot and power the Telescope with a Mekanism Energy Tablet while it does its research! Once it's done, you'll locate the exact position of the Moon and unlock the ability to travel to it!
Craft two Tier 1 Boosters! This will let you fly farther with your Rockets...!
Find a couple Spacerocks hidden inside the above ground custom Moon Dungeons!
Find some Cheese Ore underground on the Moon! Or, you know, just use your Quarry.

betterquesting:10.name:8: Welcome to 7x7 machines, I hope you'll enjoy your stay!
betterquesting:10.desc:8:
Make a Circuit Fabricator!

Although the quest only asks for one, you might as well make 4 (or 5), to automate every Wafer type. You can automatically input items from the top (they'll go into the right slots), and pull the output from the bottom.

It's also important to note that most Galacticraft machines can ONLY be powered from the left side, where the green dot is.

Craft some Tough Galactic Plating. I recommend setting up a couple Alloy Smelters with at least Melodic Capacitors to produce them passively, since you'll need a LOT of these going forward.

Then use them and your Galactic Ingots to craft your first Galactic Machine Frame!

Craft a Satellite Builder! This machine requires power input from the top.

Before you can visit any of the planets in person, you'll need to locate them, learn their orbit, and plot your trajectory. The Planet Progression mod does exactly this! You'll send up a Satellite into orbit, contact it, and slowly locate each of the available planets in order.
Craft a Basic Satellite Module! The quest only asks for one, but you'll need 6 for a complete Satellite.

betterquesting:10.name:8: To the red planet! Are there aliens...?
betterquesting:10.desc:8:
Craft a Tier 2 Rocket in your NASA Workbench and obtain the Research Paper for Mars from your Satellite Controller! Make sure to discover Mars before attempting to travel to it.

Before you launch, make sure again that everything is alright. If you're doing the intended way, you might want to bring even more fuel, 3 Filled Fuel Canisters will do.
Additionally, you'll need at least 1 empty Bucket and a Tank that can store at least 5 Buckets of Liquid. 

Read the Tier 1 Rocket quest "TO THE MOON!" again if you're unsure if you're missing something.

Insert the Key into the Tier 1 Dungeon Reward located behind the boss room. This might contain one of two Schematics: The Moon Buggy or the Tier 2 Rocket Schematic. You're looking for the latter, but fortunately even if you were unlucky and got the Moon Buggy Schematic, you can convert it into the one you need by crafting.
Craft a Nose Cone, 4 Rocket Fins and a Tier 1 Rocket Engine. These are the main components for a Tier 1 Rocket.
Craft an Oxygen Fan and upgrade it to an Oxygen Vent. This is a common component used in Galacticraft Rocket and Machine crafting.
Craft some Tin and Copper Canisters. These are simple crafting ingredients for some Galacticraft items and machines.

Obtain some Solar Ore from underground; some Volcanic Rock from around Lava pool, and near (or underneath) Volcanos; and at least 8 Buckets worth of Sulphuric Acid.

The easiest way to find Sulphuric Acid is to locate Vapor Spout blocks on groundlevel - a Sulphuric Acid pool will be right below. Alternatively, use the Roots Light Drifter spell and drift underground to spot them.

If you're low on Sulphuric Acid, you can duplicate the Liquid with some AbyssalCraft Crystallized Sulfur Clusters in the Liquicrafter.

Enough with the Lightning strikes!

With the RF Lightning Generator, you can convert RF directly into LE!

Find an Underground Moon Dungeon, enter it, and get to the end. Defeat the Evolved Skeleton Boss to obtain the Tier 1 Dungeon Key.

If you have a Dungeon Locator, it will point you to the nearest one, likely saving you a significant amount of time searching.

Craft some Crystaltine Ingots in your newly acquired 9x9 Crafting Table!

They are a pain to craft manually... But wait, the next quest might be able to help you on that.

Craft a Fuel Loader! When placed on the left side of a Launch Pad, and powered from the left, you can fill a Rocket on top of the Launch Pad.

To insert fuel, you'll need to use the right side, where the Launch Pad is normally. It's simplest to do this with a Phantomface.
Craft and equip an Oxygen Mask, an Oxygen Gear and a Parachute. These will be vital to survive out in space, and vital to come back and land without dying.
Craft 25 Satellite Launch Pads and assemble them into a 5x5 square. When correctly assembled, the middle square should pop up.
Use your Liquicrafter to process the Solar Ores you collected into Empowered Solar Dust and Solar Ingots!

Craft a Satellite Rocket! This is what you can use to send a Satellite into space:

1. Place the Satellite Rocket onto the 5x5 Satellite Launch Pad.

2. Place the Fuel Loader on the left of it to load some fuel into it. You'll need to power the Fuel Loader from the left.

3. Right Click the Satellite Rocket and place a Satellite into it.

4. Launch the Satellite Rocket. Your Satellite will be correctly sent into space!

5. Now you can use your Satellite Controller and Communications Dish to connect to the Satellite.

Make a NASA Workbench! This is used to build all your Rockets. For now, only the Tier 1 Rocket and the Satellite Rocket is available. To unlock more Schematics, you'll need to find them on Moon, Mars or Venus. To do so, scroll to the last page, insert the Schematic and press "Unlock Schematic".

(If you can't click on the buttons on the left because JEI is interfering, you can press Ctrl+O to disable JEI temporarily. Press it again to re-enable it.)

Most Rockets can have an inventory. Simply insert Chests in the top right when building the Rocket to add some.

Craft all the components for the Laser Focus multiblock listed on the right! You can use larger Input, Output and Energy input Hatches.

This machine focuses a laser beam at the input item to plasmafy it, charging it with a LOT of power... Good thing Portions of the Sun can transfer such energy, and Hyperglued Meteoric Casing can sustain it...!

You'll also need Mekanism Laser Energy, inputted near the tip of the Focus. You can easily convert RF into Mekansim Laser Energy using a Mekanism Laser. To charge the Mekanism Laser Acceptor faster, you can use all 4 sides. To make it EVEN faster, you can combine up to 5 Mekanism Laser beams into 1 stronger one using a Laser Amplifier.

betterquesting:10.name:8: It makes the Asteroid as strong as possible
betterquesting:10.desc:8:
Craft a block of Hyperglued Meteoric Casing!

The central point of this block is very strong and can sustain any sort of pressure...

Obtain the required materials listed on the right, and assemble them into a Liquicrafter Modular Machine multiblock.

You can use larger Input and Output Hatches, and you can use any kind of Conduit to import liquids and items into the Hatches on the left, and output them from the right.

This machine can combine liquids and items into other liquids and items, and it'll be used for some recipes from now on.

The first recipe you'll need it for is Galacticraft Oil, to be able to fuel your Rockets that you want to send to space.

betterquesting:10.name:8: Quarrying some Desh, Deshing some Quarry
betterquesting:10.desc:8: Obtain some Desh Ore from Mars. I recommend quarrying the place again.

After researching the Asteroid Belt, fly there with your Tier 3 Rocket!

Preparations include the same items as before. You won't need a Fluid container this time.

Find an Underground Mars Dungeon, enter it, and get to the end. Defeat the Creeper Boss! You can only do this by reflecting its projectiles back at it, similarly to Ghasts in the Nether.

If you have a Dungeon Locator, it will point you to the nearest one, likely saving you a significant amount of time searching.

Locate the underground Venus Dungeon using your Dungeon Locator! Get to the end and defeat the Spider Queen boss! Use some Shears to cut off some of her special string. Make sure to start from the bottom, otherwise you'll destroy the whole stem and get less string at the end.




You made sure to bring Shears like I told you riiiiiiiiiiiiiiiight...?

betterquesting:10.name:8: Parts of it still orbit the Sun to this day...
betterquesting:10.desc:8: Find 5 Chunks of Meteor that Ended the Era of Dinosaurs! They're located in custom Dungeon in the Asteroid Belt.

Break some Ilmenite Ore from the Asteroids. Then, process the Titanium Shards into Titanium Ingots.

If you use Silk Touch you get Ilmenite Ore directly, which has a more efficient conversion to Titanium Ingots.

The quest only asks for 10, but you'll need more eventually, so also setup a Quarry here.
Craft an Energy Beam Reflector and an Energy Beam Receiver to unlock Draconic Evolution Fusion Crafting!

Craft the required materials listed on the right to build an Ultimate Compressor! It's a MUCH faster variant of any of the base Galacticraft Compressors and it can craft even if the inputs are jammed up in a couple stacks. Woohoo!

betterquesting:10.name:8: Up, down, up, down, up, down...
betterquesting:10.desc:8: Craft 2 sets of Hydraulic Platforms! Place one in a 2x2 on the ground, and place the other one a couple blocks higher up. You can use this as a fancy elevator!
Craft your first Wyvern Core! It takes a quarter of a Mana Pool. You'll need a LOT of these, so it might be time to increase your Mana generation.
Craft a couple Draconic Energy Cores!
Use Dragon Egg Essence to craft some Dragon Eggs and Dragon Hearts!
Once the Wither slayer is correctly set up, take your prized Nether Stars and run off with them!

Make a Draconic Evolution Mob Grinder!

When powered, it's even capable of destroying the Wither with a single blow. Use this to your advantage and build a Wither killer machine! Summon the Wither using Wither Builders (or Formation Planes, Block Placers, your choice). Make sure it stays inside a Witherproof enclosement, and wait for its invulnerability to wear off. Then kill it with a Mob Grinder (it even works through the Witherproof wall)!

It's also important to mention, that the Wither CAN destroy your Wither Builder or other machines that aren't protected by Witherproof blocks. Popular solutions include:

- letting the Wither fall in a tall chamber while its invulnerability wears off, and killing it at the bottom.

- using Draconic Evolution portals made out of a Dislocator Receptacle and a some Draconium Infused Obsidian, and teleporting the Wither away from your precious machines into another Chamber with the Mob Grinder next to the outer walls. This design takes up less space but is more expensive.

Craft a Draconic Flux Capacitor! This is the highest tier Flux Capacitor available in the pack.

Charge it up in your Thermal Expansion Energetic Infuser or Draconic Evolution Energy Infuser.

Shift+Right Click with it to toggle it inbetween multiple modes. You can also equip this in a Bauble slot or just leave it in your inventory to charge your desired items.

Craft a Packager! You'll only ever need one Packager on your Network, which stores one copy of each Packaged Recipe Holder. The other copies are stored in individual Unpackagers.

If your Packager is running out of space, extend it with Packager Extensions!

Make some Packaging Components!

Packaged Auto is a mod that lets you encode recipes that have more than 9 unique input items. Good examples are Elevatium Ingots in the Laser Focus or some 9x9 crafts.

Craft a Quantum Compressor! This machine is capable of producing Singularities...! That's right! You'll need good material production using either a Quarry or preferably Seeds, and you'll need to compress them.

This machine needs to be powered, it needs a Singularitfication Catalyst in its left slot (which won't be used up), and all inputs can be inserted from the top and the sides, outputs can be extracted from the sides and the bottom.

Holds no energy, just takes it. 0 stars.

Even takes like a stack of Redstone Blocks. Make sure to automate their crystallization at least!

Make a Plasma Core in the Laser Focus and use it to craft your first Draconic Core!

All of the 4 included ingots are non-trivial, but all of them can be fully automated. You'll need a lot of Draconic Core moving forward, so make sure to automate every single step of its creation!

Channels are incredibly complicated. This is an attempt to guide you through channels, p2p, ad hoc networks, and subnetworks. If you have any questions,§  try things out in a creative testing world, and then ask on the discord.

Currently WIP

Finally you feel powerful enough to hold what seems to be pure Dark Energy in your hands...

Are you ready to abuse its powers?

Make your first 9x9 Crafting Table!

Something's missing though...

It's not EXTREME enough...
I swear this is the last tier of Machine Frames... For sure, this time! For suuuuuuuuuuure.....!!
Craft some Draconic Fusion Injectors! With these, you'll have access to almost all Draconic Evolution Infused items.

Craft all Draconic Tools & Weapons.

Similarly to your armor, you can further upgrade these by applying some Upgrade Keys to them through Fusion Crafting.

Upgrade your Inert Potato Armor into Infused Potato armor, then Right Click each piece to turn it into an Energized Potato piece!






















(Now you might think it's bad design not to have the Infused Potato pieces here, but if you Right Click one before this quests would detect it, then you'd have no way to finish the quest other than to recraft the piece from the start.)

Tier up the following Armor pieces until you obtain a full set of Inert Potato Armor:

1. Emeradic armor
2. Refined Coralium armor
