Craft some Dragon Egg Seeds! You'll need to plant them on some soil with a block of Dragon Egg Crux underneath. These were the 4 Dragons you needed to kill throughout the pack. Now you can craft everything that a Dragon would drop.

Make 4 Scheduling Processors!

They're used for the highest tier Storage Components and Packaged Auto items.

Do you like the idea of taking zero damage?

Do you like the idea of your armor being simply recharged by RF?

Do you like the idea of your armor providing you with Creative flight?

DO YOU WANNA BE OVERPOWERED?!?!?!?

Well then. This is the armor set for you. Make good use of it.

This is it...

It's finally EXTREME enough!

The difference is...

More POWER!

Yeeeessss!

I can craft EVEN MORE POWERFUL items in this...!

Nothing can stop me now!

Craft a Wyvern Flux Capacitor! Charge it up in your Thermal Expansion Energetic Infuser or Draconic Evolution Energy Infuser.

Shift+Right Click with it to toggle it inbetween multiple modes. You can also equip this in a Bauble slot or just leave it in your inventory to charge your desired items.
Charge up some Draconium Blocks in the Laser Focus, then use your Fusion Injector setup to convert them into Awakened Draconium Blocks!
Well what can you do with your Basic Fusion Crafting setup...? Immediately upgrade it to Wyvern tier! Yup! That's it. Nothing else. So do it!

Craft a Package Recipe Holder! This Pattern can have up to 20 recipes that all use up to 81 unique input items. To encode it, use the Package Recipe Encoder. You can also copy its settings there onto another Package Recipe Holder, but make sure not to override one that already holds some recipes. It's safest to check each Recipe Holder first by placing them into the Encoder and hitting "Load" one by one. Only press "Save" if you're sure you intend to override the input Recipe Holder.

You'll need 2 identical Recipe Holders for each craft, one for the Packager and one for the Unpackager.

Upgrade your Wyvern Armor into a full set of Draconic armor!

The upgrades aren't over though... Check the Draconic Evolution Upgrade Keys in JEI to make your Armor even stronger!

betterquesting:10.name:8: It's got Sparklez like a certain Captain
betterquesting:10.desc:8:
Now that you have a steady source of Nether Stars, make a couple Crystal Matrix Ingots!

(If you're low on Diamonds, craft a Diamond Seed!)

Craft an item Dislocator! This is the best Magnet available so far, even better than the Greater Ring of Magnetization.

Simply Shift+Right Click to activate / deactivate it. You can also place it in a Bauble slot.

"Can my Magnet get even better?!?!?!" - is what you'd think, and yes, yes it can. This is the best Magnet available in the pack, and it work similarly to the previous tier:  Simply Shift+Right Click to activate / deactivate it, and you can place it in a Bauble slot.

Needing to automate some 5x5, 7x7 or 9x9 Extended Crafting recipes?! Well, look no further than the Automation Interface!

1. Once crafted, place it on top of an Extended Crafting 5x5, 7x7 or 9x9 Crafting Table, and setup a recipe in the Crafting Table on the bottom (you can use the "+" button from JEI).

2. Then open your Automation Interface and click the "Save Recipe" icon on the bottom left.

3. It's important to also click the Gear icon on the bottom right and choose which direction the input items are coming from and which direction the output items should go to.

4. Power the Interface with some RF, and use perhaps an ME Interface to send items to it and back. To save on ME channels, you can use one ME Interface for 8 Automation Interfaces by whitelisting which items should go into which crafts from the ME Interface.

Craft a full set of Wyvern tools & weapons. These tools can be charged up and upgraded.

You can also apply the Reaper enchantment to the Sword to sometimes obtain Mob Souls when killing Mobs. These can then be used in Stabilized Mob Spawners.

Simlarly to the armor pieces, you'll need to tier up weapons and tools through the exact same tiers as before.

betterquesting:10.name:8: The balance of power must be preserved
betterquesting:10.desc:8: Craft the most "BALANCED" tool in the game. Yup.

Craft a Package Recipe Encoder! Use this machine to Encode recipes that take more than 9 unique input items. You can fill any slot in the 9x9 with the requirements. The maximum amount of unique items you can have is 81.

Throughout the entire modpack, you'll only need to kill the Ender Dragon 4 times. You had to have killed it at least twice now; once in the first Exploration section, and once to get your first Dragon Scale for Bewitchment. You might need to kill it 2 more times, if so, grab your Ender Crystals, resummon it, and whack it a couple times. It's the perfect way to test out your new armor set anyway!

Collect some Dragon Eggs and craft a Dragon Token to continue.
To use your Packaged recipes, you'll need to place an Unpackager before each machine, in place of an ME Interface.

Build a Draconic Energy Storage multiblock structure!

This quest asks for Tier 4, but you can build a higher tier one to store even more power!

If you're unsure of the construction, consult your Draconic Evolution Information Tablet. You can also simple Right Click the Energy Core to see the exact layout.

Tier 1 stores 45.5 Million RF
Tier 2 stores 273 Million RF
Tier 3 stores 1.64 Billion RF
Tier 4 stores 9.88 Billion RF
Tier 5 stores 59.3 Billion RF
Tier 6 stores 356 Billion RF
Tier 7 stores 2.14 Tillion RF, or Java's Max Integer Limit (the highest number possible in Java)
Tier 8 stores 2^63 RF. Best represented by "Infinite". Even if you generate a very respectable 10 Million RF/tick, you'd need over 1460 IRL years to fill it up... So, just consider it an infinite power storage!

To insert or extract energy, use Energy Pylons. Plcae them nearby the multiblock, and place a Glass block on top or on the bottom, closer to the center of Energy Storage structure.

You can simple Right Click the blue orb that forms to toggle between input and output mode.

You can craft Green Heart Canisters now...!

No need to hurry though, they're not an easy thing to acquire.




















I spent the last two weeks just screaming,
I spent the last two weeks just screaming...
Trying to work you out is killing,
Ever since my heart's been missing...

Finally, after all this time, you gain access to Blue Hearts, the final tier of Heart Canisters!

They're not the easiest thing to make, but eventually I'm sure you can max out the final layer of hearts.

Craft a Mantle of the Stars. This is the only armor from Astral Sorcery you can get - and its one of the most powerful and varied in the game. You can attune (and reattune, overwriting the prior attunement) the Mantle to specific constellation for buffs and effects - which will be listed here. Additionally, all Mantles have +80% Chaos Resistance, which is direct damage reduction against the Chaos Dragon, a terrifying boss that you will have to fight soon (Chapter 25).

When attuned to:

Discidia, 1/3 of damage against you is added to your next attack.
Armara, you gain 3 charges of complete damage protection, which slowly regen.
Vicio, an elytra that does not lose durability from flying - and can be upgraded to creative flight via a perk.
Aevitas, slowly restores missing health and hunger.
Evorsio, breaks block faster, mines in an AOE, and does damage to nearby mobs.
Lucerna, highlights nearby mobs and spawners.
Mineralis, highlights nearby blocks that match what is in your hand or offhand.
Horologium, freezes all nearby mobs when hit, but has a minute long cooldown.
Octans, gives water breathing, and removes all movement and tool usage penalties for being submerged.
Bootes, flares spawn when you are attacked, and will attack your most recent attacker.
Fornax, applies healing equal to the damage taken from fire.
Pelotrio, when breaking a block or attacking a mob, spawn a Spectral Tool, which will then attempt to mirror what you are doing.

BQ, short for Better Questing, allows pack makers to create a detailed quest system for players, as both guide and goal. It can be opened by a keybind (default: K).

Quests are broken up into small Chapters. You don't have to completely finish one to begin working on the next, but you could if you wanted to. 
In this pack we have made the major points, which unlock real progression through the next Chapter, larger and distinct.

Quests have a requirement to complete, located on the right side. On the top left, they have a description of what the quest is (or a pun). On the bottom left, they will typically have a reward, which can be claimed by clicking the "Claim" button at the bottom. Some quests are "Choice Quests", meaning you must choose between one of several rewards before claiming.

Quests have different forms as you unlock them and progress through them:
When you cannot access a quest and thus cannot complete it, it has a gray background.
- Unlocked quests are indicated by a glowing red background.
- Completed, but with quest rewards still unclaimed quests are indicated by a glowing blue background.
- When you have completed a quest and claimed its reward (if any), it turns into a static green background.

Additionally, there are 6 buttons on the left side of the screen.
From top to bottom, they are:
- Toggle the visibility of Questlines, or Chapters.
- Display the description of the Chapter you are on.
- Claim all quest on the page (note that Choice Quests will not be claimed).
- Adjust the viewing size so all quests are displayed.
- Lock the tray, which keeps the chapter selection open.
- Back, which returns to the home page.

Lastly, you can see the requed quests to unlock a quest by enabling "Advanced Tooltips" by pressing F3+H.

JEI, or Just Enough Items, is the most downloaded mod ever. It is used to search items and recipes that mods add. As such, its crucial to understand how JEI works.

Left Clicking on an item or pressing your recipe key (default: R) displays all the recipes to craft that item - show it won't show anything if there are no recipes to make it.

Right Clicking on an item or pressing your use key (default: U) displays all the recipes that use that item - again, if there are none it won't do anything.

You can use the scroll wheel to change pages when viewing recipes. You can also use the Backspace key to go back to the previously viewed recipe.

On the right side of the recipe viewer, you see all* the places that recipe can be done in.
    *due to compatibility issues, its only most, not literally all.

If you click on the title of the page, you can "Show All Recipes", which lists every recipe in the game! 

Pressing your Bookmark key (default: A) saves the item to the left side of your inventory - use this to keep track of what you intended to do 3 seconds ago.



How to search with JEI:

JEI uses substring matching, meaning searching "coal" finds both "Coal" and "Charcoal".

You can search from a mod by using @ - eg. "@botania" finds everything from the mod Botania.

You can search for two separate things by separating them with JEI's "or" symbol |, a vertical line, typically located above the Enter key.

You can exclude results by attaching a - before it, eg. "-@minecraft" finds everthing that isn't from Vanilla Minecraft.

You can also combine these, for example while "@alchem" would show both Alchemistry and Blood Magic: Alchemical Wizardry items, you can use "@alchem -@blood" to show only Alchemistry, or you can use for example "@alchem -@blood|singu" to search for everything in Alchemistry AND Singularities.

If you can't find an item in a Chest or a Crafting field, JEI allows you to double click the search bar to toggle highlighting, which will highlight any item in an inventory that matches your search.

If you'd like to import a recipe into a Crafting Table without having to lay it out, you can simply view the recipe in JEI while in the Crafting interface, and Left Click the "+" button. That will move all items into the Crafting field. If you'd like to move as many items into the Crafting field from your inventory as possible, hold Shift while pressing the "+" button.

Note: This is not for setting up servers, ask on the Discord for that. This is only for players when playing as a team.

Want to play with a team? There are only a few steps you need to do.

For questing:

Step 1: Go to the home page of the questbook by clicking the back button in the bottom left.
Step 2: Click on Party, and invite the person you want with you.
Step 3: Have them accept quickly, as invitations are time sensitive.

Now they have joined your questbook party, and all quest progress will advance ALL players on the team.

For claimed chunks:

Step 1: Open your inventory and click "My Team" in the top left.
Step 2: Click on Members and add them.
Optional: Click on settings and change the display name.
Now they have joined your FTB Team, and can interact with things in your claimed chunks.

Later on, with the mod Extra Utilities 2:
To share Grid Power, do §c/xu_powersharing§r and select your teammates. They must do the same to you for Grid Power to be shared.

That's about it!

Keyboard shortcuts, not hot strats to bypass challenges. 

Pressing T while hovering over an item in your inventory or JEI will highlight nearby inventories with that item inside, indicated by a white dust particle effect. If there are no valid inventories, it will do nothing.

Pressing F3+Q displays a list of all F3+[x] shortcuts, and what they do.

F3+H, or Display Advanced Tooltips, will allow you to see extremely helpful information - while it may be a bit much, the benefit it adds is incredible. One of these benefits is allowing you to see the exact requirements to unlock the quest - meaning you aren't scrambling around trying to figure out what you missed midway through a later chapter.
While not a shortcut, you can enable NBT data visibility by opening your inventory, clicking on the gray cog in the top left called "Client Settings", selecting FTB Library, and setting "Display Item NBT" to true.

F3+G, or Show Chunk Borders, allows you to see the, well, borders of the chunk you are in. However, a superior option exists, by default bound to F9. This allows you to switch between 4 modes:
- Invisible,
- Corners,
- Full (similar to F3+G)
- Region.

Use this to make sure you never build a complex automation process across a chunk border that then unloads, as that can clog things up, or even cause crashes.

F7, or Show Spawnable Spaces, highlights all currently spawnable spaces as Red, and all spaces that are spawnable during the night.

P, or Place in World puts the item you are currently holding into the world, somewhat akin to placing it in an item frame.

F3+P, or Pause on Lost Focus only does something in Singleplayer. This is active by default, and when it is active, switching tabs while not in an inventory will open the escape menu, pausing the game. 

F3+A, or Reload Chunks, will reload any loaded chunks, which can fix issues such as chunks not rendering, or blocks being invisible.

There are a wide variety of other shortcuts useful as you progress through the pack, if you check Escape -> Options -> Controls, you can see and change almost all of them.

Divine Journey 2, often shortened as "DJ2" is an expert pack oriented around DivineRPG and automating Magic Mods.
DJ1, typically known as Divine Journey, was a pack with similar goals made for 1.7.10 in 2017. You do not have to play DJ1 to understand DJ2.

DJ2 is an Expert Pack. This means different things to different people, but here we are using it to mean:

1. The pack will take a long time to complete.

2. The pack is structured around progression - most things are gated, many recipes are changed from their default.

3. The recipes will be expensive, and will require automation - sometimes minimal, sometimes extreme. Fortunately, there are a lot of tools that help you in this endeavor, and they'll slowly get unlocked through the first half of the pack. Applied Energistics is going to be your friend, you'll need to autocraft or autoprocess almost everything that there is a quest for.


The goal of the modpack is to "Find the Meaning of Life", already located inside a convenient bag in your inventory upon startup, so it shouldn't be that hard to.... Oh. Oh hold on a second. It needs some sort of a Key to open... The "Key to Infinity?" Oh. Oh no. That's gonna be hard.

Similarly to Divine Journey, you'll need "Infinite Infinity Ingots", while not truely "infinite" this time, you'll need a LOT to craft the Key to Infinity, and it'll be best done using a Creative Chest.

Soooo the goal of the pack is basically to get to Creative items... Not so original, I know.


But what IS original is the progression. Over 450 custom items and over 3000 changed recipes will guide you towards the end... Good luck!


The structure of the modpack is the following:

1. Early game: Vanilla Minecraft, Tinker' Construct, Totemic, Roots, Immersive Engineering, Early game Mekanism, AE2 Item Storage.

2. Big Exploration Block: Better Nether, Twilight Forest (optional), Atum 2, Erebus, Aether I, Iceika.

3. Big Tech Block:
   - Stage 1: Extra Utilities Pt.1, Open Blocks, Mob Grinding Utils
   - Stage 2: Thermal Expansion, EnderIO Pt.1, AE2 Crafting Terminal & Fluid Storage
   - Stage 3: Industrial Foregoing, some RFTools, SolarFlux Reborn, QuantumFlux
   - Stage 4: Actually Additions, EnderIO Pt. 2, Simply Jetpacks
   - Stage 5: Mekanism Pt. 2, Extra Utilities Pt. 2, AE2 Autocrafting & Autoprocessing, Wireless AE2, Ender Utilities, Ender Storage.

4. Big Magic Block:
   - Stage 1: AbyssalCraft Pt. 1, DivineRPG start, Blood Magic Pt. 1, EvilCrat Pt. 1
   - Stage 2: AbyssalCraft Pt. 2, Botania Pt. 1
   - Stage 3: Botania Pt. 2, Blood Magic Pt. 2, EvilCraft Pt. 2
   - Stage 4: Thaumcraft
   - Stage 5: Bewitchment
   - Stage 6: Thaumic Augmentation, Thaumic Energistics
   - Stage 7: DivineRPG end, LightningCraft, Extreme Reactors
   - Stage 8: Astral Sorcery. lategame Extra Utilities, Galacticraft

5. Lategame: Draconic Evolution, Alchemistry, AgriCraft, RFTools Dimensions, Avaritia, Creative Items, Unlocking the Meaning of Life.

betterquesting:10.name:8: Beam Core? Huh, more like Be-gone Core!
betterquesting:10.desc:8: Break down some Beam Cores into Nickel Chloride and Polyvinyl Chloride!

betterquesting:10.name:8: I though it was over... But alas, more Cores!
betterquesting:10.desc:8: Obtain some Kaolnite from Draconic or Wyvern Cores, and combine it with Barium, Psyllium and Chaotic Cores to get the actual final tier of Draconic Evolution Cores: The Corrupted Core!
Break down Refined Coralium into Psyllium, or use some Hybrid Abyssalium to also get Potassium Permaganate.

Get some Hand Purple from Wyvern Cores or Barium Sulfate from Crystaltine Ingots, and break them down further into elemental Barium.

...

- Why are Helium, Curium and Barium called the medical elements?

- Because if you can't Helium or Curium, you Barium!

It is highly recommended that you do the "Growing Chaos" quest at the top of this Chapter before doing this quest, so you won't have to kill another Chaos Guardian... unless... you'd LIKE to do that. Then go ahead.

Build the Chemical Caster multiblock! Note that all 4 Casting Tables require an Ingot Cast to be placed in them.

The quest requires an additional Resistive Heater, which you'll use to provde heat for the machine. You can use any Mekanism Heat Acceptor on the top. Simply power the Resistive Heater, and set its power usage high first (to a couple thousand RF/tick), to have it heat up. Once it's sufficiently hot, you can bring its power usage down to only about 200 RF/tick. It takes a little while to have the heat transfered to the multiblock, so be patient.

Using this machine, you can cast any solid Alchemistry element into its Ingot form. It's fast, and it's available earlier than the Chemical Combiner, which is also capable of doing this. However the Combiner can create a bunch of Compounds as well.

You'll likely end up using both of the machines later on.
Break down Tungsten into Rubidium in the Fission multiblock!

betterquesting:10.name:8: Why didn't you tell Alphonse Elric about this?!
betterquesting:10.desc:8:
Build the Fission Controller multiblock!

You can check your Alchemistry Guidebook to see how to constuct it, but it's a simple 5x5x5 hollow cube of Fission Casing blocks, with a 3-tall pillar of Fission Cores in the center. Then make sure to place the Fission Controller while looking AT the multiblock. (Sometimes the Guidebook shows its orientation incorrectly.)

Then power the Controller, and you can input and output items from any side.
Break down Bismuth into Molybdenium in the Fission multiblock!
Use Potassium Dichromate, Chromium Oxide, Wafers or Rainbow Plates to get some Chromium!
Get some Antimony Trioxide from End Steel, and break it down further into pure Antimony!
Combine some Zirconium, Yttrium and some Beryllium Alimude into Zircyttrid Beryllium Alumide!

Break down Beryl Zincite to get Beryllium Alumide and Silicon Trioxide!


...Oh, the wonders of Alchemy!
Break down some Platinum, Iridium or Gold in the Fission Multiblock to obtain some Yttrium!
Break down some Gold or Mercury in the Fission multiblock to obtain some Zirconium!
Make an Atomizer to turn any Fluid into atoms and molecules! It's the easiest way to get H20 or any other molecule that has a liquid form in room temperature.
No, it's pretty strong. Make some!

betterquesting:10.name:8: Heat resistant AND allows for circuits
betterquesting:10.desc:8:
Zirconium
Yttrium
Scandium
Copper
- 
Beryllium
Alumide
Argon
Carbonate
Helium

Sheet.

Or, a Zysc-Baach Sheet, for short.

Craft it in the Liquicrafter!

Remember than Helium and Argon are considered liquids right now, so use liquid transporting Tanks or Fluid Conduits.
Break down Niobium further into Scandium!
Break down some Lithium or Beryllium in the Fission multiblock into Helium!

betterquesting:10.name:8: Where have all the flowers gon
betterquesting:10.desc:8: Break down Rubidium further into Argon!
Break down Luminessence to get Urea, then break it down further into Amide!

Combine liquid Mercury, Potassium Carbonate and Potassium Cyanide in your Liquicrafter to obtain some Growth Infusion Liquid!

The easiest way to get liquid Mercury is in the Alchemistry Liquifier, which you can craft right after you obtain some Chromium-Barium Compounds. Its quest is located near the center of this Chapter, called "Melting Atoms".

Finally, use your Growth Infusion Liquid to obtain some Crop Sticks!

These sticks are way more powerful than they look like - they allow you to duplicate any Mystical Agriculture Seed planted on them, either through spreading or using the Clipper.

You can also mutate the same type of crop with itself by planting 2 of them on a Crop Stick placed diagonally from each other, and placing a double-Crop Stick in the corner. The Seeds will eventially mutate (which you can speed up a lot with the Imaginary Time Block), creating a potentially better one.

Each AgriCraft Seed has 3 stats, and maxing them out is commonly referred to as "10/10/10'ing the Seed". The last 10 doesn't matter for this pack, as weeds as disabled, but the first two increase the rate at which the crop grows and the second one increases the average yield of the crop.

You can check the 10/10/10'ing progress in a Seed Analyzer.

You'll need a bunch of Seeds in one of the later Chapters, so definitely take advantage of AgriCraft!
Break down some material crafted from Elevatium Ingots or Elevatium itself to obtain Potassium Cyanide. Also break down specifically the green, Corrosive Will Crystals to obtain Potassium Carbonate.

Craft an Evaporator. When a fluid is placed in it, it will slowly evaporate into an item. You'll want to passively automate this, as you'll need a large amount of Mineral Salt.

You can push fluids from any side and pull items from any side as well.

Craft a Chemical Dissolver! Give it some power and toss in a material and it will dissolve down into elements. You can push inputs and pull outputs from any side.

If you'd like to craft more Dissolvers but you don't have enough Chaos Shards, try to move towards the quest near the top of this Chapter called "Growing Chaos" that allows you to craft Tiny Chaos Fragments!

This quest also unlocks a lot of other quests on this page that aren't connected to it. This is because the connections would get really messy otherwise!

§6(Note that if you have for some reason enabled edit mode, you must disable it to continue.)

Okay I might have lied when I said the Draconic Machine Frame was the highest tier... but I swear this time there is no more... no more Machine Frame tiers... nah-ah, not at all. Nada. Yup. Definitely.

Dissolve Meteoric Iron to gain some Calcium Carbonate. Your immediate use for them is to craft Mekanism Heat Input blocks from Modular Diversity.

However you might need more Chaos Shards for the upcoming multiblock, some check out the quest near the top of this Chapter called "Growing Chaos" to get more!

betterquesting:10.name:8: So THAT's what Mana tastes like
betterquesting:10.desc:8: Break down AbyssalCraft Crystallized Mana or Runes of Mana into Ammonium. Your best bet is to use the highest tier AbyssalCraft Crystallized Mana Clusters.
Obtain some Beryl from Mirion Ingots and Zinc Oxide from Alchemical Brass, and combine them into Beryl Zincite!

Craft a Chemical Combiner! This machine allows you to create a bunch of Compounds as well as any Alchemistry Ingot. You can also create some basic materials with it.

Similarly to the Dissolver, you can input and output from any side.

You can combine up to 9 inputs, and each input slot can have any number of items. Sometimes putting elements into different slots will yield different results, for example both a Copper Ingot and a piece of Copper Dust takes 16 Copper elements, and placing the input into slot 1 or 2 will determine what the output is going to be.

This machine is 4x slower than the Chemical Caster multiblock, however it's still an essential block.

In order to automate it, it's best to set a target recipe by looking at a Combiner recipe in JEI, and pressing the "+" button to import it into the machine. This way, all the input ingredients will land in the correct slot.

To create AE2 Patterns for the machine, use Alchemistry Slot Fillers wherever you don't want an item to be placed. These Slot Fillers are incredibly cheap, but get consumed upon crafting, so you'll want a lot of them.
Break down AbyssalCraft Methane into Alchemistry Methane!

Use one of the main Impetus items to get Strontium Carbonate and break it down further into regular Strontium!

You might want to semi-automate the creation of some of these Impetus items. You can use an External Crafter to keep your Primordial Pearl repaired.

However, once you get to Fission, you'll be able to break down regular old Osmium into Strontium, so it's not hugely important to automate it now.

Combine some materials in your Chemical Combiner into some Alchemistry Fertilizer, then into some Mystical Fertilizer!

You can use the latter to Bone Meal your Mystical Agriculture crops.
Combine some Ammonium, Hydrogen and Phosphate in your Chemical Combiner into Diammonium Phosphate!
The Electrolyzer is an optional machine, but it's the easiest way to get Chlorine using only Water and Salt as the inputs.
Make some Chromium Barium Compound!
While regular Titanium does yield Titanium elements, you can only get Titanium Oxide from Compressed Titanium or Titanium Boxes. The Boxes reliably yield more, not just with a 50% chance.
Break down some Evil Infused Iron into Lead Iodide, and break it down further into regular Iodine!

Melt some Nether Stars to get Hydroxylapatite, and break it down further into Phosphate.

This might be the perfect time to upgrade your Wither farm as well!

betterquesting:10.name:8: So that's why your Tung Stanks when you bite this
betterquesting:10.desc:8: Dissolve some Stone Ichor ingot Tungsten!

1. First use Iodine, Mercury and Copper Chloride in your Liquicrafter multiblock to get a little bit of Impure Mercury-Iodine Mixture.

2. Then purify this liquid with some Nickel Chloride to get pure Liquid Iodine.

3. Finally, combine 10mB of Liquid Iodine with some Mesquite and Titanium Oxide to get 6 Tiny Chaos Fragments!

It might not be a bad idea to automate this entire process. I recommend using 3 separate Liquicrafters for it.

betterquesting:10.name:8: We can't GO to Mercury, but we can GET some Mercury
betterquesting:10.desc:8: Break down Supremium Ingots into Mercury Sulfide, and break it down further into elemental Mercury.

betterquesting:10.name:8: It is nature green or poison green...?
betterquesting:10.desc:8: Alloy up some Cadmium and Arsenic! What could POSSIBLY go wrong?!
Break down some Flying Ointment into Cadmium Sulfide, and break it down further into Cadmium elements.

betterquesting:10.name:8: Taste the rainbow... Or don't, actually, DON'T!!!
betterquesting:10.desc:8:
Break down Rainbow Plates into Arsenic Sulfide and further into pure Arsenic.

So yeah, DON'T taste the Rainbow. For your own safety.

betterquesting:10.name:8: "Sap Hire" - is what a gemotoligist would call "Free Honey".
betterquesting:10.desc:8: Combine some Cobalt Aluminate, Potassium Permanganate and Aluminum Oxide to get your first Sapphire Gem!
Break down some Mirion Ingots or Blocks into Cobalt Aluminate!
Combine some Han Purple and Calcium Carbonate into Han Calcite!
Break down Silver into some Vanadium!

1. Melt your elemental Tungsten in your Liquifier.

2. Then also melt some Nitrogen. Even though Nitrogen is a gas, this time it can only be picked up in Fluid tanks! Low on Nitrogen? Well, there are several ways to get it. Check out all the possibilities in JEI!

3. The combine the above two liquids with a Copper Canister, some Barium Calcite, some Silicon Trioxide, some Dense Ice from the Asteroid Belt and some Sapphire to obtain an Oxygen-Rich Barium Calcite Perpetuator!

There are lot of quest titles and quest descriptions, and these seeds really haven't been giving me much to work with, you know? Cut me some slack, Im trying my best. Like, what could you come up with for Wither Skeleton Seeds, Titanium Seeds, and End Steel Seeds? I know I could have arranged them differently, perhaps shuffled these and Sortless around, but that would ruin the theme of Sortless requiring just the base tier 4 seed, with Patternless requiring an additional (or two!) seeds to be crafted. Really, the name of this quest is a lie, because I made sure theres a pattern for everything. Its important to notice the patterns - they tell you a lot about how something works. Or doesn't, depending. As is the case here - there is a pattern, but its not something you can construct a name based on. Its not a pattern substantial enough to create with. Some patterns just aren't there enough to impact the world. But maybe you can never be certain of the pattern of a thing. Your perception of an instance may change with time, and while the patterns within it will not, is perception not reality? Does your perception of a pattern create the pattern? Is a pattern but a social construct we create to comfort ourselves in the chaotic cosmos that encompasses all we might ever know? So perhaps a better name for this quest would be "Patternless?". However, that attracts less attention that a statement delivered with certainty, such as "Patternless". And if one believed that attention creates what is given attention, would it not be in the interests of a creator to attract as much attention as possible? In each mind that gives it attention, their work is replicated.
So is birthed clickbait, the art form of creating predominantly visual stimulus that increases the value of a product in the prospective buyer's mind beyond what they would have otherwise believed it to be. Clickbait is often said to be a misrepresentation of the contents of the product, but this is a misunderstanding of the term. For example, this quest name was misleading, but was not clickbait, as it was not designed and likely did not increase your internal evaluation of the quest within. Clickbait can be misleading, but it is far more commonly used to highlight the best qualities of the product within. This understanding of clickbait includes advertising, although advertising frequently induces the belief in value, and is not limited to simply increasing it.
Another aspect of this concept is memes - that of actions or information spreading and mutating via imitation of others. It is most commonly used to refer to jokes on shared the internet, but ideas spreading and mutating via imitation is as old as humanity. Gossip and fireside tales are examples of memes prior to the internet. The folk tales told varied based on the teller, but the most successful elements were consistently included in them. The characters have different names or faces, the setting may change, the exact actions vary, but the themes remain.
The creation of a meme and creation of clickbait are, while unique in purpose, similar in action and goal: to get people to spend their attention on it, using references and hooks to increase engagement. Some people do this for fun, as a hobby, as a creative outlet. Others do it for profit, to convince you that entry is worth the price. Everything you know influences your choices. And now you know this. Will this knowledge change what you do? Would you even know if it had? In this essay, I will...
All jumbled up.

The first benefit of pretending to know how to use Infusion is to craft Elevatium Ingots with a higher yield! Change your Elevatium automation to be more efficient!

Craft some EnderUtilities Portal Frames and 2 Portal Control Panels! These are the best Teleportation Devices you could get your hand on so far, as they do not require any power, and can send you to either another EnderUtilities Portal (with the Link Crystal (Portal)), or using any of the other 2 Link Crystals, you get also go to a some other Location or Block you specify (but you won't be able to return in that case).

They're very handy, and can be built vertically or horizontally, in any shape and size (within limits), as long as the Portal Frame blocks from a closed loop!

Build the Mob Loot Fabricator Modular Machine structure! The quest doesn't ask for Bromine, but you'll need 8 Buckets of it.

This machine uses a bit of energy and mana to output a MASSIVE amount of useful mob loot. No longer will you need laggy Spawners!

The maintenance cost is also very low - it requires 2 units of Mana per tick, and since a Mana Pool can hold 1,000,000 units of Mana, you'll be able to use the machine for 25,000 seconds or almost 7 IRL hours on just 1 full Mana Pool.

The machine works on percentages, every 2 ticks it rolls a die for each and every single possible output, and if it lands on a certain number, it outputs the given mob loot. So technically it's possible to output ALL types of mob loots AT ONCE, although astronomically unlikely. But, because of this, §6you'll need a large output buffer§r. The machine can generate 72 unique items, so to avoid clutter, I recommend 3 Ludicrous Item Output Hatches (which you can craft now), or multiple smaller Output Hatches. §6There are 7 locations you can place Output Hatches on the machine, make sure their total capacity is at least §c72 slots§6 for the machine to function.

betterquesting:10.name:8: Let the Lights Dim, Dim the Let Right
betterquesting:10.desc:8:
The Dimlet Workbench lets your break down and combine Dimlets into other ones.

Do you want to find a dimension full Molten Mithril oceans but no luck so far? Well, place down this machine, look for 'Molten Mitrhil' and check what it needs. Maybe you already have all the Dimlet parts that are needed for its construction. If not, explore more RFTools Dimensions and find more Dimlet containing buildings to loot.

It turns out that even through the previously made 'alloy' of sorts had some unforeseen properties, it's also pretty useful in some ways....

It allows you to create seemingly 'randomized' dimensions...! The oceans can be made out of Molten Gold, the terrain could be filled with Diamond Block tentacles... You never know!

Welcome to RFTools Dimensions!

Craft an Empty Dimension Tab!

This is the main and most important item of RFTools Dimensions, as this is where Dimensions are going to be stored. However, it's also simply used a crafting ingredient.

To craft it, you'll have to make a Master Infusion Crystal and convert some Insanium into Perfectium. The Master Infusion Crystal has infinite durability and can convert any type of Essence into the next tier. I recommend setting up an external RFTools Crafter to convert to higher tier Essences.
All the ProjectRed Seeds!

betterquesting:10.name:8: Train the Terrain to attain the Domain
betterquesting:10.desc:8: Craft a Terrain Absorber. Similarly to the other Absorbers, place it down, and let it absorb the current Terrain type it's in. You might need to visit specific RFTools Dimensions to absorb the type of terrain you want.

Craft a Dimension Builder! This is the most powerful RFTools Dimensions machine. It lets you power up your Realized Dimension Tabs.

First, Dimensions need to be created. Simply put it in the Dimension Builder and provide the machine with power to build the dimension. Then, while you want to visit the dimension, §cLEAVE THE DIMENSION TAB IN THE DIMENSION BUILDER§r to let it receive power.

You don't want to be in a dimension while it unpowers... it's not a very pleasent thing to put it lightly.

Dimension creation costs are up 20x from base, but the Dimension Builder can accept waaaay more power than default, and generating power shouldn't be an issue with an Extreme Reactor or a Draconic Reactor (or both!).

Craft a Dialing Device! This machine lets you call up the Receiver that's automatically placed in the center of each created RFTools Dimension, and lets your Matter Transmitter know where to go.

Just place it near your Transmitter / Receiver combo, and it'll work wirelessly.

To dial up a Dimension, select your destination from the list below. Press 'Dial' to constantly keep your nearby Transmitter provide a teleportation beam to the selected dimension, or (since this could be dangerous if the dimension unpowers and you accidentally saunter into the teleportation beam) you could press 'Dial Once' to only dial the dimension until you enter the beam. To interrupt the beam, simply press 'Interrupt'.

DIAL UP!

betterquesting:10.name:8: Tell NASA about this before they send people to Mars!

The Destination Analyzer, when placed next to a Dialing Device, lets it check the status of a Receiver. This way you can be sure that a receiver has enough power or is not blocked before attempting to travel to it.

You can also place the Destination Analyzer next to a Transmitter. In that case, the Transmitter will show a red colored teleportation beam if there is something wrong on the receiving end. You can check the actual problem in the dialing device.

Craft a Matter Transmitter! This machine lets you teleport to an RFTools Dimension by calling it from a nearby Dialing Device. You'll need to power both of the machines.

You can name the Transmitter something like 'Home' or 'Base', and this name will show up wherever possible to let you know where to teleport from/to.
Craft a Material Absorber! This block is used to create Material Dimlets. To use it, simply place it down, and place 128 of the desired block next to it. They will quickly be eaten up!
The Advanced Charged Porter holds way more charge than the regular Charged Porter. Less refilling, yay!

betterquesting:10.name:8: I wouldn't give a DIME for this... But I WOULD give a Dime-ond...
betterquesting:10.desc:8: Craft an Infused Diamond! You might want to automate this going forward.

Dimensional Shard Ores spawn in any non-void RFTools Dimension from Y=2 to Y=64. Find some and mine up some!

You'll need a lot of these going forward, so setup a Quarry or Digital Miner in a (preferably pleasant) Dimension of your choice to mine some up.

Craft a Point to Point Dislocator. This is used as a crafting ingredient for the Advanced Dislocator, but it also has its own usage:

You first have to Right Click it to split it into a bound pair. You can use either Dislocator to teleport to the other. This works if the Bound Dislocator is in a Pedestal, portal, in a player's inventory or even on the ground as an item entity.

betterquesting:10.name:8: Make sure to add Adam and Eve, and an apple...
betterquesting:10.desc:8:
The Dimension Enscriber is the machine that lets you choose what your custom RFTools Dimension is going to contain. Simply place an Empty Dimension Tab in the bottom left, and optionally place some Dimlets or other modifiers inside that let you change the aspects of the Dimension.

As your first Dimension I recommend leaving the large screen of slots alone, and simply create a random dimension. So just click on 'Store'.

This Empty Dimension Tab will then need to be placed into a Dimension Builder to create it.

If you want to recycle your Empty Dimension Tab, simply place it back into the Enscriber, then click 'Extract'.

The Phased Field Generator lets you enter unpowered RFTools Dimensions for 500 seconds, to perhaps recover something that you lost. Hopefully you'll never have to use this, but it's important to let you know that this is an option.


























Lucario's favorite move!
Craft an Infused Enderpearl! Automating this is in your best interest.

Are you flooding in materials? But still in need of more Dimlets? Craft some lootboxe... ahem, I mean Dimlet Parcels that could give you the Dimlet of your Dreams! (Or disappointment, you never know...)

The Advanced Dislocator is the most OP teleportation item in the pack. To use it, first have some Enderpearls in your inventory, and open its interface with a Right Click. Then Shift+Left Click the 'Add Fuel' button on the bottom right.

The 'Add New' button will add a teleport location to the list of locations. This will default to where you're standing, but can be changed. Click 'Commit' to add the new location. You can then click 'Rename' to change its name to something other than coordinates.

You can do this as many times as you want, in multiple different locations. From this point on, use Shift+Right Click to open the Advanced Dislocator, as Right Click will teleport you to the selected location.

This all works even cross-dimensionally. No more pesky Portals! We're OP now.

Craft a Bound Dislocator (Player). This is used as a crafting ingredient for the Advanced Dislocator, but it also has its own usage:

Right Clicking this Dislocator will bind it to yourself. Another player or entity can then use that dislocator to teleport to your location as long as you are online.

Craft a Machine Infuser! Any RFTools or RFTools Dimensions machine can be placed inside this to give it a bonus (usually a speed increase) using Dimensional Shards. To read the exact infusion bonus of each machine, simply hold Shift while hovering over it.

Craft an RFTools Receiver and a Charged Porter.

§cBind the Charged Porter to the Receiver by Shift+Right Clicking on it.§r

By this point, you might have other ways to come back from the RFTools Dimension, but it's not a bad idea to emphasize it: You'll need a way back, and this combo allows you to do so.

When you want to return, simply Right Click the Charged Porter and you'll appear on the Receiver you set the Charged Porter to.

When you enter the RFTools Dimension, there will be a Receiver at your feet. If you name the Receiver, that name will show up in the Dialing Device.

You can also name the your own Receiver something like 'Home' or 'Base', and this name will show up wherever possible to let you know where to teleport from/to.

Craft a Liquid Absorber! This block is used to create Liquid Dimlets. To use it, simply place it down, and place 128 of the desired liquid (in source block form) next to it. They will quickly be swallowed up!
You can craft a Dimension Editor to change already created dimensions by inserting various Dimlets. Though be aware that a Dimlet is lost after it's inserted in the Dimension Editor.

Notice that if you create another random dimension by putting in no Dimlets into the Dimension Enscriber's main screen, then the new Dimension Tab will link back to the same dimension.

To avoid this, add Digit Dimlets to the creation screen. A different combination of Digits will always result in different Dimensions! You can craft the Digit (0) Dimlet, and craft the larger Digits from that.

Craft a Liquid Stellar Alloy Dimlet and create a Dimension of Stellar Alloy oceans! Pump it up and make blocks upon blocks of it.

Note that Gaia Spirits can be gotten from the Mob Loot Fabricator Modular Machine.
Craft a Liquid Mystic Dimlet and create a Dimension of Mystic oceans! Pump it up and make blocks upon blocks of it.
Craft a Molten Starmetal Alloy Dimlet and create a Dimension of Molten Starmetal oceans! Pump it up and make boatloads of Starmetal.
Craft a Supremium Block Dimlet or a Molten Supremium Dimlet and create a Dimension of Supermium Blocks or Molten Supremium oceans! Mine or pump it up for blocks upon blocks of it.

Well now that you have a Dread Crystal... you're pretty powerful. You can choose to use it to get into Blood Magic, or to make the most powerful quarry: The Digital Miner!

If you chose the latter, here is how to use it:

In its GU you'll find a config button which lets your specify:

- A radius of up to 32 blocks,
- Which y-levels you want to mine on.
- What to mine (you'll need to add a filter for this).

betterquesting:10.name:8: Capturing the Power of the Sun
betterquesting:10.desc:8: No need to travel to Venus anymore! WE'LL DO IT LIVE!
Discover Europe (-ium) by traveling across the Atlanti-- I mean dissolving some Dimensional Shards!
The elements seem to be moving WILDLY inside the Highly Radioactive Dimension-Splitting Compound! Break it down into its (new) elements!

betterquesting:10.name:8: Where are the other countries though?!
betterquesting:10.desc:8: It's quite an amusing accident that half of the atomic number of Europium is (almost) exactly the atomic number of Germanium...!
Hopefully you found a good source of Molten Stellar Alloy. You'll need a lot!

betterquesting:10.name:8: Don't tell ur ium about this
betterquesting:10.desc:8: Break down some Rutherfordium into Tellurium!
Your greatest feat so far! You managed to find a way to combine Erbium, Gallium, Tellurium, Polyvinyl Chloride & Diammonium Phospate into a stable compound...
Combine Neptunium, Germanium, Butane and Amide and see what it turns into...!

This compound has never before been created...

And...


And, wait...


???

That would make alchemical transmutations way too simple....




...




WHAT

HAVE

I

CREATED?!

Use your Alumite Pickaxe to Ore Excavate a field of Obsidian! You can easily get stacks of Obsidian in a couple minutes with this method.

Use Lava Buckets on Smeltery Drains to insert Lava into your Smeltery! You can insert Water the same way to craete Obsidian inside the Smeltery. Now create Alumite inside the Smeltery by alloying Obsidian with Aluminum and Iron! Then pour out some of the resulting Alumite into a Pickaxe Head Cast! Using this you can create an Alumite Pickaxe capable of mining anything up to Obisdian level!

Note: You can automate the insertion of Lava and Water using Fluiducts, which you have access to right now.
Craft a lot of Grout! You'll need it.
Collect some Sand with Ore Excavator!
Collect some Gravel with Ore Excavator!
Collect some Clay with Ore Excavator!
"Smelt" your Rough Iron Mesh using the Burning Essence you've created! Just drop the two Essences into water and voilà! You got youself an Iron Ingot!
Combine some Coal with Yellow Dye to create an essence which is surprisingly reactive!
Smack your Iron Ore you've gathered with your Rough Hammer to create some Rough Iron Mesh.
Obtain 15 pieces of Cobblestone or any base stone material you find underground! DON'T FORGET ABOUT ORE EXCAVATOR!
That's right! The Crafting Table ain't so easy to create! You first need to make a Wooden Pickaxe Head and a Tool Rod, then combine them!

Upgrade the Tier 1 Drawer upgrades all to way to Tier 4! Lots of storage capacity! :O

[Note: Tiers 2 & 3 have been skipped in the Quest Book, as they should be very easily accessible at this point.]
Use your Obsidian you've just gathered to create some basic Drawer Upgrades! You can use these to upgrade the capacity of your Drawers!
Tool-7? What does that mean? Well, it's not Tool-8, not too late to create cool new Tinkers' Tools! >:D
Craft some Blank Patterns which let you create Tinkers' Parts!
- says the molten metal when it's being poured into a Casting Basin, which you need to craft to complete this quest. You can use this block to pour out entire blocks at once!
Smelt your Grout into Seared Bricks and enter Tinkers' Construct!
Craft a Rough Hammer! This tool is used to create Rough Iron Mesh out of Iron Ore.
(Not very.)

Check out the Spartan Shields mod in JEI, and create one of the basic Diamond-level shields available. You can use these shields to bash enemies while blocking: Just hold right click like you would usually do to block, then press left click for a bashing attack!
Mine up some DIAMONDS!
Mine up some Redstone! It's found on low elevations underground, near lava-level!

Having too many Patterns? Scientists have long been working on a potential solution, and only recently have they found one: For only $9.99 a month and a life-long subscription, an all-new Pattern Chest can be YOURS to own! Just sign here and add your Credit Card number with the 3 digits on the back, and this wonderful new creation is in YOUR hands!
...
Just kidding, it's free (as long as you have the materials for it)...!
Craft a Casting Table to be able to pour out your molten metals into casts! The most important cast is the Ingot Cast, using which you can create (you guessed it) ingots!
Mine some Redstone, using which you can create a Smeltery Controller!
Check out the Iron Backpacks mod and work your way up to a Diamond Backpack! You can store a lot of items in it and bring it with you on your journey!

Use various materials to form Parts using Patterns from the Stencil Table! For example, 3 pieces of Cobblestone with a Pickaxe Head Pattern will create a Stone Pickaxe Head! For Parts made out of metal however, you'll need to use the Smeltery, melt the metal and pour it out into a Cast, e.g. a Pickaxe Head Cast!

betterquesting:10.name:8: It all starts the same way...
betterquesting:10.desc:8: You know what to do: Get wood!
Craft some Seared Drains to pour your liquid out through Seared Faucets! If you wish to route the liquid further, you can use Casting Channels!

[This is an optional quest. You can use any other Fluid Tank available to you a this point, however, the Thermal Expansion Portable Tank is a good option.]

Craft and fill up the Tank with Lava! You'll use it to create obsidian inside the Smeltery!
Use your 2x2 crafting grid to create an undamaged Stone Axe, Stone Pickaxe and 2 Crafting Bases, then combine them to create a Crafting Table!
Craft a Stone Pickaxe Head and use it to craft a Stone Pickaxe!

Craft any kind of Drawer from the Storage Drawers mod! You can store a lot of one specific type of item in it! It's useful if you have a lot of Cobblestone, Dirt, Gravel, etc. piling up in your Chests!
No longer will you need to bring excess wood with you for Sticks to craft Torches! Just put together 2 pieces of Cobblestone to get Stone Rods, and use them to create Stone Torches!
Mine up some Coal! Don't forget about Ore Excavator!

You can store your tools here. Well, partially.

...By that I mean, you can't store your tools here at all, only its parts.

Harvest some Yellow Flowers (Dandelions, Sunflowers, Yellow Botania Flowers, etc.), and turn them into Yellow Dye!

In the case of Botania Flowers, you can craft a Pestle and Mortar in order to do this!
Use your Obsidian you've just gathered to craft a full set of Obsidian Armor! This is slightly weaker than Iron Armor, however, Obsidian is easily available to Ore Excavate at any time!
Create a Totem Whittling Knife to unlock Chapter 2: Dancing on a Totem Pole!
Your Smeltery requires one Seared Tank constantly fueled with Lava to keep it running. Later on you'll be able to use Liquid Pyrotheum to speed up the entire multiblock by a lot!
Obtain some Tier 5 Storage Upgrades! Villager trading is disabled, but to compensate for that, Emerald Ore generation has been added to each biome (and it's slightly more common in Extreme Hills).

Use your Iron you've obtained to create 2 Iron Rods, Then mine up a lot of Cobblestone with Ore Excavator to compress them into Compressed Cobblestone! If you can't find regular Cobblestone, note that you can craft 4 pieces of any Underground Biomes Cobblestone type into 4 pieces of Cobblestone by forming a square shape in the Crafting Window. Using these materials you can finally create a Furnace!
Check out the Iron Chests mod in JEI, and work your way up to creating a Diamond Chest, which has a lot more storage space than a regular Chest!
Mine up some Copper from underground! It's found on higher elevations, sometimes even on exposed Stone on the surface! Then smelt it or ore-double it in the Smeltery!
Make a Stencil Table! You can use it to transform your Blank Patterns into various Patterns for Tools! This is where all Tool Creation in Tinkers' Construct starts.

Craft a bunch of OpenBlocks Tanks and an XP Drain! You can store your Experience by standing on the XP Drain with a Tank below. Tanks also connect to each other nicely. To regain your XP, simply right click any of the connected Tanks!

[Pro Tip: If you craft 4 XP Drains, place them down in a 2x2 square on top of some Tanks, you can drain you XP much faster than you would with only 1 Drain!]
FIIIREEEE!!!
Use your Coke Oven to create Coal Coke, then feed it and Iron Ingots into your Blast Furnace, to create a couple pieces of Steel Ingots!

Craft the required components for the Diesel Generator! This is a great source of energy when Biodiesel is fully automated. You can easily run a medium sized ME System with a couple Biodiesel Generators.

Check your Engineer's Manual -> Powers, Wires, Generators -> Diesel Generator to see how to create the multiblock. To form it, click on the central Generator Block.

To provide it with fuel, place a Biodiesel Tank or Fluid Pipes pushing into the front corner. Then connect some Wires to one of the 3 connectors on the top. This will distribute 4096 IF/tick between all connectors. Once you've routed the power, you'll notice that THE MACHINE IS INCREDIBLY LOUD AND OH MY GOSH I CAN'T HEAR MY FOOTSTEPS AND IT'S NOT EVEN POSSIBLE TO MUFFLE IT WITH EXTRA UTILITIES SOUND MUFFLERS, AND I WISH I HAD BUILT IT FARTHER AWAY FROM MY BASE, TIME TO TEAR IT DOWN.

§cWARNING: Do NOT build this on a chunk border. Press F9 twice to show them. If built on a chunk border, eventually the machine could get corrupted and crash your world.

Obtain your first Bucket of Biodiesel by combining Ethanol and Plant Oil in the Refinery!

I highly recommend you to immediately start working on automating the entire Biodiesel generating process, as it's not only a great source of early-to-mid-game energy, but it's also heavily required for the upcoming Tech Mods!
Use your Squeezer to craft some HOP Graphite Dust using Coke Dust!

Craft a Charging Station! Apply power to it from either the bottom or the back side. You can Right Click chargeable items into the Charging Station to fill them with energy! Right Click again to remove.

Craft an LV Wire Coil and 2 LV Wire Connectors. By attaching the Wire Connectors to Machines, Generators, or Capacitors, and connecting them with a Wire, you'll be able to transfer power between them!

LV Wires can stretch out up to 16 blocks apart, and cannot be obstructed by any blocks. The LV Wire can only transfer 2048 RF/tick. So if you have multiple machines, you might need to upgrade it to MV or HV. If you don't want to replace your entire system of wires, you can craft Transformers to change between LV and MV, or MV and HV.
Create your first Bucket of Plant Oil by Squeezing some Seeds! This is one half of the ingredients of Biodiesel.

Craft the required components for a Squeezer! Check your Engineer's Manual -> Heavy Machinery -> Squeezer on how it's formed. Then click on the central Barrel from the side to complete the multiblock!

Power's supplied from the top through the orange dot. Input items from the back through the blue dots (use Hoppers or push item with Item Ducts and Servos), and output Fluids on the lower front, Items on the upper front.

§cWARNING: Do NOT build this on a chunk border. Press F9 twice to show them. If built on a chunk border, eventually the machine could get corrupted and crash your world.

Craft a Kinetic Dynamo. By attaching Water Wheels or Windmills to it you can generate some IF Power! (which converts to RF with a 1 to 1 scale). You can attach up to 3 Water Wheels to a side, but only 1 Windmill.

Like the Engineer's Workbench! So craft the required components for one (though you might want to craft more, for different Blueprints and outputs), and check your Engineer's Manual -> Simple Machines -> Automated Workbench on how to create the multiblock. To form it, click on the slab closer to the center from the side. Now you can input a Blueprint, and select the item you wish to craft. Item input is on the back (where the conveyors are running from, you'll need to use a Hopper or push items into it), output is on the front (where the conveyors are running to).

§cWARNING: Do NOT build this on a chunk border. Press F9 twice to show them. If built on a chunk border, eventually the machine could get corrupted and crash your world.

Craft an HV Wire Coil, 2 HV Wire Connectors, and an HV Wire Relay. They can transport up to 32,768 IF/tick and stretch out up to 32 blocks. However, there is a key difference between HV Wire Connectors and lower tiers. They can only be used as inputs and outputs, but not throughputs. If you want to stretch out your cables further and need to use throughputs, use an HV Wire Relay.

Craft the required materials for a Metal Press. Then check your Engineer's Manual on Heavy Machinery -> Metal Press to find out how to construct it. Once you've placed down the blocks, right click on the central Piston to form the Multiblock! You can also rotate the Piston with your Engineer's Hammer to make it face down.

Once formed, Right Click on the face of the Press with a Mold! Provide Power from the top using a Wire Connector, provide inputs from a Chest or Conveyor Belt on the front, and obtain outputs from the back!

Plates, Rods and Wires crafted through the Metal Press are half as expensive as crafting them in the Crafting Table.

§cWARNING: Do NOT build this on a chunk border. Press F9 twice to show them. If built on a chunk border, eventually the machine could get corrupted and crash your world.
Use the Engineer's Workbench with the Crafting Components Blueprint to create some Iron & Steel Mechanical Components!
Use your Industrial Slimeballs to craft a pair of Slime Boots and a Slimesling!
Use your Arc Furnace to craft some Industrial Slime Balls!
Craft a set of Energized Certus Quartz Crystals to unlock Applied Energistics 2!

betterquesting:10.name:8: Is this how wine is made?
betterquesting:10.desc:8:
Craft the required components for a Fermenter! Check your Engineer's Manual on how the multiblock is formed at Heavy Machinery -> Fermenter.

To form the multiblock, click on the central Cauldron from the side. Once formed, Item Input will be on the back or side (blue dots, use Hoppers or push items with Itemducts and Servos) and Fluid output will be on the lower front (orange dot). Of course you'll need to provide power for the machine through the orange dot on the back (facing up).

§cWARNING: Do NOT build this on a chunk border. Press F9 twice to show them. If built on a chunk border, eventually the machine could get corrupted and crash your world.
Crush some Coal Coke into Coke Dust with your Crusher!

betterquesting:10.name:8: Did you treat your wood well?
betterquesting:10.desc:8: Use Creosote Oil and Planks to obtain Treated Wood! Later you'll be able to use a Fluid Transposer to automate the process.

Craft 27 Coke Bricks! JEI shows some Coke Bricks from Chisel, so make sure to craft the right one: the one from Immersive Engineering.

Then set them up in a 3x3x3 cube! Finally, right click on one of the faces with your Engineer's Hammer to create a Coke Oven!

Insert some Coal in the left slot and some kind of liquid storage in the top right slot (Buckets, various Tanks, etc.)! The Oven will automatically transform the Coal into Coal Coke, and fill the Bucket/Tank with Creosote Oil.

Make sure to keep emptying the Creosote, otherwise the Oven will stop functioning.

It's also possible (and recommended) to automate extraction and insertion of Coal, Coal Coke, and Creosote Oil using Hoppers and Pipes. Feed Coal from the top, remove Coal Coke from the bottom, and pipe out Creosote Oil from one of the sides (in this case, Buckets/Tanks aren't even needed).

§cWARNING: Do NOT build this on a chunk border. Press F9 twice to show them. If built on a chunk border, eventually the machine could get corrupted and crash your world.
Craft 3 Radiator Blocks! It's used as Machine Components and it's quite a pretty building block with connected textures. I'd rate at least 9/10.
Craft an Engineer's Wire Cutter! This is a handy tool that allows you to disconnect wires without having to break the Connectors. You have no idea how much time you can save with it!
Use your Fermenter to create your first Bucket of Ethanol! This is one half of the ingredients of Biodiesel.

Craft 27 Blast Bricks! Then set them up in a 3x3x3 cube and Right Click on one of the faces with your Engineer's Hammer!

This machine creates Steel and Slag when provided with Iron Ingots and Coal Coke.

Unlike the Coke Oven however, it's not possible to automate it. You'll need to craft an Improved Blast Furnace, Arc Furnace or progress far enough until your reach Thermal Expansion if you want to automate Steel production.

§cWARNING: Do NOT build this on a chunk border. Press F9 twice to show them. If built on a chunk border, eventually the machine could get corrupted and crash your world.
Craft an HV Capacitor. It can hold 4,000,000 IF.

Craft a Thermoelectric Generator! This is a compact machine that generates power when hot and cold liquids or solids are on opposite ends of it. For now the best type of fluids you can provide are Lava and Water, or alternatively you can replace the Water with Ice or Packed Ice. Later you can use Pyrotheum and Cryotheum for even more power. And while you're at it, why not use all 4 sides of the generator for twice as much power generation!
Craft an MV Capacitor! It can hold 1,000,000 IF.

Craft the required components for a Refinery! Check your Engineer's Manual to setup the multiblock. To form it, click on the central Heavy Engineering Block on one of the longer sides with your Engineer's Hammer.

Power input is on the top, and 2 Fluid inputs are on either side. Make sure to push Fluids into the machine. Fluid output is on the center of the longer side.

§cWARNING: Do NOT build this on a chunk border. Press F9 twice to show them. If built on a chunk border, eventually the machine could get corrupted and crash your world.

Craft 2 Blast Furnace Preheaters! Place them on both sides on your Improved Blast Furnace (make sure they connect, place them while facing the Blast Furnace)! When the Preheaters are provided with power (from the top), they will improve the production speed on the Improved Blast Furnace.

Craft the components for an Improved Blast Furnace! Set up the Reinforced Blast Bricks in a 3x3x3 cube, then place a Hopper on the top center. Right click on the central block on the side with your Engineer's Hammer to form the multiblock!

You can automatically import Iron Ingots, Coal Coke through yet another Hopper (or Item Conduit, Transfer Node, etc.) on the top, and export Steel and Slag by placing a Chest on the front and back, respectively.

§cWARNING: Do NOT build this on a chunk border. Press F9 twice to show them. If built on a chunk border, eventually the machine could get corrupted and crash your world.
Craft a Blueprint for Metal Press Molds! JEI shows all Blueprint recipes, even if you only lookup one, so check which one you need.
Craft a Blueprint for Crafting Components! It's like we're in a game of Mine...CRAFT, because you have to do these two things all the time...

Craft an Engineer's Workbench! Use a Blueprint and crafting materials to create various items! Later you'll be able to create an Automated Engineer's Workbench (topmost quest on the next page) to automate the crafting of items created on the Workbench.
Use your Arc Furnace to craft some Industrial Leather!

Craft the required components for an Arc Furnace! Check your Engineer's Manual -> Heavy Machinery -> Arc Furnace on how to construct it. Once formed, click on the central Cauldron to create the multiblock!

Provide power to one of the 3 black squares on the back. Inputs are on the top. When facing the front of the machine, the left slot inputs the main items, and the right slot inputs the additional items. Output is on the front bottom, where the Cauldron used to be during construction pull items out of there. The Arc Furnace can be used to smelt, alloy, or create Steel, so additional outputs (a.k.a Slag) can and should be removed, and are automatically pushed out on the pack, below the power input.

§cWARNING: Do NOT build this on a chunk border. Press F9 twice to show them. If built on a chunk border, eventually the machine could get corrupted and crash your world.
Craft the 3 most essential Molds! Using a Metal press with these Molds, you can gain more output from your materials.

Now that you have made some Steel, craft a Drawer Controller! By attaching this to your Drawer Line you'll be able to access all of the Drawers at once! No longer will you have to search for specific spots to put your items into, you can simply Right Click your Drawer Controller with an item, and if you have room for it in your attached Drawers, it will get placed inside one.

You can also attach any kind of item translocator, like Hoppers, Pipes, Transfer Nodes, etc. to the Drawer Controller to send items into your Drawer Storage. Later I recommend you to attach an AE2 Storage Bus to your Drawer Controller. That way, your ME System can see your entire Drawer Network, and have access to items inside.

Craft a Current Transformer! Break up your wiring into 2 pieces by connecting it to a generator (like a Kinetic Dynamo) on one side, and a Machine or Capacitor on the other side. You don't need to use Wire Connectors for the Current Transformer. This will let you know how much power is flowing through the cable, or how much power you're generating.

Trying to generate some power, that's what! Craft a Water Wheel, and attach it to a Kinetic Dynamo to generate IF power! Make sure to have at least 2 blocks cleared in each direction to be able to place down the Water Wheel. By placing a Water source block up at the top, and letting it flow down on the sides and on the bottom, the Wheel will start spinning, and generating power.

§cWARNING: Do NOT build this on a chunk border. Press F9 twice to show them. If built on a chunk border, eventually the machine could get corrupted and crash your world.

Craft an Engineer's Blueprint for Arc Furnace Electrodes! Then craft 3 Graphite Electrodes in your Engineer's Workbench! This is a required ingredient in all Arc Furnace recipes. Don't worry though, these Electrodes have durability and do last a while.

Craft the required components of a Crusher! Check your Engineer's Manual -> Heavy Machinery -> Crusher to see how to build the multiblock. Once built, click on one of the central Fence blocks on a longer side with your Engineer's Hammer to form the multiblock.

The Crusher doesn't have an interface. Instead, when provided with power (through the orange dot on the center back) and throwing materials inside, it will try to crush it into dust form granted there exists a crushed form of the given item. It will gladly eat up items that don't, so be careful what you throw in it. To output items, simply place a Chest next to the black dot on the side.

§cWARNING: Do NOT build this on a chunk border. Press F9 twice to show them. If built on a chunk border, eventually the machine could get corrupted and crash your world.

Do you wobble when you go?
Do it shine in the light?
Is it leather, is it wool?
Could you throw it over ya shoulder
If ya fly it make ya go
Do your Hangs glide low?

Craft an Engineer's Hammer to get into Immersive Engineering!

Note: Chapters 3 and 4 (Roots and Immersive Engineering) are meant to be completed side by side.

Craft a batch of Baykok's Bloodied Stones! To obtain Coagulated Blood, smelt Rotten Flesh in your Smeltery, or alternatively stand in it: But watch out, this method might be painful...

Note: Crafting with Baykok's Bow will only use up 1 durability.

Craft a Mining Drill and combine it with a Steel Drill Head in the Engineer's Workbench. Then fill it up with Biodiesel directly from the Refinery or an EnderIO Tank. When charged with fuel, it mines blocks very quickly in a 3x3 area. The chosen upgrade can be applied in the Engineer's Workbench. Note: The other upgrades are also craftable.
Craft some Insulating Glass! Make sure to use Lime Green Glass specifically.
Craft an MV Wire Coil and 2 MV Wire Connectors. This type of Wire can transport 8192 IF/tick and can stretch out up to 16 blocks.
Punch some tall grass to obtain some Industrial Hemp Seeds! Then plant them to get some Industrial Hemp Fiber! I recommend using Roots Elemental Soils.

Craft an External Heater! Place some Furnaces next to it, and provide it with power through the orange dot! Now adjacent Furnaces will use the IF power you're generating instead of fuel to smelt.

If you have access to Cincinnasite from the Nether, you can also craft a Cincinnasite Forge for double Furnace speed!

Craft one of more Core Sample Drills. When provided with power and Right Clicked, it will dig up a sample from the ground. The sample may contains some Veins. If it does, the given chunk is suitable for mining with the Excavator. The machine won't actually mine up the terrain, just generate some of that Ore as output. The likelihood of finding a Vein has been increased, hopefully you'll have no trouble finding them close enough to your Power generation.

Craft an LV Capacitor! This block can store 100,000 IF (or RF). Each side can be configured to accept power, or output power. Click on a side once to turn it into a side that accepts power (blue dots), or twice to turn it into a side that outputs power (orange dots). Despite its name, it can accept power through MV and HV Wires and Wire Connectors too.

Craft a Revolver, 8 pieces of basic ammo, and a Revolver Speedloader! Then check out different types of Cartridges you could use in JEI! To use the Revolver, Shift+Right Click on it to fill it up with ammo. Then simply Right Click to shoot. Now, you don't wanna run out of ammo during a fight, do you? That's what the Speedloader is for! Once you've ran out of ammo, it'll quickly fill up the Revolver with its contents, so you can pew-pew while your heart desires (and while you have ammo). To apply the chosen upgrade, use the Engineer's Workbench. Note: The other upgrades are also craftable.

Craft a Chemical Thrower! The chosen upgrade can be applied in the Engineer's Workbench. To actually use the Chemical Thrower, fill it up with any fluid. You can use an EnderIO Tank for this, or simply Right Click on any kind of Tank. The Chemical Thrower will then spray out the fluid on Right Click. Well what's the point of this - you'd ask. Well, try Shift+Right Clicking to turn it into FLAMETHROWER MODE (granted the Fluid you filled it with is flammable). It's an extremely wasteful weapon, but can absolutely destroy some enemies.
Craft a set of Energized Osmium Ingots to unlock Mekanism!

Craft an EnderIO Fluid Tank and some Immersive Engineering Fluid Pipes to store and move Fluids.

You can set each side of the Fluid Tank to push or pull Fluids.

Perform the Totentanz Ritual to summon Baykok. Before you do though, make some preparations:

1. Baykok shoots arrows constantly, so equip some armor that can handle it. It's also recommended to use a ranged weapon if you want to fight it head to head.

2. You can setup some kind of a hidey hole where you get can into, but Baykok can't. Baykok can't activate buttons, trapdoors, or break blocks.

Once you have defeated Baykok, he will drop his Bow. You can use this bow with regular arrows, or use it for upcoming crafting recipes. Both of these actions will require 1 durability per shot or craft.

Craft the required components for an Excavator and a Bucket Wheel! Check the Engineer's Manual -> Heavy Machinery -> Excavator to see how to set both of them up. Before you do so though, make sure to set it up in the right area. Craft a Core Sample Drill (see the quest besides this one). Once you found a suitable location, power it from the side (one of 3 black dots), and place an output chest (or preferably Item Ducts connected to 2-3 Drawers) as an output. Be aware, that this machine uses 4096 RF/tick, so you need good power generation to keep it going. (1 Diesel generator can keep it up exactly.)

§cWARNING: Do NOT build this on a chunk border. Press F9 twice to show them. If built on a chunk border, eventually the machine could get corrupted and crash your world.

Craft a Railgun! The rewarded upgrades can be applied in the Engineer's Workbench. To use it, power it up in your Charging Station! Then keep some projectiles in your inventory. These include: Iron Rods, Steel Rods, and Graphite Electrodes. To use it, hold Right Click while the meter in the bottom right reaches 99, the release Right Click to FIRE!
Craft an Artificial Scarab Body! .... But what for...?
Obtain some Barrel Cacti and one stem of Nether Cactus! They are spread out through the whole Nether, but are more common on Gravel fields! It shouldn't be difficult to find 'em!

betterquesting:10.name:8: Going down low, low, low, low, low, low, low, low
betterquesting:10.desc:8:
Create a portal to the Nether and enter it! When you enter the first time, the loading time might take a while, because custom Better Nether terrain is being generated. Once you enter, make sure to create a waypoint with Journey Map so you can find your way back!




Player had them Iron Leggin's on (on),
Boots with the Plate (with the Plate),
The whole world is lookin' at sir!
They hit the floor (they hit the floor),
Next thing you know,
Player went low, low, low, low, low, low, low, low!

Obtain the 3 different kinds of Better Nether Mushrooms!

- Lucis Spores are commonly found near Egg Plant fields, they're large 6-block yellow mushrooms on the side of Nether walls.

- Orange Mushrooms confuse you with their name, because they're actually purple, large 1-block models.

- Bone Mushroom Spores can be found growing from Bone Blocks usually near Soul Sand fields.
Slay the Wither and obtain its precious Nether Star!
Find a Nether Fortress and slay some Wither Skeletons for their Bones and Skulls! Make a Tinkers' Cleaver if you're having trouble obtaining Skulls! The Cleaver has built-in Beaheading functionality.
Craft a Blank Magic Map and use it in the Twilight Fores to reveal boss locations!
Once you've entered the Twilight Forest, collect some Torchberries from underground and slay some Ravens for their Feather!

Enter the Dark Tower found in the middle of the Dark Forest! Climb to the top to find the Ur-ghast! This boss won't take damage from meelee hits, so you must damage it with ranged weapons. Once defeated, obtain its Trophy and some Carminite!

Enter the Dark Forest and find the entrance to the Goblin Knight Stronghold! Before you can enter however, you'll need to place at least 1 Trophy you've collected on a Trophy Pedestal near the entrance. Once inside, fight some Knights, Goblins or Helmet Crabs to obtain some Armor Shards! Then find the central room with the four Knight Phantoms inside! Defeat them to be able to move on!

Note: There is no sure drop the Knight Phantoms give, so the quest only asks for Armor Shards.
Enter the snowy biome and find the Alpha Yeti Cave! Defeat the Yeti packs and the boss to obtain some Alpha Yeti Fur!
Once you've completed Roots, Immersive Engineering and the Twilight Forest, you can craft a Flawless Scarab Body and a pair of Flawless Scarab Wings! ...But what for?

Climb down from the Giant Cloud and enter the caves below the Highlands biome! Find the Giant Obsidian structure and break it with your Giant's Pickaxe to find the Lamp of Cinders inside a Chest!

GG, you have completed the Twilight Forest!



Or have you skipped it...? Either way, I hope you had fun and made the right decision!
Find one of the rare Scorchers that can spawn in the Nether! Slay it for its Purple Blaze!
Find a platform of Nether Reed and obtain some! It can be used as a replacement for Sugar Cane in the Paper and Sugar recipe, and Nether Reed Blocks can be used as a replacement for Wood Logs.

betterquesting:10.name:8: Then everything changed when the fire nation attacked...
betterquesting:10.desc:8: Find a Stronghold or an Underground Blaze Dungeon to obtain some Blaze Rods!
Find the 2 types of DivineRPG Nether Ores and mine up some of them!
Find some cute orange Imps roaming around in the Nether! Then mercilessly slaughter them for their hide! D:

During the creation of the pack, a vote was held on the Divine Journey 2 Discord server about the inclusion of Twilight Forest into the main progression line. The result was: Implement an item that lets you skip the Twilight Forest, since many of us players have already completed it, and there is nothing new to see.

If you wish to skip the Twilight Forest, craft a Twilight Key. This will allow you to craft the Lamp of Cinders, which would otherwise be the final item obtained in the Forest, and allow you to progress further into the pack.

However, if you haven't played through Twilight Forest yet, I highly encourage you to try it out, since it's most likely the single best exploration mod in Minecraft - especially if OP flight methods aren't available. The best way to travel through Twilight in this pack is with the Roots Sky Soarer spell, as well as Tinkers' Slime Boots and Slimestring.

Due to Twilight's popularity though, it's incredibly overused: it's included in a large portion of packs, which is understandably why people get bored of it.

So if you wish to follow this route, you don't have to enter the Twilight Forest to go on.

Craft a Twilight Rock! It is used to enter the Twilight Forest. Surround a 2x2 pool of Water with Dirt or Grass blocks, and place any kind of Flowers all the way around (even on the corners). Then throw in the Twilight Rock to create a Twilight Forest Portal!

This quest will unlock once you've completed the Stalicripe quest in Chapter 3 and the HOP Graphite Dust quest in Chapter 4.
