Summon and defeat the King of Scorchers in the Nether! It's recommended to fight it in an enclosed area so it can't fly away and shoot your down with fireballs. Once defeated, obtain its Statue and Fury Fire!
Craft an Infernal Flame! This item can be used to summon the King of Scorchers in the Nether.

Now that you have defeated the Lich, entering the Twilight Swamp won't cause bad Hunger effect on the player. So go there, and find the entrance of the Minoshroom Labyrinth! Get to the end to fight Minoshroom himself! He won't give you a warm welcome though... Slay it to obtain the Meef Stroganoff!

Now that you have defeated the Naga, the barrier around the Lich's Tower will disappear. Enter the Tower, climb to the top, and fight the Twilight Lich!

If you're having trouble with the fight, know that you have to knock back its projectiles to break its shields. Once all of its shields are broken, you can start to damage it!

Once you've defeated the Minoshroom, keep heading deeper inside the Swamp, all the way to the Fire Swamp! Right in the dead center you'll find the Hydra. Defeat all of its heads to obtain its Trophy, Hydra Chops and some Fiery Blood!

Use some Cincinncasite, Steel, Constantan and Lava to create a Forged Cincinnasite Block! You can obtain Constantan by mixing Copper and Nickel in the Smeltery or Crushing them with the Immersive Engineering Crusher, then combining the Dusts.
Mine up some Cincinnasite Ore from the Nether! It can be affected by Fortune.

Once the Hydra, Ur-Ghast and Snow Queen have been defeated, you will no longer take damage from Acid Rain in the Highlands biome! So enter it and find the Giant Cloud floating above the biome! Climb up to fight Giant You and obtain the Giant's Pickaxe!
Enter the Glacier biome! In the middle, you'll find the Aurora Palace. Climb up to the top to fight the Snow Queen and obtain its Trophy!

Mine up some Egg Plants! Watch out if you're in a field of them - they will poison you when you set foot on them, because they have

VENOMMMM, got that poisonous VENOMMMM,
And I'm not knowin' when I'mmmm
Ever gonna step in themmmm
Ready to step any moment and I'mmm
Thinkin' it's time to go get 'em
They ain't gonna know what him 'em
W-W-When they get collected -

VENOMMMM, got that poisonous VENOMMMM,
And I'm not knowin' when I'mmmm
Ever gonna step in themmmm
Ready to step any moment and I'mmm
Thinkin' it's time to go get 'em
They ain't gonna know what him 'em
W-W-When they get collected.

Find the Naga Fortress and defeat the Naga to obtain its Trophy and some of its Scales! To defeat it, keep hitting it while its tail keeps getting shorter, all the way until it's basically only a head!
Use your Brewing Stand to create some Extended Water Breathing Potions! You will need to fish up a Pufferfish for this.
Craft a Brewing Stand!

Find an Underwater Monument and raid it using your Water Breathing Potions to obtain some Prismarine Shards and Prismarine Crystals! Later you'll be able to craft them from Quartz with an Atomic Reconstructor and some kind of a Crusher.
Find some ominous-looking Black Apple plants in the Nether! They commonly spawn in Egg Plant fields. Break them for a couple Black Apples!
Break some Eyeballs hanging from the Nether ceiling to obtain some Eye Seeds!
Use your Nether Star to craft a Magical Snow Globe! Then enter at least 7 of the biome types listed to activate it!

Craft a Cincinnasite Forge! This machine functions like a vanilla Furnace, except smelts twice as fast. It can also be used in combination with the External Heater from Immersive Engineering to have it use power instead of fuel to smelt!
Craft a Golden Fury! It's a weapon with infinite durability that uses Gold Nuggets to rapidfire. If you're out of Gold Nuggets in the Nether, know that Cincinnasite can be crafted into them.

betterquesting:10.name:8: Don't get caught in the spikes
betterquesting:10.desc:8: Use some Shears to obtain some Thornvines! If you wanna get a lot, make sure to break them from the bottom, since blocks that pop off and are not broken by Shears will just disappear.

Find an Altar built out of Cincinnasite and Bone Blocks! It will contain a Respawner Statue! Mine it up to complete this quest! You can offer it Glowstone Dust to set a spawn point, even in the Nether or End!
Craft some Stalicripe, then plant it onto Terran Soil to get more! This is the only Soil it can be planted on.
Obtain some Stalagnate commonly found near Thornvines! Simply chop them with an Axe, you can't obtain the leafy version, but you can obtain Stagnuite Seeds to regrow the plant.

betterquesting:10.name:8: Feels no pain in Forest Fires
betterquesting:10.desc:8: Obtain some Magma Flower Seeds commonly found near Lava Lakes and on Magma Blocks! It's one of the most difficult Flowers to find in the Nether, but don't give up!
Use some Shears to obtain some Agave plants scattered around in the Nether.
Upgrade your Energy Cube even further into the Elite variant!
Craft an Advanced Energy Cube! You can craft Energetic Alloy in the Arc Furnace or alloy it in the Smeltery.
Craft some Reinforced Alloy! This component is used in higher tier machines.

Craft an Energy Acceptor! Your ME System needs power through this machine. Use Glass, Covered or Smart cables to route the energy from the Acceptor to your Controller, or simply place it next to the Controller.

Okay, now what could possibly require more energy than this!?

*Insert another warning about FPS issues.*
Still need more energy transfer? Well, craft some Elite Universal Cables, they might do the job! But again, use them sparingly because of FPS issues.

Craft a Charger! Use it to create some Charged Certus Quartz Crystals! Make sure to automate it as soon as possible with 2 Itemducts on the side: one pushing regular Certus into the Charger, one pulling Charged Certus out! Make sure to setup a filter for Charged Certus Quartz. The Charger can accept both regular power and transformed power through Glass Cables placed after an Energy Acceptor. However it'll most likely work faster with regular power.
Make some Enriched Alloy in your Metallurgic Infuser!

Craft a Metallurgic Infuser! This is the main machine you'll use to create all the various Mekanism components. Like for all Mekanism machines, you can simply connect an Immersive Engineering Wire Coil to it by placing a Wire Connector on any side. Once it's powered, place the main material in the second slot from the left, and the infusing material in the first slot from the left. Note that the machine can only hold and use one type of infusing material at once, meaning you're most likely better off creating multiple Metallurgic Infusers for maximum efficiency. To automate the machine, click on the Side Config button on the left. You can select which side you want items, infusion materials and energy to be input on, and which side you want to use as output. Make sure to push and pull items in/out with a Hopper or an Itemduct with an active Servo on it. And one more thing: All Mekanism machines can be picked up and moved by a Crescent Hammer from Thermal Expansion, so you don't need to worry about energy loss.
Craft a Steel Casing! It's used as a basis of all Mekanism machines.

Craft some Servos! Attach them onto an Itemduct to have it automatically pull items out of a container. Right Click on the Servo to turn Redstone Control to Ignored mode and have them always run! You can also craft Hardened Servos at this stage, which pull slightly faster.

Craft some Itemducts from Thermal Expansion! To use them, place one next to a container or machine, and apply a Servo if you want to pull items out of it. Servos can be Right Clicked on to change them to Always On mode.

Craft the Eye of Gaea...!



...Just don't let it SEE you..... D:
...the Atomic Alloy! Such impecable purity! Such magnificent beauty! It's the highest tier Alloy from Mekanism.
Craft a Mekanism Crusher! It works alongside the Enrichment Chamber, but instead of grinding Ores, it can grind down Ingots into their Dust form.

Craft an Enrichment Chamber! You can power it and automate it just like the Metallurgic Infuser. This machine doubles ores, just like the Tinkers' Smeltery. However it's much simpler to automate, as it only takes up 1 block of space. Once you ground up your Ores, simply transfer them into an Energized Smelter to turn them into Ingots! And voilà, ore doubling!

Craft a Basic Energy Cube! This is the Mekanism way to store energy for later use. You can configure its sides to select where the energy should be inputted or outputted. You can also charge items by placing it into the slot marked with a Plus, and remove charge from an item by placing it into the slot marked with a Minus (granted there is space in the Energy Cube). You can move this machine and all other Mekanism machines with a Crescent Hammer (Shift+Right Click). But by breaking it, it will still retain its energy.
Craft an ME Drive! This is where you can store all your Storage Cells with items inside.
Combine your previously created Printed Circuits in the Inscriber to create some Processors! It's recommended to craft and automate multiple Inscribers, as you'll need many Processors from now on.
Throw some Charged Certus Quartz Crystals, Redstone, and regular Quartz into a puddle of water and watch as they all transform into Fluix Crystals!
It needs power... a lot of power... to awaken...
Craft 4 Basic Control Circuits! These are heavily used in the creation of more machines.
If your machines consume a lot of energy, it might be worth upgrading them with Energy Upgrades! Each machien can accept 8 of them. Use the top right icon on the UI of any machine to apply them!
Use your Osmium Compressor to create some Infused Obsidian and Infused Glowstone Ingots! Then combine them in the Arc Furnace or the Smeltery to create some Osgloglas Ingots!

betterquesting:10.name:8: The Heart of your ME System
betterquesting:10.desc:8: Craft an ME Controller and power it through the Energy Acceptor! Each side can provide 32 channels that your AE2 machines can use. If you're running low on channels, try extending the Controller! It can only take the shape of a rectangular frame, so no four Controllers can touch eachother in a 2x2 shape!

Find the additional five custom Presses inside of Sky Stone Chests in the middle of Meteorites! It's not too important to find all of them right now, since you'll only need them once you revisit AE2 with Autocrafting, Autoprocessing, Fluid/Gas Storage, higher tier Storage Cells, Wireless Terminals and Spatial Storage. These are what custom Presses and Processors are used for.

Craft a Meteorite Compass and use it in Atum! That's right, AE2 Meteorites don't generate in the overwold, they only generate inside Atum! This compass will point you to the nearest chunk with a Meteorite inside. It will start spinning as soon as you've entered such a chunk. Make sure the Meteorite isn't on a Chunk border, or if it is, start digging in the correct spot! Meteorites have a Sky Stone Chest in the middle which holds all the Presses you'll need.

Craft a Storage Bus and connect it to your Drawer Controller to have access to all those items in your ME Network! You can also connect it to various Chests and other storage devices for the same functionality. Also make sure to Right Click on it and set its priority higher than your ME Drive's, because otherwise all your items will get sent back to your Drive, not your Drawers.
Craft an Export Bus! Use it to send items to different locations from your ME System!
Craft an Import Bus! Use it to send items from an outside source into your ME System!
Use your Inscriber to create some Logic, Engineering and Silicon Presses!
Find the original four Applied Energistics Presses located inside Sky Stone Chests in the middle of Meteorites! These are the Presses you'll need first.

Craft an Inscriber! Use AE2 Presses found in Atum and basic materials to create Printed Circuits and Processors! To automate it, push items into the machine from different sides. The top side will accept items that go in the top slot, the side will accept the central items, and guess what the bottom does. And pull out items from the other side. The Inscriber takes regular power, but can also work using the power from an Energy Acceptor through Glass Cables.

A Dense Cable only has a 32-channel capacity, but if you want to route more channels to a faraway location, you can use a P2P tunnel. With this, you can transform your Smart or Dense Cable to route 32 channels per cable-channel, then on the other end use another P2P tunnel to turn it back into regular functionality. To connect the two P2P tunnels at each end, use a Memory Card.

This will save you many Dense Cables. Instead of having to run 16 Dense Cables at once, you can run just 1, and have 16-16 P2P Tunnels at each end, with pairs joined by Memory Cards.
Wanna go further? Craft a 1024k Storage Component!
Once you have access to higher tier materials from other Chapters, come back to craft a 256k Storage Component!
Craft some Acceleration Cards! This can speed up your Import/Export Buses, or the crafting speed of your Inscribers.

Craft 5 Crystal Growth Accelerators and place them around a block of Water! Provide energy to them through Glass Cables and throw Certus Quartz Seeds inside. Watch as they turn into Pure Certus Quartz Crystals! Note that this machine requires a lot of power. It's recommended that you break up your line of Glass Cables with a Toggle Bus, place a Lever next to it, and only turn it on when you need the Crystal Growth Accelerators to be active.
If your Basic Universal Cables can't transfer enough energy, craft some Advanced ones! However, use these ones sparingly as well, since they cause FPS lag too due to inefficient rendering.
Craft two Formation and Annihilation Cores! They are used as Crafting Components for AE2.
Craft an ME Terminal and connect it to your Network through a Glass or Smart Cable! You can view your items stored in the Network, search for specific items and sort them in numerous ways.
Craft a 64k Storage Cell. This is the final Storage Cell available before getting into Thermal Expansion.
Craft an Ultimate Energy Cube! For now, this will be your best way of storing energy! ...But wait until you get into EnderIO or Draconic.
Not being able to route your Liquids fast enough? Craft some Advanced Mechanical Pipes, maybe they'll do the job!
Craft some Basic Mechanical Pipes to be able to move Fluids around easily!

Craft the required materials for a 3x3x3 Dynamic Tank multiblock! The frame has to be made out of Dynamic Tank blocks, and the faces out of Structural Glass. Finally, place a Dynamic Valve on one of the sides (while leaving the middle empty). Note that you can make a larger tank all the way up to an 18x18x18 if you need to store a lot of Liquid. Use a Mechanical Pipe to push or pull the Liquid in/out. Each block (including the frame) can hold 64 Buckets, so a 3x3x3 Tank can hold 1728 Buckets of a given Liquid, and this scales up rapidy. For example a 5x5x5 Tank can hold 8000 Buckets.
Craft a 1k ME Storage Component. You can either choose to craft a Storage Cell out of it or further upgrade it into a 4k Storage Component.
Craft some Glass Cables! They can transfer AE2 power and up to 8 channels.
Craft 4 Energetic Alloy in the Arc Furnace or by melting Gold, Redstone and Glowstone in the Smeltery! Then using these materials, craft an Advanced Control Circuit!
Craft some Elite Mechanical Pipes, if you're still not satisfied with the speed of your liquid transfer! For now, this is the highest tier available.

Craft some Dense Smart Cables! They can transmit 32 channels, but can't connect to microblocks, such as a Storage Bus, Exporter, or Importer. Use (non-dense!) Smart Cables branching off from a line of Dense Cables to avoid this problem - but remember, these Smart Cables can only carry 8 channels!

Craft some Smart Cables! Adding to the functionality of Glass Cables, they also show how many channels run through the given Cable, and how many are left available. Different colors of Smart Cables don't connect to eachother, they only connect to colorless Smart Cables.
This is getting ridiculous... Craft a 4096k Storage Component!
You've made it! This is the highest tier Item Storage Component available...! Craft a 16384k Storage Component, also known as a 16M Storage Component!
Use your Inscriber with Pure Certus Quartz Crystals to create some Calculation Processors!
Craft some Certus Quartz Seed and grow them into Pure Certus Quartz in the Crystal Growth Accelerator!

If you have a bunch of smaller Storage Cells full of items, but you want to upgrade to larger Cells, it's worth crafting an ME IO Port. Using this your can empty your items from a smaller Cell into your Storage Network. If the Network only consists of larger Cells, this will effectively transfer items from smaller to larger Cells.
Craft a 16k Storage Component! You might wanna consider storing your items in this or slightly larger Cells if you're starting to run some Quarries.
Craft a 4k ME Storage Component! These might be enough for the early game. They have plenty of space to store your items.

Craft some Basic Universal Cables! They can be used to easily transfer energy between two spots! However, I still encourage you to use Immersive Engineering Wires, since in 1.12 Mekanism Universal Cables tend to cause FPS lag due to inefficient rendering. So use them sparingly!

Turn up the radio! Blast the stereo! Riiiiiiiight noooowwww...! And craft an Electric Pump! Use this if you need a large amount of Lava from the Nether. It's easier than using individual Buckets for each Lava source block. Simply set it up above a source block of a fluid, power it from the side and place some kind of a fluid container on top. Later you'll be able to use it in conjunction with the Quantum Entagloporter to transfer your Fluids wirelessly.
Craft an Osmium Compressor! This machine can create more crafting materials for Mekanism. You can automate it the same way as the Metallurgic Infuser.

Work your way up to an Ultimate Fluid Tank! Right now this is your best way of storing Fluids in a 1x1 area, although for more storage you can make the Dynamic Tank multiblock. Like all Mekanism machines and blocks, this can also be picked up and moved with a Crescent Hammer (Shift+Right Click), and it'll still retain its stored fluid. This is also true when upgrading to a higher tier Tank.
Craft an Energized Smelter! You can smelt your Dusts into Ingots or simply use it as a Furnace powered by energy.
Craft 4 Muffling Upgrades! You can apply these via the top right button of the UI of any machine, and with each upgrade it'll make the machine considerably quieter.

Craft 8 Speed Upgrades! This is the maximum that a Mekanism Machine can accept. Simply click on the Upgrades slot in the top right of the UI of any machine, and place the upgrades in the top right slot. But watch out, with each upgrade, the machine will require more and more power!
Climb to the top of the Sunspeaker Tower and destroy the central structure encased in Glass. By Right Clicking on it, it'll blow up and drop a Heart of Ra.
Find some Relic Ore underground and mine it up without using Silk Touch! Obtain every single type of Dirty Relic from it.
Please read the quest description of the Mud Umbergolem quest! The Iron Umbergolem is found in the North-Eastern corner of the Maze.

betterquesting:10.name:8: Onwards, to the Land of Bzz!
betterquesting:10.desc:8: Enter the Erebus! Make sure to bring lots of food, good gear, a Backpack and Water Buckets. You're gonna be inside for a while. Once entered, place your second Staff of Gaea in the Gaean Keystone that spawned on the other side.
Craft TWO Gaean Gems! One's needed to ENTER Erebus, the other's needed to LEAVE Erebus. (You don't wanna get stuck, do you?)
Craft an Erebus Offering Altar! To use it, simply Right Click the 3 required items on it, and wait...

Find and raid a Pyramid! Go down into the maze below the structure. You can disable traps by Right Clicking on them with a Pickaxe. Get to the end and summon the Pharaoh using 4 Royal Torches. Once defeated, Right Click on its tomb to find various treasures and exactly one Artifact! There are 4 types of Artifacts: Melee, Ranged, Armor & Necklace. You'll need to find one of each type (so you'll need to raid at least 4 Pyramids) in order to continue. To complete this quest specifically, you'll need to find one Melee Artifact.

Craft a Scarab! This item is used to enter the Atum. To create the portal, place a 5x5 platform of Sandstone. Then raise up the edges by 1 block, and fill up the resulting 3x3 inner area with Water source blocks. Finally, build a 2-high Sandstone pillar on each of the corners, and throw in the Scarab.

Note: If you're building this portal in Creative Mode for some reason, and it isn't working, try again without flying.
Grow some Emmer! This is the Wheat equivalent of Atum. In order to grow the seeds, you'll need water and tillable soil, so either find an Oasis or go back to the Overworld for them.
Find some Emmer Seeds by either punching tall grass in an Atum Oasis or in a treasure chest!

betterquesting:10.name:8: Not M enough, do it EMMER!
betterquesting:10.desc:8: Crush your Emmer using your Quern to obtain some Emmer Flour! To turn Emmer Flour into Emmer Dough, simply Right Click with it on a Water source block.
Color your Ceramic Tile Blocks brown, then craft a Quern! To use it, place some items on it, then hold Right Click with an empty hand to crush the materials on top.

Craft TWO Staves of Gaea. One's used to ENTER Erebus, the other's used to LEAVE Erebus.

[Read this if you've still managed to get stuck in Erebus] Okay. You didn't listen to me. I warned you multiple times. Well, this is your fault now. All the materials required for an Offering Altar, a Gaean Gem and a Staff of Gaea can be found inside Erebus. Emeralds are quite rare, but you might be able to gather them from some of the quest rewards in this chapter. Welp, time to get minin'! Also, if you can't seem to craft a Furnace, just remember how you made Iron the first time. You can find Dandelions and Yellow Petal Blocks in Erebus as well. (By the way, this is why the Offering Altar, the Gaean Gem and the Staff of Gaea only require some basic materials.)
Tarantula legs might be disguisting, but if there's nothing better, cook them and munch them up! They're crispy.

Craft a Gaean Keystone! Then build a portal frame out of any kind of solid blocks and fill the middle with leaf blocks! The frame can be any shape, convex or concave, horizontal or vertical. To activate the portal, place the Gaean Keystone in front of the portal, and put one of your Staff of Gaea inside.

Craft at least one Velocity Block! Any entity on top will be pushed in the direction the arrow is pointing toward with 5x the base walking speed. Moreover, mobs can spawn on top of these blocks, which make them a perfect candidate for a mobfarm floor!
Find either some Solifuges (in the Ulterior Outback biome) or some Centipedes (in the Ulterior Outback / Elysian Fields / Subterranean Savannah biome) to obtain some Bio-Velocity!
Wash some of your Dirty Relics to turn them into beautiful Pure Relics! You can Right Click them on Sunspeakers to sell them for Gold Coins.
Please read the Melee Artifact quest description. This quest is for the rarest type of Artifacts, Necklace Artifacts!

Find a Sunspeaker Tower! They're commonly found in mountainous areas of Atum, and emit a red beacon light. Right Click on them with your washed Relics to trade them for Gold Coins! You can get a surprisingly large amount of Coins this way.
Use your Spinning Wheel to create 12 pieces of Linen Cloth! Though that's enough to complete this quest, you might need more thereafter...

betterquesting:10.name:8: You spin my flax Right Round
betterquesting:10.desc:8: Craft a Spinning Wheel! To use it, hold Right Click on the top with 3 Flax Flowers in your hands. Then You spin my flax right round, right round, when you go down, when you go down, down, since you can take out the resulting flax from down below, from the side of the block.
Grow some Flax Flowers! You'll need Water and tillable soil, so you might want to find an Oasis or go back to the Overworld for this.

Find a peculiar looking camel-shaped structure in the desert! Go inside to find some developer jokes that might or might not break the fourth wall, and find the Idol of Labor Artifact. You can even start a conversation with it by Right Clicking it...

Obtain some Poison Gland from any of the poisonous bugs in Erebus, and a Nettle Leaf from Nettles found in Elysian Fields or the Subterranean Savannahs! This is probably the most useful Potion you'll get access to, since many of the creatures in this dimension poison you. It'll be especially useful when fighting against Tarantulas and the Tarantula Brood Mother.
Craft an Erebus Co. Smoothie-matic 2000! This machine is used to create smoothies with various magical effects (just like Potions).
Find some Relic Ore underground and mine it up using Silk Touch!
Find some Marl underground in Atum and smelt it in your Kiln to create some White Ceramic Tile Blocks!

Use your Relic Ingots to craft some Relic Blocks and create an Atum Kiln! This is a multiblock structure made of 2 Kiln blocks and 6 Small Limestone Bricks in a 2x2. The Kiln blocks go on top in the same row besides each other. This machine can be used as a regular Furnace, or to create some Atum-specific items.

Find a Giant Baobab Tree that spawns exclusively in the Subterranean Savannah biome. Defeat the Tarantulas at the bottom, climb up to the top, and fight the Tarantula Brood Mother! In Phase 1, it can only be damaged by ranged projectiles. If you're using a Golden Fury, make sure to stand farther back in order to hit her! Phase 2 begins when the Brood Mother goes below 50% health. In this Phase, you can only damage it by melee hits. It might be a good idea to start off the fight from a platform you've built up next to the tower, so you can't get knocked down in Phase 1 at least. Good luck! You'll need it... Once defeated, mine up the Tarantula Egg it leaves behind!

Black Tarantula, time for the massive come sing ya!
Black Tarantula, don't play with my style I might sting ya...!
Black tarantula, you want me inject me bacteria..!
And if ya body goin' stiff and your spine goin' numb... Now come fi get some...
It almost doesn't even seem to HAVE a soul.... Or does it...?
Craft some White Linen! This can be used as a replacement for Wool, or to craft an Atum Poppet.
After you've Right Clicked your Emmer Flour onto a Water source block to turn it into Emmer Dough, smelt it to get Emmer Bread!
Find all the Erebus-specific Ores underground: Temple Ore, Fossil Ore and Gneiss Ore. Mine up some of them to complete this quest!
Craft a Power Egg! ...Now what could THIS be used for...?

betterquesting:10.name:8: It's an Ant! It's a Lion!
betterquesting:10.desc:8:
It's an Antlion!

Once you've activated all the gates, you'll find yourself in the Antlion bossroom! Watch out, this boss is tough! It can charge at you, knock you away and even blind you for two seconds at a time. It's recommended to use a Potion of Strength to take it down.

Once defeated, mine up its Antlion Egg and return through the portal you came in. One of the portals in the previous room should bring you back to the top.
Find some Bamboo Stalks in Erebus! It's pretty easy to get a lot of it.
Please read the quest description of the Mud Umbergolem quest! The Jade Umbergolem is found in the South-Western corner of the Maze.
Craft some Mixed Erebusian Stone! It's a nice building block, but it's also used to progress futher.
Find a Sunspeaker Tower in mountainous areas of Atum! Defeat some of the Sunspeakers to obtain some Efreet Hearts! Though you might want to trade with them first...

Find a Fungal Forest biome in Erebus and collect a couple pieces of each type of large mushrooms! Though this is enough to complete this quest, you might need more very soon...


(Only 4 choices by the quest rewards? Complain to the creators of HQM for adding a cap of 4 "Pick one" options.)
Mix together some Mushrooms and Ember to create some Hardened Ember Moosh!
No it's not. But find some Amber scattered around in Erebus and mine it up!
Please read the Melee Artifact quest description. This quest is for Ranged Artifacts!

Once you've defeated all the Umbergolems, find your way back to the center and activate the Capstones on top by placing one of each Umbergolem Scarab into its Capstone! Then this quest will serve as a checklist on what you'll need. Near the entrance you'll find a chest that contains 8 Jades. Place them into the floor tiles to activate the trapdoor! You'll need to do this 4 more times with the items listed in this quest.

Note: You can obtain Magma Cream from Fire Ants spawning in Erebus. The other items should be self-explanatory. You should have already gotten Exoskeleton Plates from Beetles roaming the Maze and Magma Crawler Eyes from Magma Crawlers commonly found on the ceiling of Maze corridors.

Find an Antlion Overlord Pyramid partially (or sometimes fully) hidden underground exclusively in Volcanic Desert biomes! Descend into the Maze surrounding the Pyramid, and find the four Umbergolem Idol Guardians found in the farthest edges of the Maze! This quest is specifically for the Mud Umbergolem, found in the North-Western corner. Once defeated, pickup the Scarab they drop!
Please read the quest description of the Mud Umbergolem quest! The Gold Umbergolem is found in the South-Eastern corner of the Maze.
Brrr.... Freezing cold Winter! Finish up Atum by crafting an Atum Warrior that lets you enter Iceika, the land of Winter!

Trade with Sunspeakers all the way until you get the Enchanted Golden Date trade! This item grants the exact same effect as an Enchanted Golden Apple. Though you might not want to eat it, and just keep it for progression.
Please read the Melee Artifact quest description. This quest is for Armor Artifacts!
Craft a Crown of Skies that lets you enter the Aether!
Find some Mummies in Atum! They can spawn at night or in Pyramids. Defeat them and collect their Cloth Scraps!
Obtain some Flax Seeds by either finding an Oasis and breaking the tall grass there, or finding some in a treasure chest!

Okay this block is ridiculous. This time it speeds up any entity to 10x base walking speed. It works even better for a mobfarm.

Oh, and the same mobs drop Supernatural Velocity wings as well.
Craft a Radiant Beacon! This block emits red light and is later used as an ingredient for an actual Beacon.
Combine some Skyroot Remedy, Aechor Petal, Enchanted Gravitite, Aerogel & some Purple Dye to create this gooey material...
Once you've emptied an Aechor Plant, defeat it for its drop, the Aechor Petal!
Enchant your Skyroot Poison Bucket into a Skyroot Remedy Bucket! You can drink this to clear any Poison effect from yourself, or use it for crafting.

Place some Lava in the Aether! It'll immediately freeze into Aerogel which you can mine up... Consider thinking of a way to automate this later...

'Cause you're hot then you're cold,
You're yes then you're no,
You're in then you're out,
You're up then you're down,
You're wrong when it's right,
It's black and it's white,
We fight, we break up,
Turn Lava to Ice!
Create some Enchanted Gravitite Blocks using your Enchanter! Placing one of these blocks below the Enchanter will make it work twice as fast and use half as many Ambrosium Shards.
Find some Workshop Lamps spawning in small groups on some Coalstone Pillars!
Craft a Snow Globe to enter Iceika! Build a portal out of Snow Blocks in the shape of a regular Nether Portal (with a 2x3 inner area). Then light the portal with your Snow Globe!

Find some Aechor Plants that randomly spawn on the surface of Aether islands! They have light cyan petals and usually spawn in small groups. Watch out, once you get close, they'll shoot poison darts at you. Once you get close, Right Click on them with your Skyroot Bucket to obtain Skyroot Poison. Each Plant can be Right Clicked on several times before they run out of Poison. Make sure to collect a lot of it.

Now that you have defeated all three Aether bosses, you can craft an Enchanter! Note that the Aether Power Core has 64 durability, so you can craft up to a stack of Enchanters. Just like the Freezer, this machine also accepts inputs pushed in through any side or the top, and you can pull out the result from the bottom. However, if you don't want to automate it yet, it might be smarter to put an Enchanted Gravitite Block below the machine. This way it'll work twice as fast and use half the Ambrosium Shards.
Though Draconium Dust is available in other dimensions, it's in much greater quantity in the End. It can be found on the Main Island, Outer End Islands & End Comets. Mine up some of it!

Let the Eyes of Ender guide you to the End Portal! Activate it and enter it...

Though I thought I didn't have to tell you this... Aren't you a professional Minecraft player?!

The rewarded bottles are to collect Dragon's Breath. Don't forget to nab some!

pages:9.0:8: {"text":"If you\u0027re playing in Multiplayer, others might have killed the Dragon before you.\n\nUse these items to resummon the Dragon in that case!"}

betterquesting:10.desc:8: Slay some of the creatues in Iceika to obtain their precious Ice Shards!
Craft Steel or Golden Rings and Pendants and turn them into Ice Rings and Pendants in your Freezer!
Craft an Aether Freezer! Fuel it with Icestone, and if you want to automate it, insert items from any side or top, and pull the result from the bottom using a Hopper!
After you've defeated the Ender Dragon, travel to the End Isles, find an End City and loot the Elytra!
After you've defeated the Ender Drakyboo, collect the its Dragon Egg! What could be inside...!?

After entering the End, you might have noticed this cute black drakyboo flapping around in the sky. Now, your job is to keep petting it until its Health Bar decreases to basically none and it releases cool shiny purple rays 'n stuff.

Then collect its Dragon Heart. Easy peasy!

Craft a Gravitite or Valkyrie Axe and break some Golden Oak Tree logs to obtain some Golden Amber!




















It's raining amber! Hallelujah!
It's raining amber! Amen!
I'm gonna go out to run and let myself get
Absolutely soaking weeeeet!

It's raining amber! Hallelujah!
It's raining amber! Every specimen!
Tall, blonde, dark and lean
Rough and tough and strong and meeeeaaaan!
Dig up some Zanite Gemstones, Ambrosium Shards and Gravitite Ore from the Aether underground! Watch out for Gravitite Ores... they float.

Create some GP Powder from your Festive Powder, then duplicate it via crafting!

You can later automate the duplication recipe with a single RFTools Crafter. Setup 2 recipes for crafting GP Powder, one on Keep/Int, the other on Keep/ExtC. Fill the bottom two rows with the duplication ingredients, and leave 1 slot for GP Powder. Once all of these ingredients are in place, hit "R" to make the machine remember where the items should go. The slot with GP Powder will stay on 63 GP Powder at all times, and the rest will go in the output slot. Now you just need to pump in the ingredients and pump out the GP Powder (no need for a filter)!

The Santa Armor set is great and all, but Christmas time is nearing its end... But hey, maybe you can reuse your Santa gear for something else...?

Look up the steps for crafting some Festive Powder in JEI, and create some!
Chop some Golden Oak or Skyroot Trees and craft up some Skyroot Buckets!

Create a portal frame out of Glowstone Blocks with an inner area of 2x3 blocks (just like a simple Nether Portal), then activate it with a Water Bucket. To actually enter the Aether, you'll need to Right Click onto an Aether Portal block with the Crown of Skies. This will grant you access to the Aether forever, through any Aether portal.

Once you have entered the dimension, get your Book of Lore from the quest reward. This is a useful tool for checking what each Aether item and block does. Simply place the item/block inside the book to get a short description for it.

Finally, don't worry about falling off an island. You'll simply fall back to the overworld! If you have Slime Boots on, this shouldn't be an issue.

Find a dungeon underground in Iceika! They spawn quite commonly, uniformly on any height level. Find a dungeon chest and loot some of the Snowflakes and Snowflake Shurikens that are inside. You can either use the Shurikens for damage or craft them into more Snowflakes!
Fold some Gold in the Enchanted Berries! Unfortunately this will get rid of the great taste and make it inedible though...
Enchant some Blueberries in your Enchanter. 100% guaranteed better taste!
"I sold 'er to an older!"

Craft a Portal to the Deep Dark! This is a mining world, so it's the best place to setup your Quarry with some kind of item teleportation back to your base. You'll also need to send it power.
But make sure to bring torches or some kind of lighting, because the darkness inside the dimension will constantly damage you!
Create some Crystalline Pink Slime Ingots then alloy it further into some Crystalline Brown Slime Ingots!
Mine up some Resonant End Stone to obtain Resonant Clathrate! This is used for Applied Energistics Fluid Storage Cells and Fluid-related items.
Travel to the End Islands and punch a Chorus Plant to obtain a bunch of Chorus Fruit! Build yourself up higher to obtain some Chorus Flowers!
Combine Enchanted Golden Berries and Lead Rods into Stems then ultimately a Necklace. Fancy!

Find a huge cathedral floating in the sky! This is the Silver Dungeon. Enter it and defeat at least 10 Valkyries. They'll each drop a Victory Medal. Then work your way to the final room, located on the opposite side of the main entrance. You'll find the Valkyrie Queen inside, who you can only challenge if you Right Click on her with 10 Victory Medals, to show that you are worthy to fight her.

She can teleport around and turn invisible during the fight, and send out area of effect orbs that damage the player. It's recommended to constantly push her away, or use building blocks to give you a temporary hiding place to heal up.

When defeated, she'll drop a Silver Key. Using this you can unlock the Silver Treasure Chest to earn a Silver Aether Coin and a bunch of Valkyrie Metal.
Find some Blueberry Bushes! Break them to obtain their Berry. If you want to relocate them, break them again.

betterquesting:10.name:8: Brrr, it's cold, don't touch it
betterquesting:10.desc:8: Find some Icestone underground in the Aether! It's about as rare as Iron Ore in the overworld but spawns in larger veins.
It resonates with great power... THIS must be source of energy...!
Enchant some Holystone to create some Healing Stones! They can be eaten to gain Regeneration I for half a minute. Or you can use them to progress further...

betterquesting:10.name:8: No need for Coal, it's built in!
betterquesting:10.desc:8: Obtain a Coalstone Furnace from Villager houses in Iceika! Although these Furnaces cook slowly, they don't require any fuel to function.

Find an opening on the side of a larger Aether island! You'll know if you've found a Bronze Dungeon, if the walls are made out of Carved Stone. Get to the end an awaken the Slider! This boss slides on walls and can only be damaged with a Pickaxe. Make sure to bring some Health Potions, Golden Apples and good armor to the fight, because this boss can be pretty tough!

Once you've defeated the Slider, it'll drop a Bronze Key. Open the reward chest to find one Bronze Aether Coin inside!

During your Ender Dragon petting mission, collect some Dragon's Breath!

If you missed the opportunity to do so, you can resummon the Ender Dragon with 4 End Crystals on either side of the portal.

If you're having trouble collecting some because of Botania's Ender Air Bottles, try the following: Do NOT Right Click on blocks, instead, angle your clicks so you only reach the purple Dragon's Breath particles, and NOT the blocks below.

Find a smaller floating island and the Gold Dungeon inside, with only one boss: the Sun Spirit. To initiate the fight, you'll need to talk to him several times... but you might want to prepare first.

If you've never done this fight before, this might take you a while, depending on how good your aim is. So prepare with multiple Fire Resistance and Healing Potions.

Firstly, you cannot damage this boss with any regularly obtainable weapon or projectile, you can only damage it with projectiles called "Icey Balls" that randomly spawn from the Sun Spirit during the fight. However, both the boss and the iceballs randomly bounce around, with makes it hard to hit the iceballs into the Sun Spirit. Also, you can't wait too long, the iceballs will break a short time after spawning. Meanwhile, Fire Ball projectiles will also spawn and bounce around in the room. Make sure that neither the boss, nor the Fire Balls hit you. But especially watch out for the boss, as it deals a lot of damage on contact.

You'll need the hit iceballs into the Sun Spirit 10 times to defeat it. Once you've sucessfully done so, it'll drop a Golden Key. Open the Treasure Chest that appeared to obtain the Golden Aether Coin!
Obtain some Valkyrie Metal Ingots and Nuggets from Silver Dungeon Chests!

Craft some Eye of Enders in your Induction Smelter. Use them to find the End Portal!

The End Exploration related quests are located in Exploration III.

Find a Village house in Iceika! Enter it (you can open the Steel Door with a Right Click, no need to bust in by breaking it). Find the Workshop Merchant (red NPC) and trade some Snowflakes for the full set of Santa Armor!
Craft an Auto Enchantment Table! You can automatically insert tools, armor or books inside to enchant them using liquid experience.
Craft some Open Ingots! These are used in a number of Open Blocks machines.
Craft an XP Bottler! This machine can fill up Empty Bottles with liquid experience pumped into it to create Bottles o' Enchanting. Everything can be automatically inserted and extracted.
Use materials from your Enchanter to create a Sun Crystal! Throw it on the ground for a while to fill it up with sunlight. Consider a way to automate this process for the future.

Craft some Unstable Ingots and upgrade them immediately into some Moon Stones before they blow up! Make sure to have every material in your inventory, and do the second step of the crafting under 10 seconds, before the Unstable Ingots gets you.

Or alternatively if you're rolling in Diamonds, you can spend 9 times the Diamond to craft Stable-'Unstable' Nuggets and put them together into a Stable-'Unstable' Ingot, which doesn't blow up, but can be used for crafting the same way.

Craft some Osglolapis and turn it into Lunar Reactive Dust in your Resonator! This will require 16 GP total, meaning you'll need to use both the manual mill AND the Solar Panel, at least until you've gotten more GP Generators setup.
Craft some Stoneburnt in your Resonator! Don't sniff it too much, it's got an awful smell...

Craft a Resonator! This is the most important Extra Utilities machine. You'll need GP Generating machines in order to use it. You might want to consider crafting multiple Resonators for automation.

When playing in multiplayer, you can do §§§c/xu_powersharing§r to open a GUI. Click players on there to share GP with them, provided they would also share GP with you.
Craft an Absorption Hopper! This functions very similarly to a Vacuum Hopper, except with range upgrades it can have WAAAY more range!
Craft an Open Blocks Vacuum Hopper! This machine can suck up items and experience orbs from a range. You can also set output sides for each.

Alloy some Demonlord Ingots with some Gunpowder to obtain your first pieces of Mobgrindium Ingots! This is the gateway into Mob Grinding Utils.

Note: If you're searching for Mob Grinding Utils in JEI, type @mob_grinding_utils.

An alternative way of moving mobs besides Fans are regular old Conveyor Belts! Mobs CAN spawn on these blocks, so if you want to, you can build your entire mob spawning platform out of these. However, I'd just use them sparingly since Cursed Earth and Mob Fans are way better.

"Here is Goldey!"

Upgrade your Iron Spikes into Golden Ones. These might not deal as much damage, however anything killed by them drop experience!
Craft some Wooden, Stone and finally Iron Spikes! This damages any mob standing on top of right besides it. Great for a mob farm!

Use your Resonantor to make some Red Coal, and then use it to craft a Redstone Star! The Red Coal will require 16 GP total, meaning you'll need to use both the manual mill AND the Solar Panel, at least until you've gotten more GP Generators setup.
Craft some Mob Masher Smite Upgrades. You can insert at most 10 of these in the machine. This will make the Masher stronger against undead foes like Zombies and Skeletons.

Craft a Mob Masher! To activate it, use a redstone signal. This is a highly upgradable mob killing machine that drops experience after every mob. Route mobs from your farm here, I'm sure they'll have a wonderful time!
Use your Bottling Machine to fill Empty Bottles into Bottles o' Enchanting!

Craft an Extra Utilities Enchanter! This is another crafting mechanic in the mod. You'll need to setup bookshelves around it the same way you do for Enchantment Table, and power it with RF. You can upgrade it with Speed Upgrades and auto insert / extract items into / from it.
Craft an Extra Utilities Machine Block! This is the base for all Extra Utilities machines.
Surround Lava on all 4 sides with Nether Bricks, then throw in some Gold Ingots to create some Demon Ingots. Alloy it with Lunar Reactive Dust to create Demonlord Ingots!
Use your Enchanter to make some Magical Wood! You might want to continuously keep creating this for later use.
Craft some RF Dust! This will only take 1 durability point from your Thermal Conductor Rod.
Craft a Thermal Conductor Rod! This item lets your craft RF Dust which ultimately lets you get into Thermal Expansion.
Craft some Mob Masher Bane of Arthropods Upgrades. You can insert at most 10 of these in the machine. This will make the Masher deal more damage against Arthropods like Spiders and Silverfish.

Craft a Manual Mill! While holding Right Click on it, you generate 15 GP (or Grid Power). This is a resource that doesn't need cables. Simply while you're generating X amount of GP, all your GP using machines will work granted you're using at most X amount of GP overall.
Craft some Solar Panels! Simply placing one down will generate 1 GP in the daytime.

Craft a Stone Drum and upgrade it to an Iron Drum! It can hold 256 Buckets of any liquid, and you can Right Click on it to see how much is left. I would encourage you to set one up to feed Lava into your Smeltery.
Craft a Reinforced Large Drum! It can hold 4096 Buckets of any liquid! Wow!

Craft an Extra Utilities Crusher! This is yet another way to turn your Ores and Ingots into Dust! It can be sped up by Extra Utilities Speed Upgrades to make it faster than the Immersive Engineering and Mekanism Crushers.
Craft some Lunar Panels to be able to generate GP passively during the night!

Craft a Lava Mill! This machine generates GP when and of its sides are touching lava blocks. Flowing Lava one block away from a source block generates the most GP. Having Lava on multiple sides doesn't increase the generation, but being in the Nether does slightly.

This generator has been buffed and generates 2x the normal amount.

Craft some Mob Masher Beheading Upgrades. You can insert at most 10 of these in the machine. This will make the Masher drop mobs Skulls way more frequently than they would normally drop. Only vanilla Skulls are available though.

Craft a Water Mill! This machine generates GP passively when there is flowing water on any of its sides.

This generator has been nerfed, and generates 1/4x the normal amount.
Craft an OpenBlocks Fan! When powered by redstone, it blows any entity away. Useful for a mob farm, although the Mob Fan is even better.

Drops of Evil are no longer dropped by Wither Skeletons, they're instead crafted. So craft one! And use it to turn surrounding Grass into Cursed Earth! This type of soil makes mobs spawn constantly, so it's perfect for a mob farm. Just watch out, don't let it burn.
Craft an Auto Anvil! You can automatically insert tools & armor to repair them using liquid experience.
Craft a Mob Fan Height Modifier! You can apply at most 3 of these to your Mob Fan.

betterquesting:10.name:8: Mobs aren't a Fan of this
betterquesting:10.desc:8: Upgrade your OpenBlocks Fan into a Mob Fan! When powered by redstone, this machine blows mobs with great strength, and it's the perfect way to move mobs off your spawning platform. Additionally, it's highly upgradable, and with max upgrades you'll surely only need at most one per platform.
Craft some Mob Fan Distance Modifiers! You can apply at most 10 of these to your Mob Fan.
Craft some Mob Masher Sharpness Upgrades. You can insert at most 10 of these in the machine. This will make the Masher generally deal more damage to all things.

Craft a Transfer Pipe and one of each type of Transfer Node - Item, Fluid, and Energy. Each functions slightly differently.
One big advantage is that you can route items, fluids, and energy all through one pipe - although filtering on the receiving end may be required!

§cThe Item Transfer Node is a highly upgradeable and filterable item routing mechanism, and its much better than Thermal's Itemducts when fully upgraded. It can be upgraded using Extra Utilities' Speed and Stack Upgrades, along with its Filters.

§3The Fluid Transfer Node functions very similarly to the Item Transfer Node (but, you know, with fluids?).

§6The Energy Transfer Node cannot be upgraded, and always transfers 5,000 RF/t.

Craft a Building Guide! This block can help you build nice geometric shapes. Use the arrows on top to swap between different shapes. Use the plus and minus signs on the sides to increase or decrease the side of your build. Then power it with a redstone signal to make ghost blocks appear.

You can also upgrade it into an Enhanced Building Guide to get some more available shapes.

Make a Wind Mill! Tis machine passively generates GP if there is nothing blocking its northern and southern sides. It generates more in the rain.

This generator has been buffed and generates 2x the normal amount.
Craft some Mob Fan Width Modifiers! These are likely the most useful upgrades, and you can apply at most 3 of these to your Mob Fan.
Yet another Furnace, eh? Well, this one can be pretty speedy with Extra Utilities Speed Upgrades!

Craft at least one Ultimate Speed Upgrade. This makes machines even faster, and it can stack up to 64. You might need that speed for something in the lategame, but be aware that it'll use a lot of GP.

Craft at least one Magical Speed Upgrade! This makes machines even faster, and it can stack up to 16 instead of just 4. However, be aware that your machines will use even more GP when upgraded with higher-tier Speed Upgrades.

Craft a couple Seed Upgrades, and one Stack & Mining Upgrade.

- Speed Upgrades increase a machine's speed or a Transfer Node's transfer rate.
- One Stack Upgrade makes it so the Transfer Node sends a stack of items at once, instead of individual ones.
- The Mining Upgrade is similar to the 1.7 World Interaction Upgrade. It mines Cobblestone when placed inside a Transfer Node which is over a full block with Water and Lava source blocks on the side.
Craft a couple Upgrade Bases! These can be crafted into Speed, Stack, and Mining Upgrades.

Craft some Ineffable and Dark Ineffable Glass. While players can, mobs can't travel through these blocks, which makes them useful for mob farm or mob spawner walls, as well as general base doors. The regular one does let light through, the dark one doesn't. So mobs will be able to spawn inside when you use the dark variants.
Craft some Mob Masher Fire Aspect Upgrades. You can insert at most 10 of these in the machine. This will set all mobs on fire that are touched by the Masher. Perfect for Cooked Porkchops!
These fellahs deal a lot of damage...! So why not craft some?

Craft a Fire Mill! This machine generates GP passively while over an active Fire block. Use Netherrack below.

This generator has been buffed and it generates 4x the normal amount.
Craft a couple Absorption Range Upgrades to increase the range of your Absorption Hopper! You can use at most 6 of these.
Craft some Mob Masher Looting Upgrades. You can insert at most 10 of these in the machine. This will make the Masher drop more loot.
Use Cinnabar Ore with Liquid Cryotheum in the Fluid Transposer to get a bunch of Cinnabar!

Craft all 4 types of Thermal Expansion Dusts!

- To obtain Blizz Powder for Cryotheum, use your Fluid Transposer with Snowballs and Liquid XP.

- To obtain Blitz Powder for Aerotheum, use your Fluid Transposer with Niter and Liquid XP. To get Niter, simply Pulverize Sandstone.

- To get Basaltz Powder for Pethroteum, use your Fluid Transposer with Pulverized Obsidian and Liquid XP.
Use Mithril Ingots to create Operator Processors! These are used in Fluid Storage related AE2 items.
Use your Arc Furnace or Alloy Smelter to craft some Mithril Ingots! It takes 1 Mana Dust, 1 Demonlord Ingot and 1 Platinum Ingot to craft one.
Craft a regular Energy Cell Frame and make it into an Energy Cell! You can upgrade them with Upgrade Kits, but it might be easier to craft them directly.
Create Refined Fuel using your Fractionating Still, then Fluid Transpose it onto some Dark Ingots to create Energized Dark Ingots!

Craft some Dark Ingots! You can find Bitumen underground to obtain Tar, you can either

- Use a Fractionating Still with Oil (found underground), Crude Oil (obtained from Bitumen) or Liquifacted Coal (obtained from Pulverized Coal); or

- Use DivineRPG Tar and Slimeballs in a Fluid Transposer.

Upgrade an Extra Utilities Machine Block to a Thermal Expansion one!

Apply your various wrenches to the rewarded Morphing Tool to easily swap between them.
Use some Coated Clathrate to create some Estimation Processors!

betterquesting:10.name:8: It's a gem, it's a pebble!
betterquesting:10.desc:8:
Craft some Coated Clathrate either in the Induction Smelter or the Fluid Transposer!

You need to have visited the End for Resonant Clathrate.
Use Cinnabar and Nickel Ore in your Induction Smelter to get Platinum with 100% chance!

Craft an Induction Smelter! With this machine, you can create alloys that only take 2 inputs. For these types (like Bronze, Electrum, Invar or Vibrant Alloy), the Induction Smelter will do the best job, as it's really fast when fully upgraded.
Craft some Rosin in a Fractionating Still! To get Resin, use either an Arboreal Extractor (recommended, since it's free and will generate passively), or a Sawmill with a Resin Funnel Augment.

Craft a Resin Funnel Augment! Apply it to your Sawmill to be able to create Resin. Check which Wood types give Resin in JEI (simply check the usages for this Augment), since that's the type of fluid you'll need in the future.

Craft an Arboreal Extractor! To use it, place it next to the bottom of a naturally grown tree. Different tree types will provide different types of fluids, you are looking for Resin. To see which tree type gives which fluid, you can check the usages for the "Augment: Resin Funnel" item, since the same types of trees yield Resin in a Sawmill. However, I recommend this method for obtaining large amounts of Resin, since this is free and will passively generate.
Craft a Farming Station! Place it in the center of a crop field, give it power and a hoe, set its output, and watch it work! Auto cropfarms, hurray!
Soulificate your Machine Chassis to gain access to more machines from EnderIO!
Craft a Compactor! This is the best way to automatically make all the various types of Plates. You can also create Gears for slightly cheaper.
Craft a Device Frame! This is used in all the Thermal Expansion Devices (surprise-surprise), which are Machines that usually don't need any power to function.

Combine Hardened Fluxducts and Itemducts to obtain some Signalum-Plated Itemducts. These pipes can transmit both power and items at the same time. You'll need to use Servos if you want to transmit items.
Craft some of the most basic Fluxducts Thermal Expansion has to offer: The Leadstone Fluxducts! They can transmit RF Power, but not a lot of it.
Craft together RF Powder, Pyrotheum Dust, Cryotheum Dust, Aerotheum Dust & Petrotheum Dust to obtain some Mana Dust!
You haven't crafted enough Machine Frames yet, so for that reason, craft another. Lovely, isn't it!?
Craft a Basic Alloy Smelter! This is a cheaper version of the Arc Furnace in multiple cases, but it can only handle 3 inputs. But hey, 3 is more than what the Induction Smelter could handle!

Craft all 4 upgrade kits! Use them to upgrade a Basic machine to Resonant tier by Right Clicking on it! The advantages of Resonant tier is that your can apply Augments to the machine. The most useful Augment is likely the Auxiliary Reception Coil, which speeds up the machine.
Upgrade your Fluid Conduits into Ender Fluid Conduits! These are one of the best types of Fluid Conduits available.
Craft some Fluid Conduits! Though not the best without upgrading them to the next tier, they can still be used in the same blockspace as Item & Energy Conduits.

Craft a Pulverizer! It's probably the best crushing machine you'll get, especially when fully upgraded to Resonant tier, and provided with 9 Auxiliary Reception Coil upgrades.

You can also easily setup its side configurations to input and output items from/to your storage.

Enticing pricing you have there... It's an Icing to the cake! Consider Slice'n'Splicing? If so, craft a Slice'n'Splice! Give it an Axe and some Shears (a good option is the Dark Steel variant for both), and sacrifice some mob skulls to craft some items with it! If you haven't made a Beheading Upgrade from Mob Grinding Utils yet, now would be a great time!
Upgrade your Fluxducts all the way to the Resonant variant! This type of Fluxduct can transmit of lot of power!
Craft a Red Heart Canister! Your player can equip at most 10 of these and get 1 extra full Heart of health per Canister!

Craft a Fluid Transposer! When used in conjunction with a Magma Crucible, you can use some kind of an input item and some kind of fluid provided by the Crucible to craft new items. This machine will be heavily used from now on, so make sure to at least semi-automate it. You can also craft Treated Wood and Coated Clathrate cheaper with this machine.
Craft some Hardened Fluiducts to be able to transport Fluids easily!
Craft some Signalum-Plated Impulse Itemducts by filling up the previous tier with Glowstone! Items travel more rapidly through Glowstone and you can still transmit power through this cable as well.
Craft an Enhanced SAG Mill for even more crushing power!
I heard you like Machine Chassis', so I put some Machine Chassis' in your Machine Chassis' so you can enjoy more Machine Chassis' along the way!

betterquesting:10.name:8: I saw. I milled. I conquered.
betterquesting:10.desc:8: Craft a Sawmill! This machine is capable of turning Wood into more Planks than simply crafting them in your Crafting Window, and is also capable of making Sawdust, used in some recipes.

Craft four of all 5 tiers of Empowered Dark Steel Upgrades! They can be applied to Dark Steel Armor one after another. These are needed for other upgrades and to make your armor set take energy instead of durability on hit.

To apply these upgrades, you need to use a Dark Steel Anvil. Simply have the armor piece equipped and use the tabs in the GUI of the Anvil to be able to apply them.

betterquesting:10.name:8: Riches get a great armor set
betterquesting:10.desc:8:
Once you've accumulated a lot of Dark Steel and Enderium, you can make the best midgame armor set: The Dark Steel Set!

Now, without upgrades you might not think this set is that powerful, but just type "Dark Steel Upgrade" into JEI to see the sheer amount of upgrade options available. Pretty much all of them are useful, so get on with the crafting!

Also, don't forget that this armor is still enchantable besides being upgradable.
Craft an 1k ME Fluid Storage Component! Making this into a Cell will allow you to store liquids in your ME System. You can access these with a Fluid Terminal.

Craft an Enchanter! To see the available recipes, click the Paper icon on the top right of its GUI. You can now get any Enchantment with the appropriate payment! No longer do you need to get lucky in the Enchantment Table.
Craft a 4k ME Fluid Storage Component!

Dig down to the bottom of the overworld and light up some of the Bedrock! Once the fire extinguishes, some Grains of Infinity will pop off. Collect them!

I wonder if you'll have to automate this process... Hmmm... (Yes, yes you do.)

Then use the grains you've obtained to craft a Simple Machine Chassis from EnderIO!

Craft some Item Conduits! They are the EnderIO way to transport items, and probably one of the best ways in general, since they can be used in the same blockspace as other EnderIO Conduits. You can also use Extraction Speed Upgrades and Item Filters in them. You can also simple toggle Round Robin mode on to distribute items equally between outputs and turn Self Feed mode on be able to push items back into the container you were pulling them from.
Craft a 64k ME Fluid Storage Component!
Craft a 16k ME Fluid Storage Component!

Craft a Basic Item Filter then upgrade it to an Advanced Item Filter. Apply them to your Item Conduits and guess what they do...!













































No, I'm not gonna tell you. You really have to guess.
Craft a Soul Binder! Use Soul Vials with mob souls inside the Soul into an item! Spooky!
Craft a Soul Vial! Use it to catch mobs. You can later use them for crafting with the Soul Binder, or soon enough - to automatically spawn more of them... See Chapter 13: Ender Upgrades.

Craft a Redstone Furnace! It's probably the best smelting machine you'll get, especially when fully upgraded to Resonant tier, and provided with 9 Auxiliary Reception Coil upgrades.

You can also easily setup its side configurations to input and output items from/to your storage.
Instead of crafting Fluid Storage Cells, you can choose to store your Fluids in external tanks or drums that might have a larger capacity. For this purpose, you can use an ME Fluid Storage Bus.
Craft a Magma Crucible! This machine can turn many solid items into its liquid form. You'll mostly need to use it to provide various liquids for the Fluid Transposer.
Craft all 3 tiers of regular EnderIO Capacitors! They can be used in all non-basic EnderIO machines to increase their production speed. Even higher tier Capacitors will be available later.
You thought the Alloy Smelter was gonna be that slow?! Well, no longer! Introducing: The Enhanced Alloy Smelter, which is more than twice as fast.

Craft a Fluid Terminal! Through this you can see all stored Fluids in your ME System, and manually import and export a couple of buckets at once. Through I recommend Fluid Export and Import Buses for this job, especially if you're working with larger amounts.
Smelt some Dark Steel in your Basic Alloy Smelter to be able to craft an actual Alloy Smelter! This machine can be upgraded with Capacitors for faster production.

Craft a Glacial Precipitator! With this machine, you can automatically create Snow, Ice or Packed Ice out of Water! Simply feed it Water with an Aqueous Accumulator, an Unending Bowl or an Endervoir, give it some power and watch it work!
Craft a Basic Capacitor Bank. It can store some power, but you likely want to upgrade it further!
Craft an Aqueous Accumulator! Place at least 2 Water Source blocks next to it. This is a fast way to generate a lot of Water for a couple of your machines.
Craft a Fractionating Still! This machine is used for multiple progression-related crafts. It can turn various liquids into solids and other liquids.
Craft an Experience Obelisk! You can pump Liquid XP in and out from it, or simply use the ingame GUI to store or gain XP with some simple button presses.
Craft some Extract Speed Upgrades. You can apply these to your Item Conduits for faster extraction. (Incredible, I know!)
I laid out the most important Dark Steel Upgrades: the ones that make this armor set pretty powerful. Craft them and apply them in a Dark Steel Anvil!
Craft an Enhanced Vat! You'll many of the EnderIO Liquids crafted by this machine to continue in the following chapters.

Craft an Igneous Extruder! Using this machine you can mix Lava and Water to create various stone like Cobblestone, Obsidian, Basalt, or many of the Underground Biomes Stone variants! Simply feed it Lava and Water and watch it work! Note: For Obsidian, Lava does get consumed. For the others, it doesn't.

Craft some Ender Energy Conduits! These are the highest tier Energy Conduits that are available to you currently, and the best ones for the job! Later you'll be able to make even better Energy Conduits from EnderIO Endergy.
Craft some Energy Conduits! Use them as an upgrade base for higher tier EnderIO Energy Conduits.

Craft a Redprint! You can use it to copy a machine's side configurations to a new machine. When placing a machine with it in your offhand, it will auto-apply its configuration. It also works on Servos, Retrivers, and Filters. It can save you a lot of time.
Make an ME Crafting Terminal! Upgrade your old ME Terminal to be able to directly craft using your items in your ME System!
Upgrade your Hardened Fluidcuts to Super-Laminar Fluiducts for limitless fluid transfer!

Craft a SAG Mill! Though the Pulverizer might be the best when fully upgraded, this machine isn't far behind! Later the Enhanced version with higher tier Capacitors can do the job pretty much as good as a fully upgraded Pulverizer.

Craft some Capacitor Banks together to obtain a Vibrant Capacitor Bank! The advantage of using them over any other mod's power storage options, is that you can create a huge multiblock of Capacitor Banks that can store even more power!

Craft a Resonant Energy Cell Frame, fill it up, and craft it into a Resonant Energy Cell! To find Energy Cell recipes, look up the usages of the Invar Gear, Electrum Gear, Signalum Gear, (or in this case) the Enderium Gear. It might be easier to craft them directly rather than upgrading them.

Craft 9 Auxiliary Reception Coil Augments. This is the maximum amount you can apply to a Resonant machine!

Basic machines can accept 1,
Hardened machines can accept 3,
Reinforced machines can accept 5,
Signalum machines can accept 7,
and Resonant machines can accept 9.
Craft an ME Fluid Import Bus and an ME Fluid Export Bus! They work just like their item counterparts, except for Fluids.
Crush some organic materials into Biofuel, then infuse it with Water and Hydrogen to create some Substrate and Ethylene! You can use more Ethylene to multiply your Substrate.

Craft an Electrolytic Separator! Use some kind of a pipe to import Water into the machine, and provide power to it as well. It will separate Water into Hydrogen and Oxygen. To transfer these gases, use Mekanism Pressurized Tubes. To store them, use Mekanism Gas Tanks. You can find quests for them to the right of this one.

Craft a Mekanism Pressurized Reaction Chamber! It takes 1 Fluid input, 1 Gas input and 1 Item input to create other Gases and Items. You'll also need to provide it with power, and the back side is the only one that can accept Liquids, so use all sides wisely!
Craft a Solar Panel III! It can generate 32 RF/tick. Finally a respectable amount.
Craft 8 Tier 1 Solar Panels together for a Tier 2 Solar Panel! It generates an even more incredible 8 RF/tick.
Craft a Solar Panel VIII! It's capable of generating a massive 32,768 RF/tick! It's almost like an Extreme Reactor in a singular block!
Craft a Solar Panel VII! It generates 8,192 RF/tick. Better than a lot of other generators! :O

Craft a Mob Slaughter Factory! Provide it with power, and use it to kill mobs from your Mob Farm or Animal Farm! This machine will produce Liquid Meat and Liquid Pink Slime in the process. Make sure to export both liquids. This can be done from a single side, through a Fluiduct or Fluid Conduit of sorts.

Create some Plastic Sheets either by crafting, or in the Enrichment Chamber (the latter is preferable, as it's much cheaper). Then use 4 Plastic Sheets and half a bucket of Nutrient Distillation (created in the EnderIO Vat) to create 1 Industrial Foregoing Plastic!

Craft a Material StoneWork Factory! This machine can easily create some various basic materials, and it's the perfect way to automate them. Simply lookup its capabilities in JEI, and setup multiple of them for easy automation!

Obtain at least 1 Bucket worth of Liquid Pink Slime! Make a small pen and dig out a 1x1 area to place your fluid into. After about a minute, the liquid will transform into a baby Pink Slime. Use looting on the cutie, or name it Jerry and keep it as your pet, or something. Your choice.

If you chose the first option, continue creating a Pink Slime Ingot.
Craft a Shape Card: Pump! With this, you can use your Builder to drain liquids just like any other Pump would do.

Welcome to the age of "not being low on any material" anymore! Craft an RFTools Builder and a Shape Card. You can use this machine to build structures for you, but you can also use it as a Quarry, once you upgrade your Shape Card into a Shape Card: Quarry.

(Note that the Builder's recipe takes 2 Block Breakers and 2 Block Placers.)

Feed it power and place a Chest on top for outputs. Place a lever on the side to activate it (or any other Redstone activation component).

Route the items from the output chest into your storage system and process the ores automatically with your Pulverizers and Redstone Furnaces.
Craft an Amplification Crystal! It is used to... amplify stuff...! What did you think it was used for?!
Craft 4 QuantumFlux Gold Casings! This is the base for all QuantumFlux machines.

Craft an Energy Field Provider! Craft more Energy Field Addons for machines you want to charge wirelessly. Simply Shift+Right Click an Energy Field Addon onto the Provider, then input it into any machine that requires charging. The Provider will charge the machines with the rate of 512 RF/tick, and its range is 7x4x7 around the machine, which can be expanded with Range Addons.

Craft some Matter Beamers for your RFTools Spawner to work. Link them to the spawner itself with any of the available wrenches. Provide items into your Matter Beamers that send them to your Spawner. The more Beamers, the faster the Spawner functions.

Craft an RFTools Spawner! With this, you can automatically spawn some creatures into the world, though you'll need to pay a price. Note: Not all creatures can be spawned with this primitive block. You'll need Spawners from the following Chapters if you want to spawn other mobs. To use this one though, insert a Syringe of the specified mob, then the GUI will show you items that you need for the mob to spawn. If it shows "nullRF", the mob cannot be spawned unfortunately. You'll need to use Matter Beamers to provide the items. To connect the Matter Beamers, use a Crescent Hammer, a Yeta Wrench, or a Smart Wrench.

Craft a Dread Lamp! You'll need a full OpenBlocks Tank of Tectonic Petrotheum.

This block prevents passive mobs from spawning in a 64 block radious. It WON'T prevent artificial spawning like Mob Spawners.
Craft a Basic Gas Tank! It can store 64 Buckets of a single type of Gas.
Pulverize some Industrial Grade Graphite Ores into Graphite Dust. Then blow up a stack of Graphite Dust to obtain some Hyper Diamonds!

Once upon a time, there was a village in the far west... They were in dire need of outside help, because they've been invaded by forces... Forces that cannot easily be defeated, because they outnumbered them. An expanding country tried to annex their lands and forcefully levy taxes on them. And they had no say in it!

The village elders came together one night to discuss matters... How could we the repel the invasion!? Noone knew the answer. Until a wise young man budged in and whispered: "We have something... they don't have. Let's use it."

And indeed they did. They were masters of a technique noone far and wide has ever even thought of...! The masters of Ore Creation.

They used Darkstone and refined Graphite to give back mother nature what hath been taketh away.

They indeed had mother nature herself on their side. With this knowledge, they waited for troops from the invading country. They waited patiently until one day, knights had arrived from the distance. The sun barely came up, but they were ready nonetheless.

They asked for mother nature because they knew she would listen... And mother nature provided. She created a massive earthquake that shook the knights off their horses! They got so scared they never returned.

That day would later be called "The Origin of the Oregen" and be celebrated each year thereafter.

Come, embrace the knowledge of the villagers, and create some Graphite Ore to please mother nature!

The End
Craft a Mekanism Electrolytic Core! This is used as a crafting component is some machines.
Craft a Wyvern Solar Panel! It can generate 65,536 RF/tick. Holy macaroni!
Craft an RFTools Machine Frame! This is base for all RFTools Machines.

Make a Tree Fluid Extractor and a Latex Processing Unit! Simply tap any type of Tree with the Extractor and send the fluid Latex into the Latex Processing Unit! It'll create Tiny Dry Rubber which you can easily process into Plastic. You'll need to automatically place logs in front of the Tree Fluid Extractor (using like a Block Placer), since it'll eat up the log eventually. Setup multiple of these machines for faster gain!
Use your Rotary Condensentrator to turn Ethylene into Liquid Ethylene. Then feed it into your Pressurized Reaction Chamber along with Oxygen to create some HDPE Pellets!
Setup a Plant Gatherer to gather Saplings and a Plant Sower to plant them! These make up the perfect combination for an automated Tree Farm!
Make a Quibit Crystal! Quibit - quibit!
Create some Fertilizer with your Sewage Composter! You can use it as Bone Meal, Brown Dye, an input for the Plant Fertilizer Machine, or to create some Crystalline Brown Slime Ingots.
Craft a Solar Panel V! It can generate a pretty good 512 RF/tick.
Craft a Solar Panel IV! It can generate a much more respectable 128 RF/tick. Without progressing further into other chapters, this is as far as you can get.
Craft an Advanced Circuit!

Craft an RF Entangler, an RF Exciter and 2 Exciter Upgrades! Place down the Entangler and provide power to it! Place some machines in the vicinity and place some RF Exciters on them! The Entangler is capable of powering all machines equipped with an Exciter as long as both of them are loaded! That's right, they can be any distance away! Applying Exciter Upgrades will increase the transfer rate by 100 RF/tick. Default transfer rate is also 100 RF/tick. Simply Shift+Right Click on the Exciter to apply the Upgrades.
Craft a quantity of 1 Quantum Disk. This is used as a crafting material later on.

Progress further into Ender Utilities, then craft a Matter Transporter from QuantumFlux! This tool is capable of transporting any non-unbreakable block from one location to the other. It's perfect for relocating Mob Spawners!

Make all 3 tiers of RFTools Crafters! Check back on this quest after each upgrade to see if the machine was detected or not. The RFTools Crafter is the bester external crafting machine, and you can easily set some up right now for items you need a lot of. Simply use an Export Bus with the crating ingredients and an Import Bus for the crafted materials. Don't worry, AE2 autocrafting will be here soon!
It's the Ultimate Gas Tank! Upgrade your Basic variant all the way to this! It can store 512 Buckets worth of Gas.
Craft an RFTools Syringe! Left click on a specific type of mob multiple times to fill it up! Then you can insert it into the Spawner to automatically spawn a certain type of mob.

Craft a Rotary Condensentator! This machine is capable of turning Gases into their Liquid variants or vice versa. Connect it to your power line and use Liquid/Gas cables and storage blocks for input/output.
Craft a Solar Panel VI! It can generate 2,048 RF/tick! Wow!

Setup a automatic Cow or Pig farm with the machines listed on the right!

- Have a pen of some fully grown animals with an Animal Baby Separator on one of the walls. Use an Animal Feeder on this pen.

- The babies will enter another chamber. Use an Animal Grower on this pen. Create an exit from this chamber through another Animal Baby Separator, but this time with an Adult Filter.

- Lastly, setup a third pen where newly grown adult animals will go. This is your killing chamber. Go ham. Literally.





All I do is breed, breed, breed no matter what!
Got porkchops on my mind, I can never get enough!
And every time I step up in my base then,
RF Machines let's go up!

...

And they work there (there), and they work there (there),
And there work there, buzz-zwoom, buzz-zwoom, buzz-zwoom!
'Cause all I do is breed, breed, breed,
And if you checking in, check my gear, is it cool, say so please, yeah!
Craft a Draconic Solar Panel! It can generate... wait for it... 262,144 RF/tick! Why would you need that much power anyway?!
Craft an Animal Sewer and a Sewage Composter! Place an Animal on top of the Sewer and route the resulting Sewage into your Composter to create some Fertilizer.
Craft a Speed Upgrade I & II from Tesla Core Lib! Up to 64 of these can be applied to Industrial Foregoing machines.
Craft some Darkstone from QuantumFlux!
Craft a Silk Quarry and a Fortune Quarry Shape Card. They are pretty self-explanatory. You'll get either Silk Touched or Fortuned outputs from your Builder, when using these Shape Cards.

Craft a Shape Card: Quarry! Select two corners of an area to mine and insert it into the Builder! Power up the Builder and you can use it as a Quarry now!

If you don't want to destroy the environment, enter the Deep Dark and mine out that dimension instead! The Deep Dark Portal should be craftable now.

betterquesting:10.name:8: Items will do a pullup for you
betterquesting:10.desc:8: Progress into Actually Additions, then craft a QuantumFlux Item Magnet! This is one of the best early- to midgame Baubles! It requires no power and it has quite a strong magnetic field.

Craft a Mega Torch from Torchmaster! You will need a full OpenBlocks Tanks of Energized Glowstone.

This prevents all natural hostile mob spawns in a shape of a cylinder with a 64 block range and 128 block height.

This torch WON'T prevent mobs spawning from Cursed Earth or other artificial methods like Spawners.
Craft a Spores Recreator! Provide it with any of the two vanilla Mushrooms and Water to create more!
Craft a Potion Brewer! It can automatically create all the vanilla types of Potions! You'll need some of them in large quantity later on, so I recommend automating this machine sooner than later.
Craft some Basic Pressurized Tubes to transfer Gases with!
