Craft 5 Efficiency and 5 Transfer Rate upgrades from Solar Flux Reborn! You can insert at most 20 Efficiency and 10 Transfer Rate Upgrades into 1 Solar Panel. 20 Efficiency Upgrades will double the power generation, and 10 Transfer Rate Upgrades will multiply the RF transfer rate by 2.5.
Craft a Tier 1 Solar Panel from Solar Flux Reborn! It can generate an incredible 1 RF/tick in the daytime.
Craft a Lava Fabricator! When provided with power, it'll simply create Lava! Though it uses a lot of RF, so pumping some hot stuff from the Nether might still be a better option for you.
Upgrade your Pressized Tubes all the way to the Ultimate variant! They can transfer slightly over 4 Buckets of Gas per tick, or over 80 Buckets per second!

All energy relays can wireless transmit power over 15 blocks, and through any material.
The basic relay can transfer 1000 RF/tick.

Its time to use the Empowerer to empower your Crystals! Place the Crystal you want to empower on the Empowerer, and the other four items on Display Stands:

- for Redstonia Crystal: Signalum Gear, Redstone Alloy Ingot, Bricks, Infernal Bulb

- for Palis Crystal: Lead Gear, Prismarine Shard, Moonglow Leaf, Enderium Base

- for Void Crystal: Dark Bimetal Gear, Invar Gear, Flint, Charcoal

-for Enori Crystal: Iron Gear, Steel Gear, Snow, Silicon

- fpr Glod Crystal: Lumium Gear, Energized Bimetal Gear, Wildewheat, Blaze Rod

- for Diamantine Crystal: Platinum Gear, Vivid Alloy Ingot, Cloud Berry, Clay

-for Emeraldic Crystal: Vibrant Bimetal Gear, Congealed Slime Block, Spirit Herb, Cactus.
Twice the range. Your whole base will be covered!

Charges players within 24 blocks in every direction. Right Click to show its range in-world.

No, you cannot use it to shock someone else.
You can place one of these on each side of the Enchanced Wireless Charging Antenna, doubling its charging distance in that direction. Cannot be placed on the bottom.

The Staff of Traveling allows you to teleport a couple blocks forward, at the cost of power.
Do note that you will still suffer from fall damage if you are not careful.

It can also teleport you up to 200 blocks to a Travel Anchor, so long as the Travel Anchor is loaded.

Imbue Soularium with some Dark Steel and a bit of Elevation.

What do you mean you can't?
Fine, just use an ingot of Elevatium.

Craft an Empowerer and 4 Display Stands! The Display Stands you have crafted must be placed exactly 3 blocks away from the Empowerer along the four cardinal directions.
The Empowerer is a crafting system that consumes power and specialized items from the display stands in a display of light, empowerering the item atop the Empowerer.
Using your Advanced Coil, craft a Single Battery and upgrade to a Double Battery!

Using the Atomic Reconstructor you can convert:
Quartz Block -> Ethetic Quartz
Chiseled Quartz Block -> Ethetic Green Quartz

Each tier of jetpack has a higher power storage capacity, faster vertical movement, and faster horizontal movement than the previous. There is no difference in functionality within a tier. You can upgrade a jetpack with armor plating so it will also provide armor to you.
Look at your keybinds for Simply Jetpacks 2 to change the default settings of your jetpack.

IMPORTANT: You can still take fall damage. Tapping space just before you would land cancels this, but may not be doable if there is any amount of lag.


Atricos won't check here, please help I'm trapped and he's forcing me to write some of these! ONLY YOU CAN SAVE ME!

Each tier of jetpack has a higher power storage capacity, faster vertical movement, and faster horizontal movement than the previous. There is no difference in functionality within a tier. You can upgrade a jetpack with armor plating so it will also provide armor to you.
Look at your keybinds for Simply Jetpacks 2 to change the default settings of your jetpack.

IMPORTANT: You can still take fall damage. Tapping space just before you would land cancels this, but may not be doable if there is any amount of lag.
It works similarly to the basic Item Laser Relay, except it now has a GUI that opens when you click it, allowing you to filter input and output items with precision.

When attached to inventories, the Item Laser Relay can see all the items inside.
You can link different Item Laser Relays with 15 blocks of each other together to form a network.
This network will do nothing, however, until you attach it to an Item Interface.

The Fishing Net is a passive auto-fisher.
To get it to work you'll need to place it above water, and either place an inventory above it for it to eject items into or some type of vacuum to pick up the items it spews onto the ground. No power required!

The Flux-Infused JetPlate can hold up to 50 Million RF, can fly horizontally and vertically even faster than previous jetpacks, gives a large amount of armor, and can change held items. 
Look at your keybinds for Simply Jetpacks 2 to change the default settings of your JetPlate.

IMPORTANT: You can still take fall damage. Tapping space just before you would land cancels this, but may not be doable if there is any amount of lag.

A crafting ingredient.

The other statement is true.
The Range Upgrade can be used on any Laser to increase its range from 15 to 35. The connection uses the distance of the shortest range, so both ends of the Laser will require this Upgrade.

Its time to craft an Iron Casing to begin your journey into Actually Additions!

Note: Almost all the recipes in the Actually Additions book are not the actual recipes.

The Atomic Reconstructor fires lazers that atomically reconstuct what they hit. This works on multiple stacks of items at once, but requires power for each item converted.
By default, it will auto-fire once every few seconds. Right click with a redstone torch to toggle its activation mode.
The Atomic Reconstructor can alter many items, and it is best to check JEI to get the full list.
Alloy up a Vivid Alloy Ingot, Grains of Piezallity, and an Elevatium Ingot to get a wonderful Crystalline Alloy Ingot.

Once, long ago, there was a story about a magical material that could contain near infinite power.
That's not this material, this one just hovers a bit...

But, you'll need a lot of it throughout the pack, and there are progressively easier recipes for it that get unlocked in the following Chapters. For now, you'll need to use the Atomic Reconstructor recipe.

Without being bound to a block, Phatomfaces do nothing!
For the low, low price of a Right Click on the target block and a Shift+Right Click on the Phantomface you desire, you can have them actually do something!

The Phantomface works as a remote access point for an inventory within 16 blocks.
Manipulation of items maintains its directionality.
You can place up to three Phantom Boosters on top of the Phantomface to increase its range up to a maximum of 128 blocks.

Each tier of jetpack has a higher power storage capacity, faster vertical movement, and faster horizontal movement than the previous. There is no difference in functionality within a tier. You can upgrade a jetpack with armor plating so it will also provide armor to you.
Look at your keybinds for Simply Jetpacks 2 to change the default settings of your jetpack.

IMPORTANT: You can still take fall damage. Tapping space just before you would land cancels this, but may not be doable if there is any amount of lag.

You're beautiful, like Bundles in the Sky...

Empower your Crystal Bundle further! Maximum Empowerment!

The Experience Solidifier can turn your experience into solidified lumps of goo.
You can consume this Solidified Experience by Right Clicking it, and can consume a whole stack if you also hold Shift.
Though seeing as you've already been rewarded quite a lot of this stuff, you probably know how to use it.
Though with this machine you can automate the creation of this goo and use it to empower some Crystal Bundles!
Craft a Crystal Bundle!

Each tier of jetpack has a higher power storage capacity, faster vertical movement, and faster horizontal movement than the previous. There is no difference in functionality within a tier. You can upgrade a jetpack with armor plating so it will also provide armor to you.
Look at your keybinds for Simply Jetpacks 2 to change the default settings of your jetpack.

IMPORTANT: You can still take fall damage. Tapping space just before you would land cancels this, but may not be doable if there is any amount of lag.

Look at your keybinds for Simply Jetpacks 2 to change the default settings of your jetpack.

Not all the glitters is Glod...

Look at your keybinds for Simply Jetpacks 2 to change the default settings of your jetpack.

Each tier of jetpack has a higher power storage capacity, faster vertical movement, and faster horizontal movement than the previous. There is no difference in functionality within a tier. You can upgrade a jetpack with armor plating so it will also provide armor to you.
Look at your keybinds for Simply Jetpacks 2 to change the default settings of your jetpack.

IMPORTANT: You can still take fall damage. Tapping space just before you would land cancels this, but may not be doable if there is any amount of lag.

Link using the Telepad Linking Card. Does not take power, but only teleports players on it when it gets a redstone signal.
Does not work across dimensions.

The Telepad Block is a 3x3 multiblock that consumes power and Dew of the Void to teleport you anywhere. To specify the place, use the resulting Location Printout from using the Coordinate Selector at your desired coordinates. To store more than one place, use the Dialing Device.
This also works as a Travel Anchor.

Craft an Item Interface! This block is capable of interacting with all Chests or other storage devices that have Item Laser Relays connected to them. You can use any pipe that can push or pull into the Item Interface or any connected Chest to wirelessly transfer items between the two. The more Chests connected, the more storage space you can access with the Item Interface. In that sense, it's like an ever-expanding Chest!
Bind to a Telepad by Shift+Right Clicking it, and hold Right Click to return to the Telepad. Costs power and Dew of the Void for each operation.
Right Click on a QuantumFlux Teleporter to remember it, and Right Click on a different QuantumFlux Teleporter to link them together.

Craft both tiers of Fortune Augments! To have Fortune Two enabled, you must also have Fortune One.

It works just like normal Fortune, okay?

The Drill is a mining tool that mines with the effectiveness of both a Shovel and a Diamond Pickaxe. It uses 100 RF per block mined, and has a number of possible upgrades, including speed and fortune.
Shift+Right Click with the Drill in hand to view your upgrades and upgrade slots.

The Powered Spawner is an incredibly powerful block, but it takes some effort to use.
First, capture a mob of your choice you want to auto-spawn in a Soul Vial. Then, bind the mob in the Soul Vial to a Broken Spawner through a Soul Binder. Now, combine the rebound Broken Spawner with a Powered Spawner in an anvil. Finally, place the Powered Spawner down, put a capacitor in it (the capacitor will affect the speed and quantity of mobs spawned), and provide it power.
Probably want to do this where the mobs will get automatically killed. Would hate to see another world explode due to an insane amount of mobs.

A crafting ingredient.

The other statement is false.

Travel Anchors are blocks that allow easy teleportation between them by shifting or jumping. They have a maximum range of 100 blocks.
You can change its name and how it appears by Right Clicking on it.
They do not require power for any operation.
The 4th and 5th tiers of capacitors. These can be inserted into any EnderIO machine that accepts capacitors, and greatly buffs its effects, speed, and power capacity.
Can store and teleport players to multiple places through the Telepad placed in its range.

Craft all 3 tiers of Drill Speed Augments! To have Speed Two enabled, you must also have Speed One. The same is true for Speed Three with Speed Two.
Each Speed Augment increases the power usage per block and increases the speed of the Drill. At Speed Three, you instantly mine stone, but consume 400 RF per block mined.
Craft some specialized versions of the Phantomface! These work the same way, but with Power, Fluids, or Redstone Signal instead.

Each tier of jetpack has a higher power storage capacity, faster vertical movement, and faster horizontal movement than the previous. There is no difference in functionality within a tier. You can upgrade a jetpack with armor plating so it will also provide armor to you.
Look at your keybinds for Simply Jetpacks 2 to change the default settings of your jetpack.

IMPORTANT: You can still take fall damage. Tapping space just before you would land cancels this, but may not be doable if there is any amount of lag.

The Laser Wrench allows you to link Lasers of the same type.
It can also disconnect, but what monster would want to do that?
Allows you to witness the majesty of the end, in block form.
Phantom Boosters can be placed on top of a number of blocks, increasing their range for each placed atop it, to a maximum of three.
Allows for inter-dimension transportation of power, fluid, and items. Requires a capacitor to function.

The Dark Soularium JetPlate can hold up to 50 Million RF, can fly horizontally and vertically even faster than previous jetpacks, gives a large amount of armor, and can change held items. 
Look at your keybinds for Simply Jetpacks 2 to change the default settings of your JetPlate.

IMPORTANT: You can still take fall damage. Tapping space just before you would land cancels this, but may not be doable if there is any amount of lag.

Using the Atomic Reconstructor you can convert:
Redstone -> Redstonia Crystal
Lapis -> Palis Crystal
Coal -> Void Crystal
Iron -> Enori Crystal
Gold -> Glod Crystal
Diamond -> Diamantine Crystal
Emerald -> Emeraldic Crystal
The Portable Teleporter is a hand-held device that allows you to teleport to any already existing Teleporter

The Mekanism Teleporter is a 4x3 mulitblock structure, with the Teleporter block in the middle on the bottom, and a hollow 2x1 in the middle for the player to walk though.
It works like the channel system you are familiar with in the rest of Mekanism, and requires power.

Craft both tiers of Drill Mining Augments! To have 5 by 5 enabled, you must also have 3 by 3.
As expected, 3 by 3 and 5 by 5 increase the mining size of the Drill. They also increase the RF per block cost, and decrease mining speed.
When mining downwards with the 5 by 5, it will only mine one lower, instead of two.
You can hold Shift to only mine one block.

When using this with a piece of paper in your inventory, it creates a Location Printout, which can then be used in the Telepad or a Dialing Device to teleport to that location.
Make sure to name it something that you will understand later.
Wrap some Crystaline Brown Slime Ingots around your new Enori Crystal - who knows what it will make?

betterquesting:10.name:8: Worry not: Items on the way!
betterquesting:10.desc:8:
If the player that placed the Player Interface down is within 32 blocks, Power can be inserted into the block to charge items in the players inventory, and items can be inserted and extracted, starting with the hotbar.
You can place up to three Phantom Boosters on top of the Player Interface to increase its range up to a maximum of 256 blocks.
These conduits will allow you to transfer even more power!

Upgrade your Energy Laser Relay all the way to the Extreme variant! All Energy Relays can wirelessly transmit power over 15 blocks, and through any material.
The Advanced relay can transfer 10,000 RF/tick.
The Extreme Relay can transfer 100,000 RF/tick.

Craft a Block Placing Augment for the Drill! Before inserting this upgrade into the Drill, Right Click with it. When inside the Drill, Right Clicking with the Drill will attempt to place any block that is in that slot of your hotbar. Now you'll never need to stop holding your beloved Drill!
Go universal and craft some Cosmic Alloy!

Soul Vial but even better.
Make an Ender Lasso.
Active an Advanced End Core by right-clicking on an End Crystal in The End.
Craft the Resistive Heater to turn energy into heat! This machine is required to provide heat for the Thermoelectric Boiler multiblock.

Make the Thermal Evaporation Plant multiblock to get some Brine!

To make the multiblock, build a 4x4x3 cube of the Thermal Evaportation Blocks but leave the middle and top 3 block empty so you form a bucket shape. This is the minimum size of the multiblock but it can be as tall as 18 blocks!

The Thermal Evaporation Valve and Thermal Evaporation Controller can be place on any side of the multiblock, as long as it's not in a corner.

Water can be pumped into the multiblock through a valve and to extract the brine you will need another valve to do so.

The temperature inside the multiblock depends on the biome you're in, so if you're in a snow biome, your productivity will be lower than if you were in a desert.

Craft even more generators!

You also need to be careful with some of these.
The Explosive Generator will, you guessed it, explode continuously while active, causing massive damage to anyone nearby. These explosions will not destroy the surrounding blocks.

The Halitosis Generator is also a nasty piece of work. It will spawn Ender Mites randomly while active, so watch out for those!

Craft 4 Steaming Redstonia Crystals in the Pressurized Reaction Chamber. You'll get Steam from your Thermoelectric Boiler multiblock and DT-Fuel by combining Deuterium and Tricium. Don't forget: You can obtain Deuterium by using an Electric Pump on Water with a Filter Upgrade, and Tritium from Lithium using a Solar Neutron Activator. Be aware that Steam is considered as a liquid, while DT-Fuel as a gas.
I would recommend automating each step of this process as best as you can.
Mesh your Iridium with your Osmium to make Osmiridium, and then trial and error it into a Methodology Processor.
Craft a White Laser Lens for your Laser Drill and start drilling for some Iridium!

Craft a Chemical Dissolution Chamber and a Chemical Washer to make slurries of your ores and get rid of all their impurities!

This will allow you to get 5 times the ingots from an ore!

A Handy Bag can store items based on its card size in each of its 27 slots.
Requires a memory card to function.
Can hold 4 memory cards.

Ender Pouches can be used to transmit items across dimensions and any amount of space.
Sync them by using the same dyes on them, and make them private with a diamond.
Ender Pouches use the same system as the Ender Chest, and when shift right-clicking on one, copy its dyes.

Craft a Laser Base and 4 Laser Drills and start drilling for some valuable ores!

Place the Laser Base anywhere, it does NOT have to "see" bedrock. Place the 4 Laser Drills 1 block away on each side of the Laser Base with the back towards the Laser Base.

Laser Lenses can be used to increase or decrease the chances of getting specific ores!
The Interface Terminal allows you to see the inventories of all of your ME Interfaces in one UI.
The ME Interface allows for automating patterns, which can be used in conjunction with Molecular Assemblers or any other way of processing items, such as smelting.
The fluid interface allows multiple fluid imports and exports into the system.

Blank Patterns can be converted into Patterns for a specific process (crafting or otherwise) through the Pattern Terminal. Placing them in an ME Interface will allow your system to do this process on demand.

Most Mekanism machines have multiple tiers. Higher tiers are called factories, and have a greater number of slots to for it to be processed.
Tier 1 has 1 slot
Tier 2 has 3 slots
Tier 3 has 5 slots
Tier 4 has 7 slots

Ender Chests can be used to transmit items across dimensions and any amount of space.
Sync them by using the same dyes on them, and make them private with a diamond.

Get ready to build the Thermoelectric Boiler multiblock and generate steam using one of the Heaters. 

You can either follow the description down below or watch this video turorial on how to build it. The build tutorial starts at 1:25 and ends at 3:00: https://youtu.be/WgLGOA9UztI?t=85

Description will be of the smallest possible Thermoelectric Boiler multiblock, a 3x3x4.

Make a 3x3 base/platform of the Boiler Casings.
Place a Superheating Element on the middle block (when making a larger boiler, you can add more Superheating Elements to the layer, as long as they are touching each other side to side).
Place Boiler Casings around the Superheating Element. You can use Structural Glass instead of Boiler Casings anywhere but the corner/edge blocks.
Place a Pressure Disperser under the "roof" of the boiler, in this case it's on top of the Superheating Element, and surround it the same way as the Superheating Element, with either Boiler Casings or Structural Glass.
Add a final layer of Boiler Casings on top, making the multiblock 4 blocks tall, and replace 2 Boiler Casings with Boiler Valves, 1 touching the Superheating Element and 1 touching the Pressure Disperser. A flash of redstone particles surrounding the boiler multiblock will indicate that it has formed correctly and you can now access it UI by Right Clicking anywhere on the multiblock.
Pump water into the valve touching the Superheating Element to fill up the boiler with water.
Use either a Fuelwood Heater or a Resistive Heater to add heat to the boiler. The heat cables can be attached anywhere on the boiler except on glass.
Wait for it to reach atleast 100??C and steam will be produced. The steam can be extracted through the valve touching the Pressure Disperser.
Craft the Chemical Infuser and infuse away!

Right-clicking on an End Crystal in The End will convert an Inactive Ender Core into an Active Ender Core.
There are 3 different tiers of Ender Core. Craft an Advanced.

Right click on a mob to pick it up.
Requires a Memory Card Module.

Kids these days, always going "but I need better connectivity" and "I need to use my Wireless Terminal outside the house" - back in my day, we used a payphone and were SATISFIED!
Hmph
Expensive edition.
Contains 9 slots of near-infinite storage. Middle click to keep that slot that item.
Alloy up a few Ender Alloy (Advanced).

Using the Spatial IO Port, you can "capture" and "deploy" areas of the world. The area you capture is limited by the size of your Spatial Storage Cell, and defined by a cuboid structure around the area you want and made up of Spatial Pylons.
Note: Both the Spatial IO Port and Spatial Pylons must be in the same network.

Right-clicking on an End Crystal in The End will convert an Inactive Ender Core into an Active Ender Core.
There are 3 different tiers of Ender Core. Craft an Enhanced.

Craft some generators!

Be careful though, the Netherstar Generator will give you the Wither II debuff if you're nearby while it's running and the Death Generator will give you a 1 minute debuff that will KILL you when it runs out!

Craft 4 Lithium Dust!

This can be done by putting brine in the Thermal Evaporation Plant instead of water.

The result of this is Liquid Lithium which you will then have to decondensentrate with the Rotary Condensentrator to make it a gas.

You then need to run the Lithium gas through a Chemical Crystallizer to get Lithium Dust.

Craft the Ender Porcupine and access your blocks and items wirelessly!

Acts similarly to AA's Phantomfaces and consumes 1 GP per block away from the block being wirelessly accessed.
Alloy up a few Ender Alloy (Enhanced).

Right-clicking on an End Crystal in The End will convert an Inactive Ender Core into an Active Ender Core.
There are 3 different tiers of Ender Core. Craft a Basic.
Memory Card (items) 6 B allows inventory slots to hold 64 items.
Will allow a Wireless Terminal that is linked to your ME network through a Security Terminal to access the network.

The Crafting Card can be placed in Export Buses to allow it to request items to be crafted from your system. It can also be used in Interfaces for much the same purpose, and can also be used in Level Emitters to detect when an item is being crafted.
Alloy up a few Ender Alloy (Basic).
The Molecular Assembler can autocraft recipes for your AE2 system if adjacent to an ME Interface with the a pattern inside of it.
One of the few ways to charge your Ender Capacitors, the Ender Infuser consumes Ender Pearls to give 1000 charge and Eyes of Ender to give 2000 charge.
Able to hold a maximum charge of 10,000, the Ender Capacitor (Basic) is your first step into Ender Utilities Power.

betterquesting:10.name:8: Don't be dumb, make a drum
betterquesting:10.desc:8: Craft a Demonically Garganguan Drum. It stores 65,536 buckets of fluid.

Make a Wand of the Lazy Builder. And then have a brain aneurysm trying to read and comprehend what it can do.

Sorry about that.

Craft the last generators from Extra Utilities 2!

The only effect among these generators is the Frosty Generator putting snow onto the ground.
Craft a Rainbow Block using the Resonator while the Rainbow Generator is running.

Craft the Rainbow Generator!

The Generator will produce 25 million RF/t if you have all the other 16 generators running at the same time! This will only work if the same player places all the 16 different generators.

You will also need the Rainbow Generator running to be able to craft Rainbow Blocks.
The Builders Wand and the Destruction Wand are unbreakable.

Ender Fluid tanks can be used to transmit fluids across dimensions and any amount of space.
Sync them by using the same dyes on them, and make them private with a diamond.

Used in conjunction with the Spatial IO Port to "capture" and "deploy" areas of the world. Place the Spatial Pylons as the rim of a cuboid structure, surrounding the area you want to capture.
This means a 3x3x3 structure will capture the one block inside it.
If assembled properly, the Spatial Pylons with glow purple.
In this you can convert Blank Patterns into Patterns for a specific item. Click the button below the scroll bar to toggle the pattern mode between Crafting and Processing.
The Ender Inhibitor prevents Endermen or other similar entities from teleporting while within its radius - a must-have for a mob farm.

The Crafting CPU is a multiblock made up of at least one Crafting Storage (of any size), and is a cuboid shape that can contain Crafting Storages, Crafting Monitors, and Crafting Co-Processing Units.
The Crafting Monitor will allow you to track the progress of the top level item the multiblock is crafting.
Stores up to a 2x2x2 area as a cell.

The Crafting CPU is a multiblock made up of at least one Crafting Storage (of any size), and is a cuboid shape that can contain Crafting Storages, Crafting Monitors, and Crafting Co-Processing Units.
The Crafting Co-Processing Units increase the number of simultaneous crafting orders your multiblock can do.
Stores up to a 128x128x128 area as a cell.
Stores up to a 16x16x16 area as a cell.

A Handy Chest (Large) can store items based on its card size in each of its 54 slots.
Requires a memory card to function.
Can hold 4 memory cards.

Craft a Wireless RF Transmitter from Extra Utilities! When supplied with power, it redistributes the power wirelessly within a 4 block radius. No more cables! It's pretty handy. Simply Right Click it to turn it on or off.

Craft a Solar Neutron Activator and make the sun do all the work for you, well, not really but some of it! This machine is required to convert your Lithium into Tritium, one of the ingredients for DT-Fuel.
Crystals are frequently used as modules. Install them through the Tool Workstation.
Able to hold a maximum charge of 500,000, the Ender Capacitor (Advanced) is the final tier of Ender Utilities power capacitors.
Able to hold a maximum charge of 100,000, the Ender Capacitor (Enhanced) will serve you well.

To make a Quantum Bridge, you need to have two locations that have a ME Quantum Link Chamber surrounded by a ring of 8 ME Quantum Rings.
Then, you need to place bound Quantum Entangled Singularies inside both of them. A pair of Quantum Entangled Singularies are created by causing an explosion near an Ender Dust and a Singularity.
Once you have all of this, both sides need to be powered, and only then will your network connect to both sides, and even then only for as long as both sides are chunkloaded.


Or just run spaghetti cables everywhere, its your base not mine!

Memory Card (items) 12 B allows inventory slots to hold 4096 items.


No thats not overpowered, why would you ask that?
Craft 6 Basic Thermodynamic Conductors.

The Crafting CPU is a multiblock made up of at least one Crafting Storage (of any size), and is a cuboid shape that can contain Crafting Storages, Crafting Monitors, and Crafting Co-Processing Units.
The various Crafting Storages increase the complexity of the crafting chain that can be followed, with larger Crafting Storages increasing it more.

The Dolly can pick up and move any block with an inventory, free of cost.
The Cardboard Box can move any block. Shift right-click to take the box off the block.
Upgrade your Basic Thermodynamic Conductors all the way to the Ultimate Tier!
Says it all on the tin - its a reusable Ender Pearl. Make one.

betterquesting:10.name:8: Mod your mod, with this mod
betterquesting:10.desc:8:
Ender Utilities is a very intricate mod. You should read the tooltips for the various items to learn more than this book says.
Oh, and remember to set your "Toggle Mode" key to something you'll remember.

Can't fit all your POWAH in those pesky and small Energy Cubes and Cells? Well look no further, the Induction Matrix is just the thing for you! It can get as big as 18x18x18 and is highly configurable to fit your liking!

The smallest the Induction Matrix can be is 3x3x4 and it has to be a rectangular prism.

To build this, start off by placing a 3x3 base of Induction Casings anywhere you would like.
Now take your Basic Induction Cell and Basic Induction Provider and place one of them on the middle block and the other on top of that.
Now incase those 2 blocks with the rest of the Induction Casings and add the 2 Induction Ports on any face that is not a corner or edge block.
This will form the multiblock and a redstone particle effect will show you have done it correctly. The Induction Ports act as input and output for power and this can be toggled with the Configurator by shift+clicking a port. Green means input and red means output.

The Induction Matrix is highly configurable, meaning the bigger you make the multiblock, the more Induction Cells and Induction Providers you can fit in it, though at minimum you need 1 Induction Cell and 1 Induction Provider for the multiblock to form.
The Induction Cells increase the total energy capacity of the Induction Matrix and the Induction Providers increase the power output and input rate.
Both the Induction Cell and the Induction Provider have 4 variant. Basic, Advanced, Elite and Ultimate.
The better the tier the more efficient it will be.

You do not need to fill out the entire inner area with Induction Cells and Induction Providers though it is recommended to maximize its capability.

Craft a Mechanical User!

This block works like the Autonomous Activator from 1.7.10, such that it can simulate a player's Right/Left Click. You can configure a lot in its UI!
Can store and remember 54 stacks of items. When a remembered stack is depleted, a ghost type of that item will appear, keeping the spot allocated to that item.

Craft the Quantum Entangloporter!

It acts like a Tesseract, it feels like a Tesseract, so is it a Tesseract?

No! This one can transfer gasses too!

Can transfer energy/items/fluids/gasses over long distances from 1 Entangloporter to another on the same channel. It also has a distinct advantage over the Dimensional Transceiver, as it can transport way more RF/tick. I recommend using this for pretty much every long-range project.

Craft a Quantum Quarry and 6 Quantum Quarry Actuators to start mining in a hypothetical dimension that may have existed!

Place the Quantum Quarry anywhere and place the Quantum Quarry Actuators on each of the Quantum Quarry's 6 sides. Doing this will form the multiblock quarry.

Power can be input on any face of the multiblock and right+clicking it will open its UI.

20.000 RF is used per block mined and items are output to any inventory touching a face of the multiblock

In the UI you can add a filter to either whitelist or blacklist items. Items blacklisted or not whitelisted will still be mined and consume power but will be destroyed.

You can also add an enchanted book to the quarry i.e. Fortune or Silk Touch.

The last slot is for Biome Markers. These markers will decide which biome the quarry mines in, so say you put in an Extreme Hills Biome Marker, you would get emeralds and so on.

The quarry can run without any of these addons but they are highly recommended!

Craft the Dragon Egg Mill and place a Dragon Egg on top of it to potentially generate 5000 GP!

(This generator has been buffed and it generates 10 times the normal amount.)
Using the various materials you've gathered so far, upgrade your Necronomicon to its Abyssal Wastelands version. This will unlock new chapters and allow it to store more Potential Energy.
Rend them down, get an Abyssal Wasteland Essence.

betterquesting:10.name:8: Don't like where this is going.
betterquesting:10.desc:8: Its a 5x5 crafting table, oh so full of joy, why don't you try it - this is no sinister ploy!
Its a 3x3 crafting table that won't let you craft anything new, ask your doctor if "Basic Crafting Table" is right for you.
Now that you've killed The Watcher, rip out its eye.
The second Boss of DivineRPG, The Watcher is powerful flying boss that is spawned in the Nether by Right Clicking with the Call of the Watcher.
Simply better versions of the normal Potential Energy manipulators.

Potential Energy manipulation. Both useless without a Necronomicon AND actually explained there.
Check Potential Energy/Special Materials.

betterquesting:10.name:8: From me to you, with magic
betterquesting:10.desc:8: The Transmutor is a furnace style machine, requiring unique fuel and transmuting one item into another at a slow pace.
After crafting the gateway key, right clicking on the ground with it will generate a portal that will take you to the Abyssal Wasteland.

Combining 4 Shards of Oblivion and 4 Melodic Capacitors into an Active Ender Core (Advanced), at the cost of 5000 Potential Energy and the sacrifice of an animal will gain you the Oblivion Catalyst.

Also multiple headaches and visions of eldritch gods. Don't worry about those.

Craft up 14 Eden Blocks. Make a Nether Portal shape out of them. Light with the Twilight Clock.
Welcome to the Wildwood.



















I'm out the portal again,
So hopped up to the wild ahead.
Two time!
Stay friends,
Problem that I'm not prepared!

Hands up, feel okay,
Which mob should I slay today?
Two time!
Stay frends,
Problem that I can't defend!
Mine up the Dreadlands Infused Powerstone found where you would find the End Portal in a normal Stronghold.

Using the full power of your recently upgraded Necronomicon, summon and beat Asorah, The Fallen.

You can find the Ritual in your Abyssal Wasteland Necronomicon, under the Rituals / Abyssal Wasteland section, named Ritual of the Sleeper.

After killing the Sunstorm, make sure to surgically remove its heart.


All you need is love!
Wildwood dungeon stuff
Atomically Reconstruct Canola Seeds, and then toss it into Refined Canola in an In-World Fluid Crafting operation.

Craft a Black Iron Frame!


You're totally going to use it for lighting.
Eden dungeon stuff
Eden dungeon stuff

The Shard of Oblivion captures just a bit of madness within its glowing red surface. Sometimes you can see the madness writhe.


Make 4 of them.
Most notable for being able to make the Shard of Oblivion, the Transmutation Gem is a 10-use crafting item.
Wildwood Dungeon stuff
After alloying up a Chunk of Coralium, smelt it down into two Refined Coralium Ingots.

Hold Right click while looking at an Abyssal mob to rend it and generate Energy based on the type of mob. When you reach the cap, your Staff will helpfully convert that into an essence item based on what you were rending.

The Abyssal Stronghold that these lead too functions similarly to the normal Stronghold in the overworld, and these special eyes will lead you there. Make 6 of them.

Note that the reward can only be gained through a harvest level 5 pickaxe, so you will need to find a way to get that.
No Description
Craft up 4 Coralium Infused Stone and smelt them down into 4 Coralium Pearls. These will be used to craft a large number of things.
Make 4 Monolith Stone Pillars. These increase the range your statues can transmit Potential Energy from.

Gather up one of each of the Abyssal Statues - check to be sure you're making the real ones and not just the decorative ones.

Once you have the Necronomicon, the Potential Energy chapter will be of use, as it describes it with pictures!
asd

I'm not going insane... am I? Who was that man with the shadowed face? What was that sound from my neighbor's attic? What leaves those scars on my door? What are those eyes that aren't eyes that move and writhe I see when I dream? Shoggoths aren't real... right?

Craft some Monolith Stones! This material is used heavily in AbyssalCraft recipes, so you might want to craft multiple batches.

Note: This is normally found in Shoggoth Lairs throughout the world, however they have been disabled in this pack due to Shoggoths being incredibly destructive.
Using the various materials you've gathered so far, upgrade your Necronomicon to its Dreadlands version. This will unlock new chapters and allow it to store more Potential Energy.
Rend them down, get a Dreadlands Essence.

Kill some Dreadguards and get their Dreaded Shards of Abyssalnite, then transmute them into Dreadium Ingots.

You'll want Fire Resistance.

Craft up a Wildwood Chunk. When used on a Termasect Spawner, it will summon the Termasect, a 1050 health flying ranged boss. Note that this will not remove the spawner, so you can use the same location multiple times - just be sure not to break it!
Asorah's Dreaded Gateway Key will give you access to the Dreadlands, but only if used in the Abyssal Wastelands.
I'm sure you've got the hang of it by now. Just get the heart.
The first multiboss of DivineRPG, The Ayeraco Horde is 5 boss-like creatures, all spawned in the End at the same time by the Horde Horn.
The first Boss of DivineRPG, The Ancient Entity is powerful melee boss. Spawned in the Overworld by Right Clicking with the Mysterious Clock.

The Twilight Clock is used to light portals for the DivineRPG dimensions of: Eden, Wildwood, Apalachia, Skythern, and Mortum.
Used like Flint and Steel.




Don't stop, make it pop,
DJ2, I'll beat you now,
Tonight, I'mma fight,
'Till we see the sunlight,
Tick tock!
On the clock,
But the modpack don't stop, no

Ouh, ouh-ouh, oh!
Ouh, ouh-ouh, oh!

Using your Abyssal Statues, craft the Necronomicon, the guidebook to madness. This won't consume the input statues!

When holding the Necronomicon near Abyssal Statues, potential energy will burst out of the statues and into the book.
NOTE: The destructive effects have been removed, and it is now entirely safe.

To find Shadow Gems and Shadow Fragments, visit a Darklands Plains, Hills or Forest biome at night. Capture a Shadow Beast or Shadow Creature and Powered Spawn them for more.
Empower Canola Seeds, and then toss them into Crystallized Oil in an In-World Fluid Crafting operation.
Black Iron Ingots are used for almost everything Extended Crafting. Craft 4 to get started!

Pour Liquid Antimatter (found underground in Coralium Infested Swamps) on top of Liquid Coralium (found in the Abyssal Wastelands), and mine up 10 of the Coralium Stone that results from this.

If you can't find Liquid Antimatter, you can summon an Anti Cow using the Anti Milking Ritual in the Abyssal Wasteland.
Now that you've beaten The Ayeraco Horde, tear off their wings.
The world is a wonderful yellow shade. I wonder how much your eyes hurt?
Build it like a nether portal and light it with The Twilight Clock.
Carefully placing 4 Coralium Bricks around a Monolith Stone will give you Coralium Bricks. Make 10 of them.
Many things in Abyssalcraft require a high mining level. The Refined Coralium Pickaxe provides a harvest level 5 pickaxe, which is required for the next quest, the Dreadlands Infused Powerstone.
Even better than the overworld Potential Energy blocks.

Craft up an Eden Chunk. When used on a Sunstorm Spawner, it will summon the Sunstorm, a 1000 health ranged boss. Note that this will not remove the spawner, so you can use the same location multiple times - just be sure not to break it!

The Dreadlands Staff of Rending generates 3 Energy per rend.

Note that your held Energy will be lost when upgrading your Staff.

betterquesting:10.name:8: All the crazy things I did in this Chapter...
betterquesting:10.desc:8:
All the crazy things I did tonight...
Lead up to crafting a Dread Crystal.
I just wanna let it go for the night...
Before it comes and my armhairs bristle.

The Abyssal Wastelands Staff of Rending generates 2 Energy per rend instead of just 1.

Note that your held Energy will be lost when upgrading your Staff.
Now that you've killed The Ancient Entity, break off its legs.

Craft a Docking Station! This machine lets you place your Dank Nulls on the ground, and lets you use them as a container. The Emerald (Mk. VI) Dank Null can be used as a 54-slot Black Hole Unit this way!
Craft one of each of the Tier 3 Essences. This requires at least the Magician Blood Orb, although higher tiers can be used.
Craft one of each of the Tier 2 Essences. This requires at least the Apprentice Blood Orb, although higher tiers can be used.
The Magician's Blood Orb fills your personal network up to 150,000 LP.

Craft 24 Stone Brick Paths, and place them down in 2x3s extending from the Wooden Paths. They are valid up to one block above or below the level of the Wooden Paths. In the new 64 blocks of valid space, place various crops and other natural things to increase the amount of Tranquility, up to a maximum of 120. Remember that variation is important, as there is diminishing value from the same type of block.

Craft 36 Wooden Paths, and place them down in 3x3s in each cardinal direction from the Incense Altar, up to one block above or below the original level. In the diagonal 3x3 areas, place various crops and other natural things to increase the amount of Tranquility, up to a maximum of 60. Note that variation is important, as there is diminishing value from the same type of block.

Runes can be used interchangeably with Blank Runes to form a Blood Altar structure.
The Rune of Self Sacrifice increases the amount of LP the player supplies when using a dagger by 10%, additively.
The Speed Rune increases the speed of crafting and filling Blood Orbs happens at by 20%, additively.
Craft a Reinforced Slate in your tier 2 Blood Altar.
Craft the Frozen Blood Core, and weep for what you have wrought.
It grows in them. And it hungers.
Did not break, must investigate further.
Response when fall from big cliff same as #369, #370, #371, #372, and #373. Further investigations still needed.
Craft a Promise of Tenacity III. This can be used in a couple EvilCraft machines, but most importantly in the Blood Infuser, where it unlocks new recipes. Replaces the Promise of Tenacity II.
Craft a Promise of Tenacity II. This can be used in a couple EvilCraft machines, but most importantly in the Blood Infuser, where it unlocks new recipes. Replaces the Promise of Tenacity I.
Using a Promise of Tenacity I, use an Empowered Glod Block with a full tank of Blood to get a Gold Promise Acceptor.
Place down five sources of blood, and toss a Dark Gem into it. It will consume all 5 buckets of blood to produce a single Dark Power Gem.

When killing mobs with a Blood Extractor in your inventory, it will gain blood. The Blood Extractor can be used like a bucket to place down the blood into the world, and can also auto-supply any tank that can hold blood in your inventory. If you combine it with itself it will increase its internal tank.
Create a Soul Forge. It has 4 slots for items to craft, a slot in the center for the crafting result, a bar to display crafting progress, and a space for a Tartaric Gem.
Using Coagulated Blood from Tinkers Construct, make a Hardened Blood Droplet.
Craft a Promise of Tenacity I. This can be used in a couple EvilCraft machines, but most importantly in the Blood Infuser, where it unlocks new recipes.
The Blood Altar consumes Life Essence to convert items. It has multiple tiers, and some recipes are locked behind higher tiers.

betterquesting:10.name:8: They Merge into a Common Soul
betterquesting:10.desc:8: Craft a Common Tartaric Gem, which can hold up to 1024 Demonic Will, unlocking the ability to craft more expensive recipes with it.
Craft a Lesser Tartaric Gem, which can hold up to 256 Demonic Will, unlocking the ability to craft more expensive recipes with it.

Craft an Alchemy Table. The size of two blocks, this has 6 input slots, 1 output slot, and a Blood Orb slot. It requires a bound Blood Orb, and consumes LP from the bound player to craft items. The tier of the Blood Orb affects what items can be crafted.

This will allow you to see Vengeance Spirits, but also allow them to see - and attack - you. If you enable the ring, you get multiple positive effects, but Vengeance Spirits will constantly spawn around you. If the Vengeance Spirit takes a form, you will also be able to kill it with a Piercing Vengeance Focus. Great for farming Vengeance Spirits!
Using a Promise of Tenacity II, use an Empowered Diamantine Block with a full tank of Blood to get a Diamond Promise Acceptor.
Craft a Blood Infuser. This is the fundamental machine in EvilCraft. It can craft more items and store more blood at higher tiers, which are gained through Promises of Tenacity.
Light Hardened Blood on fire to get Hardened Blood Shards, and use these to craft a Blood Infusion Core, the throbbing heart of many EvilCraft machines.
WARNING: DO NOT EAT. Enjoyed by animals about to read a book.

*Not actually the last crafting. Terms and conditions may apply. Extended use may cause excessive particles. Please consult a doctor to see if Ender Crafting is right for you. If crafting lasts longer than 3 minutes contact a doctor and install more Ender Alternators.
Kill an Enderman and have him spawn a Vengeance Spirit, and then use the Vengeance Focus and a Box of Eternal Closure to trap an Enderman to make a Block of Ender.
The Apprentice's Blood Orb fills your personal network up to 25,000 LP.
Craft the Coralium Decorated Blood Star, and scream the madness you hath seen.

Craft 8 Blood Runes, which are used to increase the tier of the Blood Altar. I suggest using the Inspectoris Scandalum to see where to place the blocks. Right click to change the tier it displays, and shift+right click on a Blood Altar to display it.
Sucks up Blood from the ground in puts it into nearby tanks, or, more usefully, when the Spiked Plate does damage to a mob.
Create Dull Dust, and then Infuse it to get Bloodied Dust, an essential crafting component.
Craft one of each of the Tier 1 Reagents.
Craft one of each of the Tier 1 Essences. This requires at least the Weak Blood Orb, although higher tiers can be used.
The Weak Blood Orb fills your personal network up to 5,000 LP. Bind to you by right clicking with it.
Craft a Box of Eternal Closure. By default, it comes with a Vengeance Spirit inside. Place it down and right click on it to open it. Shoot a spirit with a Vengeance Focus to trap it inside the box.
Shooting a Vengeance Spirit won't kill it, but it will weaken it enough that a nearby open Box of Eternal Closure can suck them in.

Craft a Petty Tartaric Gem (I suggest two or three). The Petty Tartaric Gem holds up to 64 Demonic Will, and will automatically absorb Demonic Will you pick up. You can transfer will between Tartaric Gems by holding right click with it in your hand.

Right click to throw a Rudimentary Snare. Any mob it hits will have a chance to gain a particle effect, which will cause the mob to drop Demonic Will.
The value of Demonic Will increases with the health of the mob.
Can stack up to 3 slots of 4 in a single Promise of Tenacity III machine, allowing for incredibly efficient operations.
Your every word a vow, your every breath a promise.
Craft one of each of the Tier 2 Reagents.
At long last, you can kill the Vengeance Spirits. Simply slay vanilla mobs for Vengeance Spirits to spawn, then pew pew them down. They drop extra goodies too!
Using the Sacrificial Dagger near a Blood Altar will reduce your life, and fill up the Blood Altar in exchange.

Craft Arcane Ashes. This 10 durability tool will create an special crafting location when right clicked on the ground. Place two items in it and it will make some cool effects and craft an item, typically a Sigil, for you. Some items will cause it to become an Alchemy Array, which give unique and special effects (look in the guidebook).
Craft one of each of the Tier 3 Reagents.

The Sigil of Divination will allow you to view new information about various Blood Magic blocks when held. Its main uses are finding out how much LP is in your personal network by right clicking, how much Blood is in the Blood Altar, and the Tranquility of an Incense Altar.
You vaguely gesture at the possibility of you following up.
Using the Blood Infuser, use an Empowered Enori Block with a full tank of Blood to get an Iron Promise Acceptor.
Can stack up to 3 slots of 4 in a single Promise of Tenacity III machine, allowing for incredibly fast operations.

Place the Incense Altar on a 3x3 square. By default, it has 20 Tranquility, which will give you a 20% bonus to the value of blood sacrificed when nearby. Your Sacrificial Dagger will become enhanced when this is active, and will take 90% of your health. This has a cooldown of 20 seconds due the Soul Fray effect.

betterquesting:10.name:8: S P E E D W A L K E R
betterquesting:10.desc:8: The Effortless Ring gives auto-step, makes your hunger reduce slower, and makes you walk a bit faster. It can be equipped as a bauble.
After feeding the apple to an animal, let it die and throw a Book onto the resulting particles. This is the guidebook for Evilcraft.

Runes can be used interchangeably with Blank Runes to form a Blood Altar structure.
The Rune of Sacrifice increases the amount of LP the Dagger of Sacrifice (or Well of Suffering later on) supplies by 10%, additively.
The Rune of Capacity increases the capacity of your Blood Altar by 2,000 LP, additively.
Create Imbued Slates using your tier 3 Blood Altar

Craft the Sentient Sword. Mobs killed by the Sentient Sword will always drop Demonic Will. The Sentient Sword, and other Sentient Tools, increase in power the more Demonic Will you have in your largest Tartaric Gem.

Craft a Jingle Dress! Wearing this in your leg slot will increase your musical performance while moving during Rituals.

For more information on Ceremonies, refer to the previous quest!

To complete the quest, craft 2 Totemist Drums! Read on for more information about Musical Instruments and Ceremonies:

To start a Ceremony, you need to be close to a Totem Pole. Place down some Drums (2 is likely enough), lots of Wind Chimes, and hold some musical instruments in your main- and off-hand like a Flute, and later a Rattle and an Eagle-Bone Whistle.

To actually begin a Ceremony, Shift+Right click with or on a musical instrument. Check the Ceremonies Chapter of your Totempedia for a detailed explanation on each Ceremony. It shows yo which instrument(s) you need to Shift+Right Click on, to start a certain Ritual.

The first Ritual it explains is the War Dance. If you haven't played with Totemic yet, I recommend you try it: Shift+Right Click twice on a Drum to start it. Now you'll see two bars on your screen slowly filling up. You need to fill up the top bar, before your time runs out: which is measured on the bottom bar. To use musical instruments, simply Right Click with or on them. You should see the top bar filling up.

If you do it sucessfully, you'll earn the benefits of the given Ritual; in the case of the War Dance, Strength and Speed for 3 minutes.

Failing a Ritual? There can be multiple things going wrong:

1. Each musical instrument has a short cooldown to use, so you can't just spam one Drum and expect the Ritual to complete.

2. Variety helps! Try using a Flute besides the Drum, constantly swapping between the two. Note: You can click the Drum while holding the Flute.

3. For even more complex Ceremonies, try crafting passive music generating instruments: Wind Chimes, as well as a Jingle Dress, which you can move around with to generate more music.

Craft lots of Wind Chimes. Hang them up near your Totem Pole for passive music generation. Watch out though, you should have no blocks beneath a Chime! Chimes also have preferred spots, meaning you can't just place them anywhere. After placing one, try Shift+Right Clicking on one. If it makes a sound: It's a preferred spot. If it doesn't, you'll need to move it for it to have an effect.

Note: The quest only asks for 4 Wind Chimes, however, for better performance, you might need more.

You are now tasked to perform the Rite of Spring while some Saplings are nearby. This will transform these Saplings into Red Cedar Saplings. The Ritual has additional effects, please read up on them in your Totempedia. Once you've obtained at least one Red Cedar Sapling, pick it up to complete this quest. You can now plant these Saplings and grow them normally with Bone Meal, etc.

Note: It is recommended to place some blocks above the affected Saplings, so they don't grow while you're performing the Ritual. Additionally, some modded Saplings do work, some don't. Here is a list of both:

Saplings that CAN be transformed: Minecraft, Natura, AbyssalCraft, Bewitchment, Erebus, Traverse. 

Saplings that CANNOT be transformed: Quark, Tinkers' Slime Saplings, Twilight Forest, Atum 2, Aether Legacy, Roots, DivineRPG, Extra Utilities 2, Thaumcraft.
Now that you have access to Buffalo Teeth, craft a Rattle! By offhanding it or the Flute, you can create even more music for your Rituals!

Now you are tasked to perform the Buffalo Dance Ritual, while having a few Cows nearby in a pen! If performed sucessfully, exactly 2 Cows in the vicinity will transform into Baby Buffalos!

Note: You'll likely need all the previously mentioned instruments to have a chance to complete this Ritual: A Flute, 2 Drums, at least 4 well-placed Wind Chimes and a Jingle Dress.

You can speed up the growth of Baby Buffalos by feeding them Wheat. You can also breed adult Buffalos using Wheat, like you would do with regular Cows. Once you kill an adult Buffalo, and obtain the required items, you can turn in this quest.

----------------------------

"Bison from Buffalo, which other bison from Buffalo confuse, confuse the bison from Buffalo."

or,

"Buffalo buffalo Buffalo buffalo buffalo buffalo Buffalo buffalo."

Craft a Totemic Staff! This tool can be used to Right Click on Totems and Totem Bases to display some information about effects and ongoing Rituals, but more importantly, this tool can be used to stop a Ceremony by Left Clicking on a Totem Base.

Craft a Flute! This can help you with Totemic Ceremonies by generating music via Right Clicks, and you'll need it to start certain Ceremonies by Shift+Right Clicking.

For more information on Ceremonies, refer to the previous quest!

Now you are tasked to perform the Eagle Dance Ritual. This will turn exactly 2 nearby Parrots into Bald Eagles. To complete this quest, unfortunately you'll have to stab-stab or shoot-shoot these wonderful creatures and collect some Eagle Bones and Eagle Feathers!

To more easily find Parrots, they have been added as base spawns to multiple biomes. These include: Arid Highland, Autumnal Wooded Hills, Autumnal Woods, Canyon, Desert Shrubland, Lush Hills, Lush Swamp, Magical Forest, Mini Jungle, Savanna (all variants), Swampland (all variants) & Temperate Rainforest. Additionally, Parrot spawnrates have been increased in all Jungle variants.

Sleepidy sleep! - is what you can do in your new Tipi.

(Or you can alternatively just craft a Bed, if you don't wanna embrace the Totemic lifestyle... Its recipe has also been unlocked by gaining access to Buffalo Hide!)

betterquesting:10.name:8: Can you blow my Whistle baby
betterquesting:10.desc:8: Craft your final musical instrument, an Eagle-Bone Whistle! Now you'll have 3 handheld instruments to swap between. It is recommended to use all of them though, so try to swap between 2 in your main hand while performing Rituals!

Now you are tasked to perform the Serenade of Syrinx. This will infuse any Flute in your inventory with magical powers and turn them into Pan's Flute. Using Pan's Flute you can more easily complete Ceremonies.





Shiny's like a melody in my head
That I can't keep out, got my singin' like:
Na na na na everday
I'm gonna play my flute if I may
I may-ay-ay-ay!

Craft a Medicine Bag! You can use it to Shift+Right Click on any type of Totem, and gain its effect. Then, by Right Clicking with the Medicine Bag, you can change it between an Open and Closed state. While open, the effect is constantly being used up, and while closed, the player won't gain the effect. To recharge the Bag, simply stand near your Totem Pole.

Note: The Ocelot effect cannot be bound to a Medicine Bag.

------------------------
         THIS QUEST IS MAINLY FOR
          INFORMATION ON TOTEMIC
        ------------------------

You can use your Totem Whittling Knife on any vanilla Log block to transform it into a Totem Base.

You can Shift+Right Click or Shift+Scroll Wheel on your Totem Whittling Knife to switch between Totem options. Carve any vanilla Log type (or Red Cedar) above a Totem Base to create a Totem of a specific kind. Totem poles can only be at most 6 blocks high (including the base). Various animals carved out give small area-of-effect buffs (the effect area is an 11x11x11 block cube centered at the Totem Base), similar to a small-range Beacon. To find out what gives what, please read the Totems and Effects -> Totem Effects chapter of your Totempedia.

Totem effects can stack up to the 3rd level of a given effect (like Speed III, Jump Boost III, etc.), if you build a max height Totem of all the same animal tpye. Level II can be achived with 3 totems on the same Totem Pole.

Later you'll be able to craft a Medicine Bag, shift right click on a Totem, and gain its effect while the Medicine Bag is open (for about 4 minutes).

Punch some tall grass to obtain some Terra Spores. Then place down those Terra Spores on vanilla Cobblestone that is right next to a Water source block.

Then craft an Iron Knife to scrape off the Terra Spores and collect the resulting Terra Moss!

Be aware, that later you'll need to completely automate this process (once you have access to an Extra Utilities Mechanical User).

If you can't find regular Cobblestone, you can craft 4 pieces of it from any Underground Biomes Cobblestone type by putting them in a square shape into the Crafting Window.

Note: The quest asks for an Iron Knife, however, you can also use any type of Knife to scrape off the moss.
Craft an Infernal Bulb! Then plant it onto Magmatic Soil to get more! You can only use that type of Soil to plant it on.

Perform the Wildroot Growth Ritual on your Pyre (the Ritual is available from JEI), while one fully grown Wildroot plant is nearby. If done correctly, the Wildroot will convert into a Wildwood Tree! Harvest it to complete this quest.

Note: This tree won't drop Saplings, you'll have to repeat the Ritual to get more.

Note: Only exactly one, namely the closest Wildroot plant will transform.
Snip off some fully grown Wheat using your Runic Shears to obtain Wildewheat! Then covert it into Seeds and plant it to get more! You can plant this on any type of Soil.

Punch some tall grass to have a chance to obtain some Wildroot! They're used pretty heavily in Roots, but fortunately they can be planted and grown as a crop. Alternatively, you can setup an automatic Grass shaker of sorts to obtain more of them.

Then craft a Root of the Fallen using your Baykok's Bow to get into Roots!

Craft a Harvest Spell Dust! When infused onto a Staff, you can Right Click to harvest a huge field of crops! It works best when the Magnetism effect is also infused onto the same Staff, so you can harvest then immediately collect all the drops!

In fact, it works even better if the Rampant Growth effect is also infused onto the same Staff, so you can immediately regrow everything you've just harvested!

Use Charred Stone to Craft a Mortar and a Pestle from Roots! Place down the Mortar, and to use it, place some ingredients inside. To crush the ingredients, simply Right Click with the Pestle.

This is another way to ore-double besides your Smeltery, and you can also turn 1 piece of Wheat into Flour, and later 1 piece of Bread by Smelting. If you want, you can also use it to create String out of Wool, Bone Meal out of Bones, or Sugar out of Sugarcane.
Not with this Stone nearby! Place it near your cropfield, and not only will it provide Water to nearby crops, it will also prevent anyone from trampling them!
Craft 4 blocks of Endervoirs in your Fey Crafter. When placed in a 2x2 multiblock shape, it acts as an infinite water source. You can even pump water out! Try it using the quest rewards!

Runestones! Craft some of them. They're used as crafting components, as well as Standing Stones for Pyre Rituals!

That's right: You can do Rituals using your Pyre. Everything is detailed in your Druidic Arts book (if you've unlocked it). For most Rituals, a pillar Runestones with a Chiseled Runestone on top will be necessary. It doesn't have to be placed exactly where the book shows, just somewhere nearby.

Make a Fey Crafter! This is another central crafting mechanic in Roots. To use it however, you'll need at least one Imbued Grove Stone in the vicinity. To imbue a Grove Stone, Right Click on it with a Staff that has the Grove Supplication Spell.

To use this crafting altar, open its UI and place 5 ingredients inside. Then Right Click on it with any kind of Roots Knife, to complete the craft.

Note: It's currently not possible to automate the Fey Crafter. Because of this, it won't be heavily used for later crafting.
Craft a Fey Light Spell Dust! When infused onto a Staff, you can create small light sources that can just as easily be destroyed too, if you don't want them around anymore.
Craft a Staff from Roots! You can imbue it with up to 5 Magical Spells in an Imbuer.

Craft a Grove Stone! Place it down, then Right Click on it with your Grove Supplication imbued Staff! The Grove Stone will now constantly grow tall grass around it (perfect for a Grass Shaker, but much slower than constantly Bone Mealing the ground). The Grove Stone will also allow nearby Fey Crafters to function.

Note: Don't imbue too many Grove Stones in your world, as they can cause noticeable tick lag, since they constantly try to grow tall grass around them. But 2-3 should have close to no effect on performance.

START WITH THIS SPELL DUST!
---------------------------
Craft a Grove Supplication Spell Dust with your Mortar and Pestle! This can be used to Infuse your Staff on an Imbuer.
Craft all Roots Tools! They all auto-repair, but can also be repaired with any kind of tree Bark!
Shear a fully grown Beetroot plant using your Runic Shears to obtain some Spirit Herb! Then craft it into Seeds to obtain more! You can plant this on any type of Soil.

Use your Pyre to craft 3 Dewgonias! This is the first of many flowers and spell components in Roots.

Once you craft it a single time, you can grow this flower on Aqueous Soil, which you'll have access to soon in this chapter.

Craft a Pyre! This is a central crafting mechanic in Roots. To use it, simply toss the ingredients of Right Click with them on top. To remove the last ingredient, Right Click with an empty hand.

To start any craft, you'll need to light the Pyre with a Flint and Steel. Because of this reason, to be able to do any crafting, you'll need to also start the next chapter: "Immersive Yourself", and start creating Steel!

You can also automate the Pyre by lighting the ground with a Dispenser in the immediate 3x3 area centered around the Pyre.

To stop a given Ritual, you can take a Bucket of Water, and Right Click with it on the Pyre.

Similarly to a Botania Altar, you can Shift+Right Click the Pyre to put another set of the previously used crafting ingredients from your inventory onto the Pyre.

The Pyre can also access a chest immediately below it and pull ingredients from it to keep Rituals going. Check out the Rituals provided by Roots, you'll find a lot of useful ones, like the Healing Aura, Windwall, Animal Harvest, or Summon Creatures! Once you have progressed enough in Roots, you'll unlock the Rituals Chapter in your Druidic Arts book! Make sure to read up on them!
Craft one Cloud Berry! Then plant it onto Caelic Soil to grow more. It can only grow on that specific Soil type.
Craft a Pereskia flower! Then convert it into a Pereskia Bulb, which you can plant on any type of Soil. Grow some additional Pereskias to complete this quest!

Craft a pair of Runic Shears! Using this tool, you can obtain the following 3 items:

- Wildewheat by shearing fully grown Wheat,
- Spirit Herb by shearing a fully grown Beetroot plant
- Fey Leather by shearing cows, llamas, deers, horses and donkeys.
Craft a Shatter Spell Dust! When infused onto a Staff, you can shoot a beam of light that destroys the 2 closests blocks hit! It's perfect for creating small staircases, or for strip mining.
Craft a Radiance Spell Dust! When infused onto a Staff, you can constantly shoot a strong beam of light at your target, which can obliterate your foes! PEW-PEW!

Upgrade your Component Pouch into an Apothecary Pouch! This can hold 9 spell components instead of just 6. At first it might not seem like a huge upgrade, but you actually need just a little bit of extra space to fit all spell components into one bag.

Craft a Component Pouch! You can store any items on the left side, or specific Roots spell components on the right. This will save a couple inventory slots, since Staves can use magical components from this pouch instead of your inventory.

Use the Pyre to create some Charred Stone!

Note: You'll need to progress a bit in "Immerse Yourself!" before you can light your Pyre.

Craft a batch of Elemental Soil! Crops can grow on it just like on Tilled Dirt, and they grow slightly faster than normal. Crops planted on it cannot be trampled, and water doesn't need to be placed in the vicinity for them to grow.
Craft a Magnetism Spell Dust! When infused onto a Staff, you can Right Click to magnetize and pull all nearby items into your inventory. It works like an on-demand Magnet from various tech mods.

Much better than Dirt in fact...! Craft some additional Elemental Soil and upgrade some batches of them to all 4 different types of Elemental Soil:

- Drop it in Water to upgrade it to Aqueous Soil,
- Drop it in Lava to upgrade it to Magmatic Soil,
- Drop it above Y=90 to upgrade it to Caelic Soil,
- Drop it below Y=30 to upgrade it to Terran Soil.

Each type of Soil has its benefits (read their tooltip), and there are certain Roots plants that can only be planted on one of these Soil types.

Note: The effect of the Aqueous Soil can be disabled by placing a piece of Gravel underneath the Soil.

Craft a Wildfire Spell Dust! When infused onto a Staff, you can shoot fire at enemies! This is slightly stronger than Life Drain, but doesn't heal you when used. It's also slightly weaker than Radiance, but sets enemies on fire!

Craft a Sky Soarer Spell Dust! When infused onto a Staff, you can dash ahead or into the air with a Right Click. It also catches your fall - meaning you'll take no fall damage if you quickly use it when you land. It's a perfect way to travel before Jetpacks!

Craft a full set of Sylvan armor! While wearing this, your Roots spells have an 8% chance to consume no spell ingredients from your inventory or Component Pouch.

Additionally, the armor can be repaired using Fey Leather, but it also repairs itself very slowly.

Obtain some Fey Leather using your Runic Shears on:

- a Minecraft Cow, Llama, Horse, Donkey, Mule, or
- a Mystical World Deer.

Bark! Bark!

Use your Knife to obtain some Bark by breaking any type of vanilla Log block!

Craft an Imbuer! You can use it to imbue magical effects onto Roots Staves through Spell Dusts! The first effect you should imbue is the Growth Supplication effect. To do so, simply place down the Imbuer, put the Growth Supplication Spell Dust inside, then place your Staff on top. Wait a couple seconds and it'll be magically imbued!

Staves have 5 slots that spells can be imbued to. To use some of these however, you'll need specific components. Hovering over the imbued Staff will show you which materials you need. Specifically, for the Grove Supplication, you'll need a tiny bit of Terra Moss and Wildroot. You can store them in your inventory, or preferably in a Component Pouch.

Craft all melee and ranged Roots weapons! They all auto-repair slowly, but can also be repaired with any kind of tree Bark. The Quiver can not only hold Arrows, but if you're out of Arrows, it can conjure some for you for the cost of durability damage on it.

Craft a full set of Wildwood armor! It's slightly tougher than the Sylvan set, and has a chance to heal you over time. However, it has lost its armor regenerating capabilities, but can still be repaired - this time with Wildwood Barks!
Craft an Acid Cloud Spell Dust! When infused onto a Staff, you can hold down Right Click to summon a field of poisonous clouds that constantly damages and knocks back enemies!

Craft one Baffle Cap Mushroom! Then grow it into a tall mushroom in a dark area, or spread it in a dark farm, like you would do with regular Minecraft Mushrooms!

Note: In order to craft this, you need to have visited the Nether, as Lucid Spores and Orange Mushrooms can only be found there.
Craft a Moonglow Leaf! Then convert it into Moonglow Seeds by crafting, and plant it onto any type of Soil to get more!

Craft a Rampant Growth Spell Dust! When infused onto a Staff, you can quickly regrow all crops nearby! It works best with the Harvest spell, so you can immediately harvest and regrow your whole cropfield!
Craft a pair of... Artificial Scarab Wings? What could this be used for?
Craft a Life Drain Spell Dust! When infused onto a Staff, you can shoot a beam which will damage the target and heal you! It's most effective when you can sweep across many enemies.
Craft an Unending Bowl! This block has the exact same functionality as the Endervoir, but it only occupies 1 block of space.

Craft some Floral Fertilizers and use it to gather up all 16 colors of Botania Flowers!

You can craft them into Petals, plant them, grow them with Bone Meal, and finally shear them to get more. You will definitely need to automate this.

After reaching a Tier 2 Blood Altar, craft a Dagger of Sacrifice! Hitting mobs near your Blood Altar with this weapon causes them to bleed into the Altar.

You can either try a Self-Sacrifice build or a Sacrifice build with a mob farm, though with Self-Sacrifice Runes, the former usually works out to be more efficient.
Craft a Mana Pool... or a couple! This is where you store all your Mana! (Not too surprising.)

Place any 8 Dimensional Stone types near your Daisy and wait 30 seconds to obtain Livingrock!

You definitely want to automate this with ME Annihilation and Formation Planes.

You know the drill at the point: Craft all four Tier 4 Essences.

Then take your time to automate every single Blood Magic Essence as you'll be heavily using them from this point on.

As opposed to 1.7.10, you can simply use Item Conduits on your Alchemy Tables for inputs/outputs. To only push 1 set of items at a time, Impluse Hoppers are your best friend!
It's so bulky it might spill...! Watch out.

Craft one of each basic Rune!

You definitely want to automate these and the Runic Altar in general.

betterquesting:10.name:8: If I had to Rune, it would be guess.
betterquesting:10.desc:8:
Craft a Runic Altar! Shoot it with some Mana 'cause it likes being shot by Mana (don't judge).

To craft with it, drop or Right Click the ingredients on the Altar, and once the progress bar fills up, throw a piece of Livingrock on it and hit it with your Wand.

WARNING! WARNING! You want to automate this ASAP! Use an Item Dropper or Precision Dropper and an Auto Clicker with your Wand of the Forest. WARNING OVER. WARNING OVER.

Make a Wand of the Forest! This is your wrench for Botania. You can check the Mana contents of Mana Pools, link Mana Spreaders to Pools and Flowers to Mana Spreaders, and also use it as a toothpick...! Buuuut that last one might not be as important.

betterquesting:10.name:8: Wood you make some of this?
betterquesting:10.desc:8:
Place any 8 Dimensional Wood types upright near your Daisy and wait 30 seconds to obtain Livingwood! Warning: The logs can only be transformed in their original rotation.

You definitely want to automate this with ME Annihilation and Formation Planes.

Use your Ritual Diviner [Dusk] to setup the Mark of the Falling Tower Ritual. It will take:

- 1 Master Ritual Stone,
- 100 additional Ritual Stones,
- 1,000,000 LP in your Life Network,
- an Awakened Activation Crystal, and
- a Potency Core.

Once activated you also need to drop the Potency Core on top of the Master Ritual Stone to summon the Meteor.

WARNING: The Meteor summoned can easily destroy your entire Ritual, but this can easily be stopped if you place a piece of Obsidian about 10-11 blocks above your Master Ritual Stone.

Once successfully done, you can mine up the resulting Electrotine. Pro tip: Fortune and Silk Touch totally work.

Craft some Ritual Stones! You'll definitely need more than the quest suggests, but this is just to guide you towards the right direction!

To setup a Blood Magic Ritual, place a Master Ritual Stone in the center, and use either a regular Ritual Diviner or a Ritual Diviner [Dusk] for more complex Rituals. Hold Right Click until you either run out of Ritual Stones or you've completed the Ritual. You can also color Ritual Stones yourself with Elemental Inscription Tools if you know the exact shape to set them up in.

To activate them, use either a Weak or (more likely) an Awakened Activation Crystal. This will cost some amount of LP from your Life Network.

betterquesting:10.name:8: In the depths of the dungeon...
betterquesting:10.desc:8: While exploring the Dungeon of Cha'garoth, collect the Crystallizer found inside! You'll need to wait a little bit before you can craft the machine itself though...

betterquesting:10.name:8: It's not a cult. It's definitely not a cult.
betterquesting:10.desc:8:
Craft both the bottom and the top pieces of the Altar of Cha'garoth!

To use this, enter the Dreadlands and find a Dreadlands Mountains biome. Dig down to Y=40, make a small room for yourself and place down the bottom of the Altar, then the top. Then you simply need to Right Click the Altar to spawn the Dungeon of Cha'garoth.

betterquesting:10.name:8: Baby you hot like a Thermalily
betterquesting:10.desc:8: Now that you have some Runes, why not use them? One of the better early game Mana Generating Flowers is the Thermalily. It sucks up nearby blocks of Lava to generate a large amount of Mana! Just pump some from the Nether or use a Lava Fabricator to get it going.
Use your Tier 4 Blood Altar to obtain a Master Blood Orb!

Use your Ender Crafter with some Ender Alternators to craft a Petal Apothecary! You might want to immediately automate this.

Drop a Water Bucket on it to fill it, filter Empty Buckets on a Vacuum Chest to pick it up, then dispense the required colored petals for a Botania Flower Petal! A Formation Plane with a small subnet is perfect for this.

Craft the last Tier 1 Rune: The Rune of Mana!

You also definitely want to automate this.
Craft a couple of all the various Mana items!

Craft a Ritual Diviner! This handy tool lets you setup any low-tier Blood Magic Ritual by simply:

- having enough Blank Runes in your inventory,
- and holding Right Click on the Master Ritual Stone.

Normally you could setup any Ritual by hand, color the Runes with Elemental Inscription Tools, but this does the job for you!

To toggle between Rituals, simple Shift+Right Click or Shift+Left Click.

betterquesting:10.name:8: From a Blood Mage to a Shaman...
betterquesting:10.desc:8:
Your first step of becoming a Blood Shaman is to create Rituals that consume your Life Essence for a magical effect!

For this, you'll need all 4 of these Elemental Inscription Tools. They can be used to color Blank Runes. But you might want to use a Ritual Diviner if you're unsure what each Ritual looks like exactly.

betterquesting:10.name:8: Don't get lazy, make a daisy!
betterquesting:10.desc:8:
If the daisy
Makes you crazy,
Be more hasty
Biosafety!

In this quest, you are tasked to build the Well of Suffering Ritual directly above or below your Blood Altar.

Once activated this Ritual will constantly damage nearby mobs while filling up the Altar, giving you access to Blood and LP automation.

The best mob to use are Witches, because they naturally regenerate, but you can also try any of the following:
   - Any mob + The Ritual of Regeneration,
   - A Powered Spawner constantly spawning mobs,
   - Cursed Earth constantly spawning mobs.

To automate LP gain, simple leave a bound Blood Orb in the Blood Altar you set this automation up at.

betterquesting:10.name:8: Adding a little darkness never hurts!
betterquesting:10.desc:8: Craft a Ritual Diviner [Dusk]! This will let you setup higher-tier Rituals, which you'll need a lot of to progress.

Craft some Bound Tools! The only one you'll need for progression is the Bound Pickaxe which will let you break and collect Ethaxium in Omothol - right after finishing this Chapter... So no need to hurry with this one!

To activate one of these tools, simply press Shift+Right Click. Each tool drains LP from your Soul Network while it's active and consumes additional LP on use. Be careful!

Craft some Manasteel Tools. These will later be upgraded into Bound Tools, which have a high Mining level and can break Ethaxium in Omothol. However, you won't necessarily need them before finishing this chapter.

betterquesting:10.name:8: This is where being hemophobic truely sucks...
betterquesting:10.desc:8:
Slay enough mobs and obtain enough Weak Blood Shards to be able to craft 5 Large Bloodstone Tiles! Use 4 of them to upgrade your Blood Altar to Tier 4 and the remaining one to obtain a Tier 4 Blood Orb!

You can also duplicate Weak Blood Shards with a Tier 4 Slate once you built up the Altar.

If you're unsure of the Altar's construction, check this site: https://ftb.gamepedia.com/Blood_Altar
Craft two Dusk Elemental Inscription Tools! This is the final piece to unlock higher tier Rituals (pretty much all of the useful ones).
Craft the listed AbyssalCraft Clusters in your Crystallizer! These are the most important ones that you'll need for the upcoming quests, although you'll need more than just these in the longrun.
asd
asd
