betterquesting:10.name:8: Ouchy! Don't put this on your head.
betterquesting:10.desc:8: Find four Effulgent Apalachian Spikes and combine them... Now what could this yield?
Craft all four Tier 4 Essences. Try to semi-automate them for now; very soon you'll have access to Will automation as well.
Craft an Angelic Silicon/Crystal mixture.... This is very peculiar.
Using the setup explained in the previous quest, acquire four of all types of Will Crystals!

Craft a Beacon! You'll eventually need 4 of them to upgrade your Blood Magic Altar to Tier 5! No need to hurry though. Kill some Withers and explore more of Atum in your freetime to get more of its crafting ingredients!
Now that you have access to Will Crystals, craft a Greater Tartaric Gem! Isn't it Great? (-er.)

Create all 4 Tier 2 Runes!

It's getting complicated....

Guess what I'm gonna recommend you...... Yes, automate these as well. All of their ingredients too. Now go!
Craft a batch of Wildwood Blocks! You know the drill at this point: set them up in a Nether Portal shape, light it with a Twilight Clock and enter Apalachia!

Place any 8 Dimensional Dirt types near your Daisy and wait 30 seconds to obtain Livingmatter!

You definitely want to automate this with ME Annihilation and Formation Planes.

Craft a Spectre of Thunder! This is a one time use item that lets you create a Thunderstorm. Capture the storm in an Environmental Accumulator found all around the overworld for an ingredient in the Awakened Activation Crystal!
Craft a Sigil of the Blood Lamp! This is my personal favorite Sigil, letting you light up areas from a distance by shooting little invisible Blood Lamp thingamadoohickies. No more Torches!

betterquesting:10.name:8: Make the Slate and don't be Late
betterquesting:10.desc:8:
Craft a couple Tier 4 (Demonic) Blood Magic Slates!

This is a good point to take your time and automate all available Slates up to this point. You can create an elaborate timing system for each one, or simply multiple Altars with specific filters on the outputs.

The easiest way is to create 2 Altars, with alternating Slate crafting: filter the outputs for Tier 1 and 3 Slates on one of them, and Tier 2 and 4 Slates on the other, and use ME Interfaces as inputs. This system will always reliably craft the wanted Slate, even if an insufficient amount of Blood is available. You can later expand it to Tier 5 and 6 Slates... and beyond!?

Bind a Blade to your Soul! (I'm suuuure you'll Soul will be fiiiine after so don't worry about it!)

To activate it, press Shift+Right Click. But be wary, while its active, it will drain LP from your Soul Network. Ouch!
Craft a Manasteel Sword! It's the most important tool for progression at this point.
Upgrade your Divination Sigil into a Seer's Sigil. This shows additional information when Right Clicked on a Blood Altar, namely the current progress and the LP consumption rate.
Upgrade your Weak Activation Crystal into its Awakened variant and bind it to yourself. You now have the ability to activate ANY Blood Magic Ritual.

Craft a Weak Activation Crystal! Bind it to yourself by Shift+Right Clicking in the air. By Right Clicking on a Master Ritual Stone, you can sacrifice some of the LP stored in your Life Network to activate the Ritual.

If it's not working, any of the following may be the culprit:
- The Ritual isn't setup correctly. Maybe you need more Ritual Stones?
- You need an Awakened Activation Crystal.
- You don't have enough LP in your Life Network.

Make some Endoflames! Provide them with Coal for Mana Generation. Check if they're connected to a nearby Mana Spreader using your Wand of the Forest.

You definitely want to automate this with Droppers on a Timer dropping Coal Blocks.

betterquesting:10.name:8: We're really going deep this time...
betterquesting:10.desc:8: Craft Cha'garoth's R'lyehian Gateway Key! This will let you create any AbyssalCraft portal by Right Clicking (for the next Portal) or Shift+Right Clicking (for the previous Portal). Use it in the Dreadlands to create a Portal to Omothol!

Defeat Cha'garoth to obtain his Dread-plagued Gateway Key! You can't directly use this to escape the Dreadlands, so hopefully you still know where your portal is...

Continue with the quests to be able to upgrade it to an actual functional key!

betterquesting:10.name:8: Will you do this for me?
betterquesting:10.desc:8:
=================================
      AUTOMATING WILL GENERATION
=================================

In this quest, I will provide you with information on how to setup automatic Will generation. You can choose to either read on, or watch this incredible tutorial video:

https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=K25QmSmfTRA&ab_channel=MarzuleStreams

(If §ryou can't copy the link, simply search for the title of the video: "Blood Magic - Demon Will Automation Tutorial" by Marzule Streams.)

If you chose to read on, here is a step by step breakdown on how to create infinite Blood Magic Will and Will Crystals:

§lSTEP 1.§r Obtain a couple Common Tartaric Gems with at least a couple thousand Will overall, and have at least 1,000,000 LP in your Life Network. Make sure to have every step of Ritual Stone crafting fully automated, except for automatic Will collection for Reagents. (This means you need to fully automate Tenebrae and Void Reagent creation. After this setup, you won't need to worry about your Tartaric Gems running out either.)

§lSTEP 2.§r Press F9 to see the chunk boarders. Make this build entirely in ONE chunk, because Will is stored in Minecraft's chunks separately.

§lSTEP 3.§r You have 2 options here: Use a couple Powered Spawners to spawn passive animals in the chunk; or place a Master Ritual Stone in the center of the chunk and setup the Ritual of Peaceful Souls with your Ritual Diviner [Dusk] and activate it with your Awakened Activation Crystal.

§lSTEP 4.§r Go up about 4-5 blocks from your Master Ritual Stone or the floor of your Powered Spawner room and place another Master Ritual Stone. Setup the Gathering of Forsaken Souls Ritual with your Ritual Diviner [Dusk] here. Activate it with your Awakened Activation Crystal.

§lSTEP 5.§r Place a solid block on top of your previous Master Ritual Stone, and place another Master Ritual Stone on top. Setup the Resonance of the Faceted Crystal Ritual with your Ritual Diviner [Dusk] on this one. Also activate it with your Awakened Activation Crystal. This will interlock wi§tth the Ritual below.

§lSTEP 6.§r Place a Demon Crystallizer on top of the most recent Master Ritual Stone.

§lSTEP 7.§r Build a platform out of solid blocks on the highest level of Ritual Stones, so that your Demon Crystallizer is the only thing poking out.

§lSTEP 8.§r Place 5 Demon Crucibles somewhere on your platform. Place some Tartaric Gems that contain at least a couple hundred points of Will into some of the Demon Crucibles.

§lSTEP 9.§r (Optinal, but recommended.) Make a Demon Will Aura Gauge. It shows you the amount of Will stored in the Chunk (on the first bar, because we're creating regular Will for now). A Chunk can only hold up to 100 Will. The Demon Crucibles keep this filled up while the Resonance of the Faceted Crystal Ritual drains this and creates Will crystals.

§lSTEP 10.§r It's a waiting game now! Wait until a regular Demon Crystal forms on top of your Demon Crystallizer, then splits, then creates 4 types of colored Demon Will Crystals nearby, then those split as well. If you see a total of 5 clusters of crystals with 6 spikes each, you're done. If you have to wait for a long time but still see no results, check your Demon Will Aura Gauge to see if you have ran out of Will. If so, refill your Tartaric Gem(s) in the Demon Crucible(s).

§lSTEP 11.§r Collect your crystal clusters and break your Demon Crystallizer. Use a Ritual Dismantler to also get rid of the topmost Ritual (Resonance of the Faceted Crystal). Simply Right Click twice, but don't accidentally hit the Rituals below. If parts of your platform are missing, replace those.

§lSTEP 12.§r Place 5 Drawers or Barrels nearby. Place each type of Will Crystal you just collected in its own separate Drawer/Barrel, then lock them with a Drawer Key / Storage Key.

§lSTEP 13.§r Now you can reclaim your Tartaric Gem(s) from the Demon Crucible(s). Then place a Hellfire Forge somewhere on your platform (in the same chunk). Place a Tartaric Gem inside (into the right slot) with a fair amount of Will. This can also suck up any excess Will you have in the chunk (up to 100). Then remove your Tartaric Gem from your Hellfire Forge, so it no longer sucks up the regular Demon Will from the chunk.

§lSTEP 14.§r Take 4 pieces of each of the Will Crystals from your Drawers / Barrels and use your Tartaric Forge to create a placable Crystal Cluster of each type.

§lSTEP 15.§r Place down all 5 Crystal Clusters you just crafted somewhere on your platform (still in the same chunk).

§lSTEP 16.§r Connect your Drawers / Barrels to your Demon Crucibles the following way: Each Drawer / Barrel should be connected to its own Crucible, and the Drawers / Barrels should be able to accept additional items. You can do this with a single line of EnderIO Item Conduits and 5 unique channel colors. Don't forget to set the Drawer / Barrel side to Extract (Always Active) on a specific channel and Insert on Green, and the Crucible side to Insert on the corresponding channel.

§lSTEP 17.§r Hop down below your platform and place yet another Master Ritual Stone below the one that's doing the the Gathering of Forsaken Souls Ritual (built in STEP 4 - right below your platform). Use a Ritual Diviner [Dusk] to build the Crack of the Fractured Crystal Ritual, which interlocks with the previous Rituals. Activate it with your Awakened Activation Crystal.

§lSTEP 18.§r Place a Vacuum Chest with an Item Filter right above your Crystal Clusters somewhere. Set the Item Filter to collect the Demon Crystals that are popping off right now.

§lSTEP 19.§r Extract your Vacuum Chest's inventory to your Drawers / Barrels.

§lSTEP 20.§r Congratulations! Your setup is now self-sustaining. Each type of Will Crystal will slowly move to a Demon Crucible, which fills up the Chunk with a particular type of Will, which let your placed down Crystal Clusters grow. Of course this is a farm, so Crystal growth is faster than the Crystals being used up. However be careful not to use up ALL your Crystals of a certain type. If you do so, Crystal generation of that type will stop. If you also don't have a Tartaric Gem of the specific type of will, then you'll unfortunately have to start again from STEP 5, building the Resonance of the Faceted Crystal Ritual. Otherwise, simply stick your Tartaric Gem of the correct type in the Demon Crucible that's missing its Crystal and wait for the Will in the chunk to regenerate.

§lSTEP 21.§r Once you have a fully self-sustaining setup (probably around 100 Crystals of each type), you can place your Tartaric Gem back into your Hellfire Forge to automatically keep it filled up with Will. You might want to automate Hellfire Forge recipes in this Chunk, so you'll never have to refill your Tartaric Gems again.

§lSTEP 22. (OPTIONAL)§r You can create the same exact setup in multiple chunks, or even the same chunk (and I recommend it). Just watch your Will levels with your Demon Will Aura Gauge. If they start decreasing, it's probably best to move to another chunk.

Craft a Mana Spreader! This is the block you use to transfer Mana from your generating Flowers to your Mana Pools. Use your Wand of the Forest to bind it to each.

Mana for you, and for you; mana for everybody!
Now that you have access to Blood Magic Will Crystals, you can craft your own Crystallizers as well. Do so!

betterquesting:10.name:8: Blood contains Iron -> Iron is Magnetic!
betterquesting:10.desc:8: Craft a Sigil of Magnetism. This ISN'T a direct upgrade over your previous Magnet, however it IS used for even better (Botania) Magnets later on.

Craft some Runes of Augmented Capacity. Each one increases the Blood Altar's capacity by 10%.

They aren't a straight upgrade over your previous Capacity Runes, however as they grant a multiplicative increase, they scale much better than their earlier counterparts.

It comes out to having 15 Augmented Capacity Runes is slightly better than 15 Runes of Capacity, and from that point, including 1 Augmented Capacity Rune is better (later much better) than 1 Rune of Capacity.

Meaning that if you have at least 15 Augmented Capacity Runes, you should only use them from that point on.
Craft a Horn of the Wild! Simply holding Right Click with this tool will let you clear any tall-grassy area for you to more easily build upon.
Craft a Sigil of Magnetism! This isn't a straight upgrade over your previous Magnet, but it's going to be used to make Botania Magnets, which are even better than the QuantumFlux one.
Learn about DJ2, go through some tweaked Vanilla progression, and get into Tinker's Construct!
Chug through Immersive Engineering and get your first sip of power. Gain powerful exploration tools in the Slimesling and Hang Glider.
Fight through the Nether, which has significant new challenges from Better Nether, and decide if you want to venture into the Twilight Forest.
Jump into Mekanism, and drive your storage to new heights with Applied Energistics 2's ME system.
Scavenge for materials in Atum 2 and become arachnophobic in The Erebus.
Float through the Aether from Aether Legacy, freeze in Iceika, conquer the Ender Dragon, and get devoured by the Deep Dark.
Unlock Grid Power and work through Extra Utilities 2, gain access to some useful OpenBlocks items and blocks, and unlock the ability to create extremely powerful mob farms from mob_grinding_utils.

Crank through Thermal Expansion, unlock the End, unlock Fluid storage, and progress through EnderIO.

Also beat the game with the Crafting Terminal.

Blow right into plastic and Industrial Foregoing - and blow up right into QuantumFlux.
Also unlock the world-eating power of the Builder, Solar Panels from Solar Flux Reborn, and the all-powerful Integrated Dynamics.

Zap your way into Actually Additions, unlocking Phantomfaces, Dimensional Transceivers, and Ender IO's Powered Spawner!
Also unlock the ability to elevate yourself with Jetpacks and Jetplates.

Unlock Mekanism's multiblocks, the Laser Drill, the Rainbow Generator, Ender Utilities, AND ME Autocrafting in this packed Chapter.

Also unlock a Cardboard Box.
Fight 3 bosses from DivineRPG, venture into Eden and the Wildwoods, gain 5x5 crafting from Extended Crafting, and go insane with AbyssalCraft.
Sacrifice to Blood Magic: Alchemical Wizardy and murder with EvilCraft, featuring the return of 1.7.10 Essences.
Let Botania grow on you, unlock the 4th tier of Blood Altar for Blood Magic, unlock Rituals and Will, adventure through Apalachia, and conquer the boss of The Dreadlands.
Pour over Thaumcraft, go verifiably mad, and go to Skythern and Mortum.
Brew and boil with Witchery, summon demons, and devour bosses.
Begin anew in Vethea, electrify your world with LightningCraft, and irradiate your world with Extreme Reactors.
Collapse on Thaumcraft and Thaumic Augmentations, and unlock digital storage and crafting for your Essentia needs.
Gaze into Astral Sorcery, unlocking its many powerful weapons, tools, and other perks.
Blast off with GalactiCraft, and unlock a more effiecent way of Empowering!
Breathe through Draconic Evolution, and unlock PackagedAuto for larger patterns.
Get back to your foundation with Alchemistry.
Exploit brand new worlds with RFTools Dimensions.
... mysterious ...
Explore Totemic and fight its boss Baykok.
Dig through Roots, an agriculturally themed Magic Mod.
Unlock their secrets in Omothol and the Dark Realm, bud with Terrasteel, fight the Gaia Guardians, and alloy the highest tier EnderIO metal.
